187 static OOMErrorCallback g_oom_error_callback = nullptr;
188 
189 using RCCId = i::RuntimeCallCounterId;
190 
191 static ScriptOrigin GetScriptOriginForScript(
192  i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script) {
193  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> scriptName(script->GetNameOrSourceURL(),
194  i_isolate);
195  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> source_map_url(script->source_mapping_url(),
196  i_isolate);
197  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> host_defined_options(
198  script->host_defined_options(), i_isolate);
199  ScriptOriginOptions options(script->origin_options());
200  bool is_wasm = false;
201 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
202  is_wasm = script->type() == i::Script::Type::kWasm;
203 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
204  v8::ScriptOrigin origin(
205  Utils::ToLocal(scriptName), script->line_offset(),
206  script->column_offset(), options.IsSharedCrossOrigin(), script->id(),
207  Utils::ToLocal(source_map_url), options.IsOpaque(), is_wasm,
208  options.IsModule(), Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options));
209  return origin;
210 }

214 // When V8 cannot allocate memory FatalProcessOutOfMemory is called. The default
215 // OOM error handler is called and execution is stopped.
216 void i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const char* location,
217  const OOMDetails& details) {
218  i::HeapStats heap_stats;
219 
220  if (i_isolate == nullptr) {
221  i_isolate = Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
222  }
223 
224  if (i_isolate == nullptr) {
225  // If the Isolate is not available for the current thread we cannot retrieve
226  // memory information from the Isolate. Write easy-to-recognize values on
227  // the stack.
228  memset(&heap_stats, 0xBADC0DE, sizeof(heap_stats));
229  // Give the embedder a chance to handle the condition. If it doesn't,
230  // just crash.
231  if (g_oom_error_callback) g_oom_error_callback(location, details);
232  base::FatalOOM(base::OOMType::kProcess, location);
233  UNREACHABLE();
234  }
235 
236  memset(heap_stats.last_few_messages, 0, Heap::kTraceRingBufferSize + 1);
237 
238  if (i_isolate->heap()->HasBeenSetUp()) {
239  i_isolate->heap()->RecordStats(&heap_stats);
240  if (!v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
241  char* first_newline = strchr(heap_stats.last_few_messages, '\n');
242  if (first_newline == nullptr || first_newline[1] == '\0')
243  first_newline = heap_stats.last_few_messages;
244  base::OS::PrintError("\n<--- Last few GCs --->\n%s\n", first_newline);
245  }
246  }
247  Utils::ReportOOMFailure(i_isolate, location, details);
248  if (g_oom_error_callback) g_oom_error_callback(location, details);
249  // If the fatal error handler returns, we stop execution.
250  FATAL("API fatal error handler returned after process out of memory");
251 }
252 
253 void i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const char* location,
254  const char* detail) {
255  OOMDetails details;
256  details.detail = detail;
257  FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, location, details);
258 }
259 
260 void Utils::ReportApiFailure(const char* location, const char* message) {
261  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
262  FatalErrorCallback callback = nullptr;
263  if (i_isolate != nullptr) {
264  callback = i_isolate->exception_behavior();
265  }
266  if (callback == nullptr) {
267  base::OS::PrintError("\n#\n# Fatal error in %s\n# %s\n#\n\n", location,
268  message);
269  base::OS::Abort();
270  } else {
271  callback(location, message);
272  }
273  i_isolate->SignalFatalError();
274 }
275 
276 void Utils::ReportOOMFailure(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const char* location,
277  const OOMDetails& details) {
278  if (auto oom_callback = i_isolate->oom_behavior()) {
279  oom_callback(location, details);
280  } else {
281  // TODO(wfh): Remove this fallback once Blink is setting OOM handler. See
282  // crbug.com/614440.
283  FatalErrorCallback fatal_callback = i_isolate->exception_behavior();
284  if (fatal_callback == nullptr) {
285  base::OOMType type = details.is_heap_oom ? base::OOMType::kJavaScript
286  : base::OOMType::kProcess;
287  base::FatalOOM(type, location);
288  UNREACHABLE();
289  } else {
290  fatal_callback(location,
291  details.is_heap_oom
292  ? "Allocation failed - JavaScript heap out of memory"
293  : "Allocation failed - process out of memory");
294  }
295  }
296  i_isolate->SignalFatalError();
297 }

305 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
306 // ArrayBufferAllocator to use when the sandbox is enabled in which case all
307 // ArrayBuffer backing stores need to be allocated inside the sandbox.
308 class ArrayBufferAllocator : public v8::ArrayBuffer::Allocator {
309  public:
310  explicit ArrayBufferAllocator(i::IsolateGroup* group)
311  : sandbox_(group->sandbox()),
312  allocator_(group->GetSandboxedArrayBufferAllocator()) {}
313 
314  void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
315  return allocator_->Allocate(length);
316  }
317 
318  void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
319  return Allocate(length);
320  }
321 
322  void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
323  return allocator_->Free(data);
324  }
325 
326  PageAllocator* GetPageAllocator() override {
327  return sandbox_->page_allocator();
328  }
329 
330  private:
331  i::Sandbox* sandbox_ = nullptr;
332  i::SandboxedArrayBufferAllocator* allocator_ = nullptr;
333 };
334 
335 #else
336 
337 class ArrayBufferAllocator : public v8::ArrayBuffer::Allocator {
338  public:
339  void* Allocate(size_t length) override { return base::Calloc(length, 1); }
340 
341  void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
342  return base::Malloc(length);
343  }
344 
345  void Free(void* data, size_t) override { base::Free(data); }
346 
347  PageAllocator* GetPageAllocator() override {
348  return i::GetPlatformPageAllocator();
349  }
350 };
351 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX

450 RegisteredExtension* RegisteredExtension::first_extension_ = nullptr;
451 
452 RegisteredExtension::RegisteredExtension(std::unique_ptr<Extension> extension)
453  : extension_(std::move(extension)) {}
454 
455 // static
456 void RegisteredExtension::Register(std::unique_ptr<Extension> extension) {
457  RegisteredExtension* new_extension =
458  new RegisteredExtension(std::move(extension));
459  new_extension->next_ = first_extension_;
460  first_extension_ = new_extension;
461 }
462 
463 // static
464 void RegisteredExtension::UnregisterAll() {
465  RegisteredExtension* re = first_extension_;
466  while (re != nullptr) {
467  RegisteredExtension* next = re->next();
468  delete re;
469  re = next;
470  }
471  first_extension_ = nullptr;
472 }

474 namespace {
475 class ExtensionResource : public String::ExternalOneByteStringResource {
476  public:
477  ExtensionResource() : data_(nullptr), length_(0) {}
478  ExtensionResource(const char* data, size_t length)
479  : data_(data), length_(length) {}
480  const char* data() const override { return data_; }
481  size_t length() const override { return length_; }
482  void Dispose() override {}
483 
484  private:
485  const char* data_;
486  size_t length_;
487 };
488 } // anonymous namespace

494 Extension::Extension(const char* name, const char* source, int dep_count,
495  const char** deps, int source_length)
496  : name_(name),
497  source_length_(source_length >= 0
498  ? source_length
499  : (source ? static_cast<int>(strlen(source)) : 0)),
500  dep_count_(dep_count),
501  deps_(deps),
502  auto_enable_(false) {
503  source_ = new ExtensionResource(source, source_length_);
504  CHECK(source != nullptr || source_length_ == 0);
505 }
506 
507 void ResourceConstraints::ConfigureDefaultsFromHeapSize(
508  size_t initial_heap_size_in_bytes, size_t maximum_heap_size_in_bytes) {
509  CHECK_LE(initial_heap_size_in_bytes, maximum_heap_size_in_bytes);
510  if (maximum_heap_size_in_bytes == 0) {
511  return;
512  }
513  size_t young_generation, old_generation;
514  i::Heap::GenerationSizesFromHeapSize(maximum_heap_size_in_bytes,
515  &young_generation, &old_generation);
516  set_max_young_generation_size_in_bytes(
517  std::max(young_generation, i::Heap::MinYoungGenerationSize()));
518  set_max_old_generation_size_in_bytes(
519  std::max(old_generation, i::Heap::MinOldGenerationSize()));
520  if (initial_heap_size_in_bytes > 0) {
521  i::Heap::GenerationSizesFromHeapSize(initial_heap_size_in_bytes,
522  &young_generation, &old_generation);
523  // We do not set lower bounds for the initial sizes.
524  set_initial_young_generation_size_in_bytes(young_generation);
525  set_initial_old_generation_size_in_bytes(old_generation);
526  }
527  if (i::kPlatformRequiresCodeRange) {
528  set_code_range_size_in_bytes(
529  std::min(i::kMaximalCodeRangeSize, maximum_heap_size_in_bytes));
530  }
531 }
532 
533 void ResourceConstraints::ConfigureDefaults(uint64_t physical_memory,
534  uint64_t virtual_memory_limit) {
535  size_t heap_size = i::Heap::HeapSizeFromPhysicalMemory(physical_memory);
536  size_t young_generation, old_generation;
537  i::Heap::GenerationSizesFromHeapSize(heap_size, &young_generation,
538  &old_generation);
539  set_max_young_generation_size_in_bytes(young_generation);
540  set_max_old_generation_size_in_bytes(old_generation);
541 
542  if (virtual_memory_limit > 0 && i::kPlatformRequiresCodeRange) {
543  set_code_range_size_in_bytes(
544  std::min(i::kMaximalCodeRangeSize,
545  static_cast<size_t>(virtual_memory_limit / 8)));
546  }
547 }

571 i::Address* GlobalizeTracedReference(
572  i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::Address value, internal::Address* slot,
573  TracedReferenceStoreMode store_mode,
574  TracedReferenceHandling reference_handling) {

576  ->Create(value, slot, store_mode, reference_handling)
577  .location();
578 }

603 #define EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING(V) \
604  V(UndefinedValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue) \
605  V(NullValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue) \
606  V(TrueValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTrueValue) \
607  V(FalseValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFalseValue) \
608  V(EmptyString, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kempty_string) \
609  V(TheHoleValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTheHoleValue) \
610  V(StringMapLowerBound, kStringMapRange.first) \
611  V(StringMapUpperBound, kStringMapRange.second)
612 
613 static_assert(std::is_same_v<Internals::Tagged_t, Tagged_t>);
614 // Ensure they have the correct value.
615 #define CHECK_STATIC_ROOT(name, value) \
616  static_assert(Internals::StaticReadOnlyRoot::k##name == value);
617 EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING(CHECK_STATIC_ROOT)
618 #undef CHECK_STATIC_ROOT
619 #define PLUS_ONE(...) +1
620 static constexpr int kNumberOfCheckedStaticRoots =
621  0 EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING(PLUS_ONE);
622 #undef EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING
623 static_assert(Internals::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNumberOfExportedStaticRoots ==
624  kNumberOfCheckedStaticRoots);
625 
626 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL

700 
701 HandleScope::HandleScope(Isolate* v8_isolate) { Initialize(v8_isolate); }
702 
703 void HandleScope::Initialize(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
704  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
705  // We do not want to check the correct usage of the Locker class all over the
706  // place, so we do it only here: Without a HandleScope, an embedder can do
707  // almost nothing, so it is enough to check in this central place.
708  // We make an exception if the serializer is enabled, which means that the
709  // Isolate is exclusively used to create a snapshot.
710  Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->was_locker_ever_used() ||
711  i_isolate->thread_manager()->IsLockedByCurrentThread() ||
712  i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
713  "HandleScope::HandleScope",
714  "Entering the V8 API without proper locking in place");
715  i::HandleScopeData* current = i_isolate->handle_scope_data();
716  i_isolate_ = i_isolate;
717  prev_next_ = current->next;
718  prev_limit_ = current->limit;
719  current->level++;
720 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
721  scope_level_ = current->level;
722 #endif
723 }
724 
725 HandleScope::~HandleScope() {
726 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
727  CHECK_EQ(scope_level_, i_isolate_->handle_scope_data()->level);
728 #endif
729  i::HandleScope::CloseScope(i_isolate_, prev_next_, prev_limit_);
730 }
731 
732 void* HandleScope::operator new(size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
733 void* HandleScope::operator new[](size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
734 void HandleScope::operator delete(void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
735 void HandleScope::operator delete[](void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }

765  reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(GetIsolate())));

770 SealHandleScope::SealHandleScope(Isolate* v8_isolate)
771  : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)) {
772  i::HandleScopeData* current = i_isolate_->handle_scope_data();
773  prev_limit_ = current->limit;
774  current->limit = current->next;
775  prev_sealed_level_ = current->sealed_level;
776  current->sealed_level = current->level;
777 }
778 
779 SealHandleScope::~SealHandleScope() {
780  i::HandleScopeData* current = i_isolate_->handle_scope_data();
781  DCHECK_EQ(current->next, current->limit);
782  current->limit = prev_limit_;
783  DCHECK_EQ(current->level, current->sealed_level);
784  current->sealed_level = prev_sealed_level_;
785 }

799 bool Data::IsValue() const {
800  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
801  i::Tagged<i::Object> self = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
802  if (i::IsSmi(self)) return true;
803  i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> heap_object = i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(self);
804  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(heap_object));
805  if (i::IsSymbol(heap_object)) {
806  return !i::Cast<i::Symbol>(heap_object)->is_private();
807  }
808  return IsPrimitiveHeapObject(heap_object) || IsJSReceiver(heap_object);
809 }

831 void Context::Enter() {
832  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
833  i::Tagged<i::NativeContext> env = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
834  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
835  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
836  i::HandleScopeImplementer* impl = i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer();
837  impl->EnterContext(env);
838  impl->SaveContext(i_isolate->context());
839  i_isolate->set_context(env);
840 }
841 
842 void Context::Exit() {
843  auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
844  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
845  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
846  i::HandleScopeImplementer* impl = i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer();
847  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(impl->LastEnteredContextWas(*env), "v8::Context::Exit()",
848  "Cannot exit non-entered context")) {
849  return;
850  }
851  impl->LeaveContext();
852  i_isolate->set_context(impl->RestoreContext());
853 }

855 Context::BackupIncumbentScope::BackupIncumbentScope(
856  Local<Context> backup_incumbent_context)
857  : backup_incumbent_context_(backup_incumbent_context) {
858  DCHECK(!backup_incumbent_context_.IsEmpty());
859 
860  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
861 
862  js_stack_comparable_address_ =
863  i::SimulatorStack::RegisterJSStackComparableAddress(i_isolate);
864 
865  prev_ = i_isolate->top_backup_incumbent_scope();
866  i_isolate->set_top_backup_incumbent_scope(this);
867  // Enforce slow incumbent computation in order to make it find this
868  // BackupIncumbentScope.
869  i_isolate->clear_topmost_script_having_context();
870 }
871 
872 Context::BackupIncumbentScope::~BackupIncumbentScope() {
873  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
874 
875  i::SimulatorStack::UnregisterJSStackComparableAddress(i_isolate);
876 
877  i_isolate->set_top_backup_incumbent_scope(prev_);
878 }

880 static_assert(i::Internals::kEmbedderDataSlotSize == i::kEmbedderDataSlotSize);
881 static_assert(i::Internals::kEmbedderDataSlotExternalPointerOffset ==
882  i::EmbedderDataSlot::kExternalPointerOffset);
883 
884 static i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> EmbedderDataFor(
885  Context* context, int index, bool can_grow, const char* location) {
886  auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(context);
887  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
888  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution(i_isolate);
889  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions(i_isolate);
890  bool ok = Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsNativeContext(*env), location,
891  "Not a native context") &&
892  Utils::ApiCheck(index >= 0, location, "Negative index");
893  if (!ok) return {};
894  // TODO(ishell): remove cast once embedder_data slot has a proper type.
895  i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data(
896  i::Cast<i::EmbedderDataArray>(env->embedder_data()), i_isolate);
897  if (index < data->length()) return data;
898  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(can_grow && index < i::EmbedderDataArray::kMaxLength,
899  location, "Index too large")) {
900  return {};
901  }
902  data = i::EmbedderDataArray::EnsureCapacity(i_isolate, data, index);
903  env->set_embedder_data(*data);
904  return data;
905 }
906 
907 uint32_t Context::GetNumberOfEmbedderDataFields() {
908  auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
909  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution;
910  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions;
911  Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsNativeContext(*context),
912  "Context::GetNumberOfEmbedderDataFields",
913  "Not a native context");
914  // TODO(ishell): remove cast once embedder_data slot has a proper type.
915  return static_cast<uint32_t>(
916  i::Cast<i::EmbedderDataArray>(context->embedder_data())->length());
917 }
918 
919 v8::Local<v8::Value> Context::SlowGetEmbedderData(int index) {
920  const char* location = "v8::Context::GetEmbedderData()";
921  i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
922  EmbedderDataFor(this, index, false, location);
923  if (data.is_null()) return {};
924  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
925  return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
926  i::EmbedderDataSlot(*data, index).load_tagged(), i_isolate));
927 }

929 void Context::SetEmbedderData(int index, v8::Local<Value> value) {
930  const char* location = "v8::Context::SetEmbedderData()";
931  i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
932  EmbedderDataFor(this, index, true, location);
933  if (data.is_null()) return;
934  auto val = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
935  i::EmbedderDataSlot::store_tagged(*data, index, *val);
936  DCHECK_EQ(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value),
937  *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*GetEmbedderData(index)));
938 }

940 void* Context::SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
941  const char* location = "v8::Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData()";
942  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
943  i::HandleScope handle_scope(i_isolate);
944  i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
945  EmbedderDataFor(this, index, false, location);
946  if (data.is_null()) return nullptr;
947  void* result;
948  Utils::ApiCheck(
949  i::EmbedderDataSlot(*data, index).ToAlignedPointer(i_isolate, &result),
950  location, "Pointer is not aligned");
951  return result;
952 }

954 void Context::SetAlignedPointerInEmbedderData(int index, void* value) {
955  const char* location = "v8::Context::SetAlignedPointerInEmbedderData()";
956  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
957  i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
958  EmbedderDataFor(this, index, true, location);
959  bool ok = i::EmbedderDataSlot(*data, index)
960  .store_aligned_pointer(i_isolate, *data, value);
961  Utils::ApiCheck(ok, location, "Pointer is not aligned");
962  DCHECK_EQ(value, GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index));
963 }

966 
967 void Template::Set(v8::Local<Name> name, v8::Local<Data> value,
968  v8::PropertyAttribute attribute) {
969  auto templ = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
970  i::Isolate* i_isolate = templ->GetIsolateChecked();
971  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
972  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
973  auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
974 
975  Utils::ApiCheck(!IsJSReceiver(*value_obj) || IsTemplateInfo(*value_obj),
976  "v8::Template::Set",
977  "Invalid value, must be a primitive or a Template");
978 
979  // The template cache only performs shallow clones, if we set an
980  // ObjectTemplate as a property value then we can not cache the receiver
981  // template.
982  if (i::IsObjectTemplateInfo(*value_obj)) {
983  templ->set_is_cacheable(false);
984  }
985 
986  i::ApiNatives::AddDataProperty(i_isolate, templ,
987  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name), value_obj,
988  static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attribute));
989 }
990

992  v8::PropertyAttribute attribute) {
993  Set(Local<Name>::Cast(name), value, attribute);
994 }
995 
996 void Template::SetAccessorProperty(v8::Local<v8::Name> name,
997  v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> getter,
998  v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> setter,
999  v8::PropertyAttribute attribute) {
1000  auto templ = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1001  auto i_isolate = templ->GetIsolateChecked();
1002  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> i_getter;
1003  if (!getter.IsEmpty()) {
1004  i_getter = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*getter);
1005  Utils::ApiCheck(i_getter->has_callback(i_isolate),
1006  "v8::Template::SetAccessorProperty",
1007  "Getter must have a call handler");
1008  }
1009  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> i_setter;
1010  if (!setter.IsEmpty()) {
1011  i_setter = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*setter);
1012  Utils::ApiCheck(i_setter->has_callback(i_isolate),
1013  "v8::Template::SetAccessorProperty",
1014  "Setter must have a call handler");
1015  }
1016  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1017  DCHECK(!name.IsEmpty());
1018  DCHECK(!getter.IsEmpty() || !setter.IsEmpty());
1019  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1020  i::ApiNatives::AddAccessorProperty(
1021  i_isolate, templ, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name), i_getter, i_setter,
1022  static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attribute));
1023 }

1027 Local<ObjectTemplate> FunctionTemplate::PrototypeTemplate() {
1028  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1029  i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolateChecked();
1030  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1031  i::DirectHandle<i::HeapObject> heap_obj(self->GetPrototypeTemplate(),
1032  i_isolate);
1033  if (i::IsUndefined(*heap_obj, i_isolate)) {
1034  // Do not cache prototype objects.
1035  constexpr bool do_not_cache = true;
1036  i::DirectHandle<i::ObjectTemplateInfo> proto_template =
1037  i_isolate->factory()->NewObjectTemplateInfo({}, do_not_cache);
1038  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetPrototypeTemplate(i_isolate, self,
1039  proto_template);
1040  return Utils::ToLocal(proto_template);
1041  }
1042  return ToApiHandle<ObjectTemplate>(heap_obj);
1043 }

1045 void FunctionTemplate::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate(
1046  Local<FunctionTemplate> prototype_provider) {
1047  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1048  i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolateChecked();
1049  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1050  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> result =
1051  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*prototype_provider);
1052  Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsUndefined(self->GetPrototypeTemplate(), i_isolate),
1053  "v8::FunctionTemplate::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate",
1054  "Protoype must be undefined");
1055  Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsUndefined(self->GetParentTemplate(), i_isolate),
1056  "v8::FunctionTemplate::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate",
1057  "Prototype provider must be empty");
1058  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate(i_isolate, self,
1059  result);
1060 }

1062 namespace {
1063 static void EnsureNotPublished(i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> info,
1064  const char* func) {
1065  DCHECK_IMPLIES(info->instantiated(), info->published());
1066  Utils::ApiCheck(!info->published(), func,
1067  "FunctionTemplate already instantiated");
1068 }
1069 
1070 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> FunctionTemplateNew(
1071  i::Isolate* i_isolate, FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1072  v8::Local<Signature> signature, int length, ConstructorBehavior behavior,
1073  bool do_not_cache,
1074  v8::Local<Private> cached_property_name = v8::Local<Private>(),
1075  SideEffectType side_effect_type = SideEffectType::kHasSideEffect,
1076  const MemorySpan<const CFunction>& c_function_overloads = {}) {
1077  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> obj =
1078  i_isolate->factory()->NewFunctionTemplateInfo(length, do_not_cache);
1079  {
1080  // Disallow GC until all fields of obj have acceptable types.
1081  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1082  i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> raw = *obj;
1083  if (!signature.IsEmpty()) {
1084  raw->set_signature(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*signature));
1085  }
1086  if (!cached_property_name.IsEmpty()) {
1087  raw->set_cached_property_name(
1088  *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*cached_property_name));
1089  }
1090  if (behavior == ConstructorBehavior::kThrow) {
1091  raw->set_remove_prototype(true);
1092  }
1093  }
1094  if (callback != nullptr) {
1095  Utils::ToLocal(obj)->SetCallHandler(callback, data, side_effect_type,
1096  c_function_overloads);
1097  }
1098  return obj;
1099 }
1100 } // namespace
1101 
1102 void FunctionTemplate::Inherit(v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> value) {
1103  auto info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1104  EnsureNotPublished(info, "v8::FunctionTemplate::Inherit");
1105  i::Isolate* i_isolate = info->GetIsolateChecked();
1106  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1107  Utils::ApiCheck(
1108  i::IsUndefined(info->GetPrototypeProviderTemplate(), i_isolate),
1109  "v8::FunctionTemplate::Inherit", "Protoype provider must be empty");
1110  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetParentTemplate(i_isolate, info,
1111  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value));
1112 }
1113 
1114 Local<FunctionTemplate> FunctionTemplate::New(
1115  Isolate* v8_isolate, FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1116  v8::Local<Signature> signature, int length, ConstructorBehavior behavior,
1117  SideEffectType side_effect_type, const CFunction* c_function,
1118  uint16_t instance_type, uint16_t allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start,
1119  uint16_t allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end) {
1120  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
1121  // Changes to the environment cannot be captured in the snapshot. Expect no
1122  // function templates when the isolate is created for serialization.
1123  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
1124  RCCId::kAPI_FunctionTemplate_New);
1125 
1126  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
1127  !c_function || behavior == ConstructorBehavior::kThrow,
1128  "FunctionTemplate::New",
1129  "Fast API calls are not supported for constructor functions")) {
1130  return {};
1131  }
1132 
1133  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1134  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ = FunctionTemplateNew(
1135  i_isolate, callback, data, signature, length, behavior, false,
1136  Local<Private>(), side_effect_type,
1137  c_function ? MemorySpan<const CFunction>{c_function, 1}
1138  : MemorySpan<const CFunction>{});
1139 
1140  if (instance_type) {
1141  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
1142  base::IsInRange(static_cast<int>(instance_type),
1143  i::Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType,
1144  i::Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType),
1145  "FunctionTemplate::New",
1146  "instance_type is outside the range of valid JSApiObject types")) {
1147  return {};
1148  }
1149  templ->SetInstanceType(instance_type);
1150  }
1151 
1152  if (allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start ||
1153  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end) {
1154  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(i::Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType <=
1155  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start &&
1156  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start <=
1157  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end &&
1158  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end <=
1159  i::Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType,
1160  "FunctionTemplate::New",
1161  "allowed receiver instance type range is outside the "
1162  "range of valid JSApiObject types")) {
1163  return {};
1164  }
1165  templ->SetAllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRange(
1166  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start,
1167  allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end);
1168  }
1169  return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1170 }
1171 
1172 Local<FunctionTemplate> FunctionTemplate::NewWithCFunctionOverloads(
1173  Isolate* v8_isolate, FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1174  v8::Local<Signature> signature, int length, ConstructorBehavior behavior,
1175  SideEffectType side_effect_type,
1176  const MemorySpan<const CFunction>& c_function_overloads) {
1177  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
1178  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
1179  RCCId::kAPI_FunctionTemplate_New);
1180 
1181  // Check that all overloads of the fast API callback have different numbers of
1182  // parameters. Since the number of overloads is supposed to be small, just
1183  // comparing them with each other should be fine.
1184  for (size_t i = 0; i < c_function_overloads.size(); ++i) {
1185  for (size_t j = i + 1; j < c_function_overloads.size(); ++j) {
1186  CHECK_NE(c_function_overloads.data()[i].ArgumentCount(),
1187  c_function_overloads.data()[j].ArgumentCount());
1188  }
1189  }
1190 
1191  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
1192  c_function_overloads.empty() ||
1193  behavior == ConstructorBehavior::kThrow,
1194  "FunctionTemplate::NewWithCFunctionOverloads",
1195  "Fast API calls are not supported for constructor functions")) {
1196  return {};
1197  }
1198 
1199  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1200  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ = FunctionTemplateNew(
1201  i_isolate, callback, data, signature, length, behavior, false,
1202  Local<Private>(), side_effect_type, c_function_overloads);
1203  return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1204 }

1206 Local<FunctionTemplate> FunctionTemplate::NewWithCache(
1207  Isolate* v8_isolate, FunctionCallback callback,
1208  Local<Private> cache_property, Local<Value> data,
1209  Local<Signature> signature, int length, SideEffectType side_effect_type) {
1210  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
1211  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
1212  RCCId::kAPI_FunctionTemplate_NewWithCache);
1213  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1214  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ = FunctionTemplateNew(
1215  i_isolate, callback, data, signature, length, ConstructorBehavior::kAllow,
1216  false, cache_property, side_effect_type);
1217  return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1218 }

1220 Local<Signature> Signature::New(Isolate* v8_isolate,
1221  Local<FunctionTemplate> receiver) {
1222  return Local<Signature>::Cast(receiver);
1223 }
1224 
1225 #define SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, setter, cdata, tag) \
1226  do { \
1227  i::DirectHandle<i::UnionOf<i::Smi, i::Foreign>> foreign = \
1228  FromCData<tag>(i_isolate, cdata); \
1229  (obj)->setter(*foreign); \
1230  } while (false)
1231 
1232 void FunctionTemplate::SetCallHandler(
1233  FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1234  SideEffectType side_effect_type,
1235  const MemorySpan<const CFunction>& c_function_overloads) {
1236  auto info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1237  EnsureNotPublished(info, "v8::FunctionTemplate::SetCallHandler");
1238  i::Isolate* i_isolate = info->GetIsolateChecked();
1239  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1240  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1241  info->set_has_side_effects(side_effect_type !=
1242  SideEffectType::kHasNoSideEffect);
1243  info->set_callback(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(callback));
1244  if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1245  data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1246  }
1247  // "Release" callback and callback data fields.
1248  info->set_callback_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data), kReleaseStore);
1249 
1250  if (!c_function_overloads.empty()) {
1251  // Stores the data for a sequence of CFunction overloads into a single
1252  // FixedArray, as [address_0, signature_0, ... address_n-1, signature_n-1].
1253  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> function_overloads =
1254  i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(static_cast<int>(
1255  c_function_overloads.size() *
1256  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::kFunctionOverloadEntrySize));
1257  int function_count = static_cast<int>(c_function_overloads.size());
1258  for (int i = 0; i < function_count; i++) {
1259  const CFunction& c_function = c_function_overloads.data()[i];
1260  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> address = FromCData<internal::kCFunctionTag>(
1261  i_isolate, c_function.GetAddress());
1262  function_overloads->set(
1263  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::kFunctionOverloadEntrySize * i, *address);
1264  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> signature =
1265  FromCData<internal::kCFunctionInfoTag>(i_isolate,
1266  c_function.GetTypeInfo());
1267  function_overloads->set(
1268  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::kFunctionOverloadEntrySize * i + 1,
1269  *signature);
1270  }
1271  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetCFunctionOverloads(i_isolate, info,
1272  function_overloads);
1273  }
1274 }
1275 
1276 namespace {
1277 
1278 template <typename Getter, typename Setter>
1279 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> MakeAccessorInfo(i::Isolate* i_isolate,
1280  v8::Local<Name> name,
1281  Getter getter, Setter setter,
1282  v8::Local<Value> data,
1283  bool replace_on_access) {
1284  i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> obj =
1285  i_isolate->factory()->NewAccessorInfo();
1286  obj->set_getter(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(getter));
1287  DCHECK_IMPLIES(replace_on_access, setter == nullptr);
1288  if (setter == nullptr) {
1289  setter = reinterpret_cast<Setter>(&i::Accessors::ReconfigureToDataProperty);
1290  }
1291  obj->set_setter(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(setter));
1292 
1293  auto accessor_name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name);
1294  if (!IsUniqueName(*accessor_name)) {
1295  accessor_name = i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(
1296  i::Cast<i::String>(accessor_name));
1297  }
1298  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1299  i::Tagged<i::AccessorInfo> raw_obj = *obj;
1300  if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1301  raw_obj->set_data(i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value());
1302  } else {
1303  raw_obj->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1304  }
1305  raw_obj->set_name(*accessor_name);
1306  raw_obj->set_replace_on_access(replace_on_access);
1307  raw_obj->set_initial_property_attributes(i::NONE);
1308  return obj;
1309 }

1311 } // namespace

1313 Local<ObjectTemplate> FunctionTemplate::InstanceTemplate() {
1314  auto constructor = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this, true);
1315  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(!constructor.is_null(),
1316  "v8::FunctionTemplate::InstanceTemplate()",
1317  "Reading from empty handle")) {
1318  return {};
1319  }
1320  i::Isolate* i_isolate = constructor->GetIsolateChecked();
1321  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1322  auto maybe_templ = constructor->GetInstanceTemplate();
1323  if (!i::IsUndefined(maybe_templ, i_isolate)) {
1324  return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
1325  i::Cast<i::ObjectTemplateInfo>(maybe_templ), i_isolate));
1326  }
1327  constexpr bool do_not_cache = false;
1328  i::DirectHandle<i::ObjectTemplateInfo> templ =
1329  i_isolate->factory()->NewObjectTemplateInfo(constructor, do_not_cache);
1330  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceTemplate(i_isolate, constructor, templ);
1331  return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1332 }

1404 namespace {
1405 // Ensure that the object template has a constructor. If no
1406 // constructor is available we create one.
1407 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> EnsureConstructor(
1408  i::Isolate* i_isolate, ObjectTemplate* object_template) {
1409  i::Tagged<i::Object> obj =
1410  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(object_template)->constructor();
1411  if (!IsUndefined(obj, i_isolate)) {
1412  i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> info =
1413  i::Cast<i::FunctionTemplateInfo>(obj);
1414  return i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo>(info, i_isolate);
1415  }
1416  Local<FunctionTemplate> templ =
1417  FunctionTemplate::New(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1418  auto constructor = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*templ);
1419  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceTemplate(
1420  i_isolate, constructor, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(object_template));
1421  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(object_template)->set_constructor(*constructor);
1422  return constructor;
1423 }

1425 template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Data, typename Template>
1426 void TemplateSetAccessor(Template* template_obj, v8::Local<Name> name,
1427  Getter getter, Setter setter, Data data,
1428  PropertyAttribute attribute, bool replace_on_access,
1429  SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
1430  SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
1431  auto info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(template_obj);
1432  auto i_isolate = info->GetIsolateChecked();
1433  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1434  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1435  i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> accessor_info = MakeAccessorInfo(
1436  i_isolate, name, getter, setter, data, replace_on_access);
1437  {
1438  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1439  i::Tagged<i::AccessorInfo> raw = *accessor_info;
1440  raw->set_initial_property_attributes(
1441  static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attribute));
1442  raw->set_getter_side_effect_type(getter_side_effect_type);
1443  raw->set_setter_side_effect_type(setter_side_effect_type);
1444  }
1445  i::ApiNatives::AddNativeDataProperty(i_isolate, info, accessor_info);
1446 }

1482 namespace {
1483 enum class PropertyType { kNamed, kIndexed };
1484 template <PropertyType property_type, typename Getter, typename Setter,
1485  typename Query, typename Descriptor, typename Deleter,
1486  typename Enumerator, typename Definer>
1487 i::DirectHandle<i::InterceptorInfo> CreateInterceptorInfo(
1488  i::Isolate* i_isolate, Getter getter, Setter setter, Query query,
1489  Descriptor descriptor, Deleter deleter, Enumerator enumerator,
1490  Definer definer, Local<Value> data,
1491  base::Flags<PropertyHandlerFlags> flags) {
1492  // TODO(saelo): instead of an in-sandbox struct with a lot of external
1493  // pointers (with different tags), consider creating an object in trusted
1494  // space instead. That way, only a single reference going out of the sandbox
1495  // would be required.
1496  auto obj = i_isolate->factory()->NewInterceptorInfo();
1497  obj->set_is_named(property_type == PropertyType::kNamed);
1498 
1499 #define SET_CALLBACK_FIELD(Name, name) \
1500  if (name != nullptr) { \
1501  if constexpr (property_type == PropertyType::kNamed) { \
1502  obj->set_named_##name(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(name)); \
1503  } else { \
1504  obj->set_indexed_##name(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(name)); \
1505  } \
1506  }
1507  INTERCEPTOR_INFO_CALLBACK_LIST(SET_CALLBACK_FIELD)
1508 #undef SET_CALLBACK_FIELD
1509 
1510  obj->set_can_intercept_symbols(
1511  !(flags & PropertyHandlerFlags::kOnlyInterceptStrings));
1512  obj->set_non_masking(flags & PropertyHandlerFlags::kNonMasking);
1513  obj->set_has_no_side_effect(flags & PropertyHandlerFlags::kHasNoSideEffect);
1514 
1515  if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1516  data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1517  }
1518  obj->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1519  return obj;
1520 }

1524 i::DirectHandle<i::InterceptorInfo> CreateNamedInterceptorInfo(
1525  i::Isolate* i_isolate, Getter getter, Setter setter, Query query,
1526  Descriptor descriptor, Deleter remover, Enumerator enumerator,
1527  Definer definer, Local<Value> data,
1528  base::Flags<PropertyHandlerFlags> flags) {
1529  auto interceptor = CreateInterceptorInfo<PropertyType::kNamed>(
1530  i_isolate, getter, setter, query, descriptor, remover, enumerator,
1531  definer, data, flags);

1533 }

1583 void ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallback(AccessCheckCallback callback,
1584  Local<Value> data) {
1585  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
1586  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1587  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1588  auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1589  EnsureNotPublished(cons, "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallback");
1590 
1591  i::DirectHandle<i::Struct> struct_info = i_isolate->factory()->NewStruct(
1592  i::ACCESS_CHECK_INFO_TYPE, i::AllocationType::kOld);
1593  auto info = i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(struct_info);
1594 
1595  SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, info, set_callback, callback,
1596  internal::kApiAccessCheckCallbackTag);
1597  info->set_named_interceptor(i::Smi::zero());
1598  info->set_indexed_interceptor(i::Smi::zero());
1599 
1600  if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1601  data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1602  }
1603  info->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1604 
1605  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(i_isolate, cons, info);
1606  cons->set_needs_access_check(true);
1607 }

1609 void ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallbackAndHandler(
1610  AccessCheckCallback callback,
1611  const NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration& named_handler,
1612  const IndexedPropertyHandlerConfiguration& indexed_handler,
1613  Local<Value> data) {
1614  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
1615  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1616  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1617  auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1618  EnsureNotPublished(cons,
1619  "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallbackWithHandler");
1620 
1621  i::DirectHandle<i::Struct> struct_info = i_isolate->factory()->NewStruct(
1622  i::ACCESS_CHECK_INFO_TYPE, i::AllocationType::kOld);
1623  auto info = i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(struct_info);
1624 
1625  SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, info, set_callback, callback,
1626  internal::kApiAccessCheckCallbackTag);
1627  auto named_interceptor = CreateNamedInterceptorInfo(
1628  i_isolate, named_handler.getter, named_handler.setter,
1629  named_handler.query, named_handler.descriptor, named_handler.deleter,
1630  named_handler.enumerator, named_handler.definer, named_handler.data,
1631  named_handler.flags);
1632  info->set_named_interceptor(*named_interceptor);
1633  auto indexed_interceptor = CreateIndexedInterceptorInfo(
1634  i_isolate, indexed_handler.getter, indexed_handler.setter,
1635  indexed_handler.query, indexed_handler.descriptor,
1636  indexed_handler.deleter, indexed_handler.enumerator,
1637  indexed_handler.definer, indexed_handler.data, indexed_handler.flags);
1638  info->set_indexed_interceptor(*indexed_interceptor);
1639 
1640  if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1641  data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1642  }
1643  info->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1644 
1645  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(i_isolate, cons, info);
1646  cons->set_needs_access_check(true);
1647 }
1648 
1649 void ObjectTemplate::SetHandler(
1650  const IndexedPropertyHandlerConfiguration& config) {
1651  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
1652  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1653  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1654  auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1655  EnsureNotPublished(cons, "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetHandler");
1656  auto obj = CreateIndexedInterceptorInfo(
1657  i_isolate, config.getter, config.setter, config.query, config.descriptor,
1658  config.deleter, config.enumerator, config.definer, config.data,
1659  config.flags);
1660  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetIndexedPropertyHandler(i_isolate, cons, obj);
1661 }
1662 
1663 void ObjectTemplate::SetCallAsFunctionHandler(FunctionCallback callback,
1664  Local<Value> data) {
1665  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
1666  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1667  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1668  auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1669  EnsureNotPublished(cons, "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetCallAsFunctionHandler");
1670  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(callback);
1671 
1672  // This template is just a container for callback and data values and thus
1673  // it's not supposed to be instantiated. Don't cache it.
1674  constexpr bool do_not_cache = true;
1675  constexpr int length = 0;
1676  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ =
1677  i_isolate->factory()->NewFunctionTemplateInfo(length, do_not_cache);
1678  templ->set_is_object_template_call_handler(true);
1679  Utils::ToLocal(templ)->SetCallHandler(callback, data);
1680  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceCallHandler(i_isolate, cons, templ);
1681 }

1686 
1687 void ObjectTemplate::SetInternalFieldCount(int value) {
1688  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
1689  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(i::Smi::IsValid(value),
1690  "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetInternalFieldCount()",
1691  "Invalid embedder field count")) {
1692  return;
1693  }
1694  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
1695  if (value > 0) {
1696  // The embedder field count is set by the constructor function's
1697  // construct code, so we ensure that there is a constructor
1698  // function to do the setting.
1699  EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1700  }
1701  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->set_embedder_field_count(value);
1702 }

1928 MaybeLocal<Value> Script::Run(Local<Context> context) {
1929  return Run(context, Local<Data>());
1930 }
1931 
1932 MaybeLocal<Value> Script::Run(Local<Context> context,
1933  Local<Data> host_defined_options) {
1934  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
1935  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.Execute");
1936  EnterV8Scope<InternalEscapableScope> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
1937  RCCId::kAPI_Script_Run};
1938  i::TimerEventScope<i::TimerEventExecute> timer_scope(i_isolate);
1939  i::NestedTimedHistogramScope execute_timer(i_isolate->counters()->execute(),
1940  i_isolate);
1941  i::AggregatingHistogramTimerScope histogram_timer(
1942  i_isolate->counters()->compile_lazy());
1943 
1944 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
1945  // In case ETW has been activated, tasks to log existing code are
1946  // created. But in case the task runner does not run those before
1947  // starting to execute code (as it happens in d8, that will run
1948  // first the code from prompt), then that code will not have
1949  // JIT instrumentation on time.
1950  //
1951  // To avoid this, on running scripts check first if JIT code log is
1952  // pending and generate immediately.
1953  if (i::v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
1954  i::v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
1955  i::ETWJITInterface::MaybeSetHandlerNow(i_isolate);
1956  }
1957 #endif // V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING
1958  auto fun = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
1959  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> receiver = i_isolate->global_proxy();
1960  // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): Remove once migrated to the context.
1961  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> options(
1962  i::Cast<i::Script>(fun->shared()->script())->host_defined_options(),
1963  i_isolate);
1964  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(
1965  i::Execution::CallScript(i_isolate, fun, receiver, options));
1966 }

2002 std::vector<int> Script::GetProducedCompileHints() const {
2003  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2004  auto func = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2005  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
2006  i::Tagged<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = func->shared();
2007  CHECK(IsScript(sfi->script()));
2008  i::Tagged<i::Script> script = i::Cast<i::Script>(sfi->script());
2009  i::Tagged<i::Object> maybe_array_list =
2010  script->compiled_lazy_function_positions();
2011  std::vector<int> result;
2012  if (!IsUndefined(maybe_array_list, i_isolate)) {
2013  i::Tagged<i::ArrayList> array_list =
2014  i::Cast<i::ArrayList>(maybe_array_list);
2015  result.reserve(array_list->length());
2016  for (int i = 0; i < array_list->length(); ++i) {
2017  i::Tagged<i::Object> item = array_list->get(i);
2018  CHECK(IsSmi(item));
2019  result.push_back(i::Smi::ToInt(item));
2020  }
2021  }
2022  return result;
2023 }

2025 Local<CompileHintsCollector> Script::GetCompileHintsCollector() const {
2026  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2027  auto func = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2028  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
2029  i::Tagged<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = func->shared();
2030  CHECK(IsScript(sfi->script()));
2031  i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script(i::Cast<i::Script>(sfi->script()),
2032  i_isolate);

2036 std::vector<int> CompileHintsCollector::GetCompileHints(
2037  Isolate* v8_isolate) const {
2038  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2039  auto script = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2040  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2041  i::Tagged<i::Object> maybe_array_list =
2042  script->compiled_lazy_function_positions();
2043  std::vector<int> result;
2044  if (!IsUndefined(maybe_array_list, i_isolate)) {
2045  i::Tagged<i::ArrayList> array_list =
2046  i::Cast<i::ArrayList>(maybe_array_list);
2047  result.reserve(array_list->length());
2048  for (int i = 0; i < array_list->length(); ++i) {
2049  i::Tagged<i::Object> item = array_list->get(i);
2050  CHECK(IsSmi(item));
2051  result.push_back(i::Smi::ToInt(item));
2052  }
2053  }
2054  return result;
2055 }

2135 
2136 Module::Status Module::GetStatus() const {
2137  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2138  switch (self->status()) {
2139  case i::Module::kUnlinked:
2140  case i::Module::kPreLinking:
2141  return kUninstantiated;
2142  case i::Module::kLinking:
2143  return kInstantiating;
2144  case i::Module::kLinked:
2145  return kInstantiated;
2146  case i::Module::kEvaluating:
2147  return kEvaluating;
2148  case i::Module::kEvaluatingAsync:
2149  // TODO(syg): Expose kEvaluatingAsync in API as well.
2150  case i::Module::kEvaluated:
2151  return kEvaluated;
2152  case i::Module::kErrored:
2153  return kErrored;
2154  }
2155  UNREACHABLE();
2156 }
2157 
2158 Local<Value> Module::GetException() const {
2159  Utils::ApiCheck(GetStatus() == kErrored, "v8::Module::GetException",
2160  "Module status must be kErrored");
2161  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2162  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
2163  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
2164  return ToApiHandle<Value>(i::direct_handle(self->GetException(), i_isolate));
2165 }

2167 Local<FixedArray> Module::GetModuleRequests() const {
2168  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2169  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
2170  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution(i_isolate);
2171  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions(i_isolate);
2172  if (i::IsSyntheticModule(*self)) {
2173  // Synthetic modules are leaf nodes in the module graph. They have no
2174  // ModuleRequests.

2176  } else {

2178  i::Cast<i::SourceTextModule>(self)->info()->module_requests(),
2179  i_isolate));
2180  }
2181 }

2343 std::pair<LocalVector<Module>, LocalVector<Message>>
2344 Module::GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages(Isolate* isolate) {
2345  auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
2346  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2347  Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsSourceTextModule(*self),
2348  "v8::Module::GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages",
2349  "v8::Module::GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages must only be "
2350  "called on a SourceTextModule");
2351  std::pair<i::DirectHandleVector<i::SourceTextModule>,
2352  i::DirectHandleVector<i::JSMessageObject>>
2353  stalled_awaits =
2354  i::Cast<i::SourceTextModule>(self)->GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages(
2355  i_isolate);
2356 
2357  LocalVector<Module> modules(isolate);
2358  if (size_t stalled_awaits_count = stalled_awaits.first.size();
2359  stalled_awaits_count > 0) {
2360  modules.reserve(stalled_awaits_count);
2361  for (auto module : stalled_awaits.first)
2362  modules.push_back(ToApiHandle<Module>(module));
2363  }
2364  LocalVector<Message> messages(isolate);
2365  if (size_t stalled_awaits_count = stalled_awaits.second.size();
2366  stalled_awaits_count > 0) {
2367  messages.reserve(stalled_awaits_count);
2368  for (auto message : stalled_awaits.second)
2369  messages.push_back(ToApiHandle<Message>(message));
2370  }
2371 
2372  return {modules, messages};
2373 }

2377 i::ScriptDetails GetScriptDetails(
2378  i::Isolate* i_isolate, Local<Value> resource_name, int resource_line_offset,
2379  int resource_column_offset, Local<Value> source_map_url,
2380  Local<Data> host_defined_options, ScriptOriginOptions origin_options) {
2381  i::ScriptDetails script_details(Utils::OpenHandle(*(resource_name), true),
2382  origin_options);
2383  script_details.line_offset = resource_line_offset;
2384  script_details.column_offset = resource_column_offset;
2385  script_details.host_defined_options =
2386  host_defined_options.IsEmpty()
2387  ? i_isolate->factory()->empty_fixed_array()
2388  : Utils::OpenHandle(*(host_defined_options));
2389  if (!source_map_url.IsEmpty()) {
2390  script_details.source_map_url = Utils::OpenHandle(*(source_map_url));
2391  }
2392  return script_details;
2393 }

2396 
2397 MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundInternal(
2398  Isolate* v8_isolate, Source* source, CompileOptions options,
2399  NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2400  auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2401  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2402  EnterV8NoScriptScope<InternalEscapableScope> api_scope{
2403  i_isolate, v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext(),
2404  RCCId::kAPI_ScriptCompiler_CompileUnbound};
2405 
2406  auto str = Utils::OpenHandle(*(source->source_string));
2407 
2408  i::DirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> result;
2409  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.CompileScript");
2410  i::ScriptDetails script_details = GetScriptDetails(
2411  i_isolate, source->resource_name, source->resource_line_offset,
2412  source->resource_column_offset, source->source_map_url,
2413  source->host_defined_options, source->resource_options);
2414 
2415  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_function_info;
2416  if (options & kConsumeCodeCache) {
2417  if (source->consume_cache_task) {
2418  // Take ownership of the internal deserialization task and clear it off
2419  // the consume task on the source.
2420  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(source->consume_cache_task->impl_);
2421  std::unique_ptr<i::BackgroundDeserializeTask> deserialize_task =
2422  std::move(source->consume_cache_task->impl_);
2423  maybe_function_info =
2424  i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithDeserializeTask(
2425  i_isolate, str, script_details, deserialize_task.get(), options,
2426  no_cache_reason, i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE,
2427  &source->compilation_details);
2428  source->cached_data->rejected = deserialize_task->rejected();
2429  } else {
2430  DCHECK(source->cached_data);
2431  // AlignedCachedData takes care of pointer-aligning the data.
2432  auto cached_data = std::make_unique<i::AlignedCachedData>(
2433  source->cached_data->data, source->cached_data->length);
2434  maybe_function_info =
2435  i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithCachedData(
2436  i_isolate, str, script_details, cached_data.get(), options,
2437  no_cache_reason, i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE,
2438  &source->compilation_details);
2439  source->cached_data->rejected = cached_data->rejected();
2440  }
2441  } else if (options & kConsumeCompileHints) {
2442  maybe_function_info =
2443  i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithCompileHints(
2444  i_isolate, str, script_details, source->compile_hint_callback,
2445  source->compile_hint_callback_data, options, no_cache_reason,
2446  i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE, &source->compilation_details);
2447  } else {
2448  // Compile without any cache.
2449  maybe_function_info = i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScript(
2450  i_isolate, str, script_details, options, no_cache_reason,
2451  i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE, &source->compilation_details);
2452  }
2453 
2454  if (!maybe_function_info.ToHandle(&result)) return {};
2455  DCHECK(!i::HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*result));
2456  return api_scope.Escape(ToApiHandle<UnboundScript>(result));
2457 }
2458 
2459 MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundScript(
2460  Isolate* v8_isolate, Source* source, CompileOptions options,
2461  NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2462  Utils::ApiCheck(
2463  !source->GetResourceOptions().IsModule(),
2464  "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundScript",
2465  "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule must be used to compile modules");
2466  return CompileUnboundInternal(v8_isolate, source, options, no_cache_reason);
2467 }
2468 
2469 MaybeLocal<Script> ScriptCompiler::Compile(Local<Context> context,
2470  Source* source,
2471  CompileOptions options,
2472  NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2473  Utils::ApiCheck(
2474  !source->GetResourceOptions().IsModule(), "v8::ScriptCompiler::Compile",
2475  "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule must be used to compile modules");
2476  v8::Isolate* isolate = v8::Isolate::GetCurrent();
2477  MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> maybe =
2478  CompileUnboundInternal(isolate, source, options, no_cache_reason);
2479  Local<UnboundScript> result;
2480  if (!maybe.ToLocal(&result)) return {};
2481  v8::Context::Scope scope(context);
2482  return result->BindToCurrentContext();
2483 }

2485 MaybeLocal<Module> ScriptCompiler::CompileModule(
2486  Isolate* v8_isolate, Source* source, CompileOptions options,
2487  NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2488  Utils::ApiCheck(v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileOptionsIsValid(options),
2489  "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule",
2490  "Invalid CompileOptions");
2491  Utils::ApiCheck(source->GetResourceOptions().IsModule(),
2492  "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule",
2493  "Invalid ScriptOrigin: is_module must be true");
2494  MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> maybe =
2495  CompileUnboundInternal(v8_isolate, source, options, no_cache_reason);
2496  Local<UnboundScript> unbound;
2497  if (!maybe.ToLocal(&unbound)) return {};
2498  auto shared = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*unbound);
2499  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2500  return ToApiHandle<Module>(i_isolate->factory()->NewSourceTextModule(shared));
2501 }
2502 
2503 // static
2504 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeLocal<Function> ScriptCompiler::CompileFunction(
2505  Local<Context> v8_context, Source* source, size_t arguments_count,
2506  Local<String> arguments[], size_t context_extension_count,
2507  Local<Object> context_extensions[], CompileOptions options,
2508  NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2509  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{
2510  v8_context, RCCId::kAPI_ScriptCompiler_CompileFunction};
2511  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
2512  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2513 
2514  DCHECK(options == CompileOptions::kConsumeCodeCache ||
2515  options == CompileOptions::kEagerCompile ||
2516  options == CompileOptions::kNoCompileOptions);
2517 
2518  i::DirectHandle<i::Context> context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*v8_context);
2519 
2520  DCHECK(IsNativeContext(*context));
2521 
2522  i::Handle<i::FixedArray> arguments_list =
2523  i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(static_cast<int>(arguments_count));
2524  for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(arguments_count); i++) {
2525  auto argument = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*arguments[i]);
2526  if (!i::String::IsIdentifier(i_isolate, argument)) return {};
2527  arguments_list->set(i, *argument);
2528  }
2529 
2530  for (size_t i = 0; i < context_extension_count; ++i) {
2531  i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> extension =
2532  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*context_extensions[i]);
2533  if (!IsJSObject(*extension)) return {};
2534  context = i_isolate->factory()->NewWithContext(
2535  context,
2536  i::ScopeInfo::CreateForWithScope(
2537  i_isolate,
2538  IsNativeContext(*context)
2539  ? i::Handle<i::ScopeInfo>::null()
2540  : i::Handle<i::ScopeInfo>(context->scope_info(), i_isolate)),
2541  extension);
2542  }
2543 
2544  i::ScriptDetails script_details = GetScriptDetails(
2545  i_isolate, source->resource_name, source->resource_line_offset,
2546  source->resource_column_offset, source->source_map_url,
2547  source->host_defined_options, source->resource_options);
2548  script_details.wrapped_arguments = arguments_list;
2549 
2550  std::unique_ptr<i::AlignedCachedData> cached_data;
2551  if (options & kConsumeCodeCache) {
2552  DCHECK(source->cached_data);
2553  // ScriptData takes care of pointer-aligning the data.
2554  cached_data.reset(new i::AlignedCachedData(source->cached_data->data,
2555  source->cached_data->length));
2556  }
2557 
2558  i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> result;
2559  bool has_exception =
2560  !i::Compiler::GetWrappedFunction(
2561  i_isolate, Utils::OpenHandle(*source->source_string), context,
2562  script_details, cached_data.get(), options, no_cache_reason)
2563  .ToHandle(&result);
2564  if (options & kConsumeCodeCache) {
2565  source->cached_data->rejected = cached_data->rejected();
2566  }
2567  if (has_exception) return {};
2568  return api_scope.Escape(Utils::CallableToLocal(result));
2569 }

2573 ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask* ScriptCompiler::StartStreaming(
2574  Isolate* v8_isolate, StreamedSource* source, v8::ScriptType type,
2575  CompileOptions options, CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback,
2576  void* compile_hint_callback_data) {
2577  Utils::ApiCheck(v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileOptionsIsValid(options),
2578  "v8::ScriptCompiler::StartStreaming",
2579  "Invalid CompileOptions");
2580  if (!i::v8_flags.script_streaming) return nullptr;
2581  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2582  i::ScriptStreamingData* data = source->impl();
2583  std::unique_ptr<i::BackgroundCompileTask> task =
2584  std::make_unique<i::BackgroundCompileTask>(
2585  data, i_isolate, type, options, &source->compilation_details(),
2586  compile_hint_callback, compile_hint_callback_data);

2588  return new ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask(data);
2589 }

2639 ScriptCompiler::ConsumeCodeCacheTask*
2640 ScriptCompiler::StartConsumingCodeCacheOnBackground(
2641  Isolate* v8_isolate, std::unique_ptr<CachedData> cached_data) {
2642  if (!i::v8_flags.concurrent_cache_deserialization) return nullptr;
2643  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2644  return new ScriptCompiler::ConsumeCodeCacheTask(
2645  std::make_unique<i::BackgroundDeserializeTask>(i_isolate,
2646  std::move(cached_data)));
2647 }

2649 namespace {
2650 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> CompileStreamedSource(
2651  i::Isolate* i_isolate, ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource* v8_source,
2652  Local<String> full_source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
2653  auto str = Utils::OpenHandle(*full_source_string);
2654  i::ScriptDetails script_details =
2655  GetScriptDetails(i_isolate, origin.ResourceName(), origin.LineOffset(),
2656  origin.ColumnOffset(), origin.SourceMapUrl(),
2657  origin.GetHostDefinedOptions(), origin.Options());
2658  i::ScriptStreamingData* data = v8_source->impl();
2659  i::IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
2660  return i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForStreamedScript(
2661  i_isolate, str, script_details, data, &is_compiled_scope,
2662  &v8_source->compilation_details());
2663 }
2664 
2665 } // namespace
2666 
2667 MaybeLocal<Script> ScriptCompiler::Compile(Local<Context> context,
2668  StreamedSource* v8_source,
2669  Local<String> full_source_string,
2670  const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
2671  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context,
2672  RCCId::kAPI_ScriptCompiler_Compile};
2673  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
2674  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2675  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2676  "V8.CompileStreamedScript");
2677  i::DirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi;
2678  if (!CompileStreamedSource(i_isolate, v8_source, full_source_string, origin)
2679  .ToHandle(&sfi)) {
2680  i_isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
2681  return {};
2682  }
2683  Local<UnboundScript> generic = ToApiHandle<UnboundScript>(sfi);
2684  if (generic.IsEmpty()) return {};
2685  return api_scope.Escape(generic->BindToCurrentContext());
2686 }
2687 
2688 MaybeLocal<Module> ScriptCompiler::CompileModule(
2689  Local<Context> context, StreamedSource* v8_source,
2690  Local<String> full_source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
2691  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context,
2692  RCCId::kAPI_ScriptCompiler_Compile};
2693  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
2694  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2695  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2696  "V8.CompileStreamedModule");
2697  i::DirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi;
2698  if (!CompileStreamedSource(i_isolate, v8_source, full_source_string, origin)
2699  .ToHandle(&sfi)) {
2700  i_isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
2701  return {};
2702  }
2703  return api_scope.Escape(
2704  ToApiHandle<Module>(i_isolate->factory()->NewSourceTextModule(sfi)));
2705 }

2712 ScriptCompiler::CachedData* ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache(
2713  Local<UnboundScript> unbound_script) {
2714  auto shared = Utils::OpenHandle(*unbound_script);
2715  // TODO(jgruber): Remove this DCHECK once Function::GetUnboundScript is gone.
2716  DCHECK(!i::HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*shared));
2717  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*shared);
2718  Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
2719  "ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache",
2720  "Cannot create code cache while creating a snapshot");
2721  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution(i_isolate);
2722  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions(i_isolate);
2723  DCHECK(shared->is_toplevel());
2724  return i::CodeSerializer::Serialize(i_isolate, shared);
2725 }

2744 ScriptCompiler::CachedData* ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCacheForFunction(
2745  Local<Function> function) {

2747  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
2748  Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
2749  "ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCacheForFunction",
2750  "Cannot create code cache while creating a snapshot");
2751  i::Handle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> shared(js_function->shared(), i_isolate);
2752  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution(i_isolate);
2753  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions(i_isolate);
2754  Utils::ApiCheck(shared->is_wrapped(),
2755  "v8::ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCacheForFunction",
2756  "Expected SharedFunctionInfo with wrapped source code");
2757  return i::CodeSerializer::Serialize(i_isolate, shared);
2758 }

2760 MaybeLocal<Script> Script::Compile(Local<Context> context, Local<String> source,
2761  ScriptOrigin* origin) {
2762  if (origin) {
2763  ScriptCompiler::Source script_source(source, *origin);
2764  return ScriptCompiler::Compile(context, &script_source);

2767  return ScriptCompiler::Compile(context, &script_source);

2772 v8::TryCatch::TryCatch(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate)
2773  : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)),
2774  next_(i_isolate_->try_catch_handler()),
2775  is_verbose_(false),
2776  can_continue_(true),
2777  capture_message_(true),
2778  rethrow_(false) {
2779  ResetInternal();
2780  // Special handling for simulators which have a separate JS stack.
2781  js_stack_comparable_address_ = static_cast<internal::Address>(
2782  i::SimulatorStack::RegisterJSStackComparableAddress(i_isolate_));
2783  i_isolate_->RegisterTryCatchHandler(this);
2784 }

2786 namespace {

2788 i::Tagged<i::Object> ToObject(void* object) {
2789  return i::Tagged<i::Object>(reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object));
2790 }
2791

2793 
2794 v8::TryCatch::~TryCatch() {
2795  if (HasCaught()) {
2796  if (rethrow_ || (V8_UNLIKELY(HasTerminated()) &&
2797  !i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->CallDepthIsZero())) {
2798  if (capture_message_) {
2799  // If an exception was caught and rethrow_ is indicated, the saved
2800  // message, script, and location need to be restored to Isolate TLS
2801  // for reuse. capture_message_ needs to be disabled so that Throw()
2802  // does not create a new message.
2803  i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_ = true;
2804  i_isolate_->set_pending_message(ToObject(message_obj_));
2805  }
2806  i_isolate_->UnregisterTryCatchHandler(this);
2807  i_isolate_->clear_internal_exception();
2808  i_isolate_->Throw(ToObject(exception_));
2809  return;
2810  }
2811  Reset();
2812  }
2813  i_isolate_->UnregisterTryCatchHandler(this);
2814  DCHECK_IMPLIES(rethrow_,
2815  !i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_);
2816 }

2818 void* v8::TryCatch::operator new(size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2819 void* v8::TryCatch::operator new[](size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2820 void v8::TryCatch::operator delete(void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2821 void v8::TryCatch::operator delete[](void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }

2823 bool v8::TryCatch::HasCaught() const {
2824  return !IsTheHole(ToObject(exception_), i_isolate_);
2825 }

2827 bool v8::TryCatch::CanContinue() const { return can_continue_; }
2828 
2829 bool v8::TryCatch::HasTerminated() const {
2830  return ToObject(exception_) ==
2831  i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate_).termination_exception();
2832 }
2833 
2834 v8::Local<v8::Value> v8::TryCatch::ReThrow() {
2835  if (!HasCaught()) return {};
2836  rethrow_ = true;
2837  return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate_));
2838 }

2840 v8::Local<Value> v8::TryCatch::Exception() const {
2841  if (!HasCaught()) return {};
2842  if (HasTerminated()) {
2843  return v8::Utils::ToLocal(i_isolate_->factory()->null_value());
2844  }
2845  return v8::Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(ToObject(exception_), i_isolate_));
2846 }
2847 
2848 MaybeLocal<Value> v8::TryCatch::StackTrace(Local<Context> context,
2849  Local<Value> exception) {
2850  auto i_exception = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*exception);
2851  if (!IsJSObject(*i_exception)) return {};
2852  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_TryCatch_StackTrace};
2853  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
2854  auto obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(i_exception);
2855  i::DirectHandle<i::String> name = i_isolate->factory()->stack_string();
2856  Maybe<bool> maybe = i::JSReceiver::HasProperty(i_isolate, obj, name);
2857  if (maybe != Just(true)) return {};
2858  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(
2859  i::JSReceiver::GetProperty(i_isolate, obj, name));
2860 }
2861 
2862 MaybeLocal<Value> v8::TryCatch::StackTrace(Local<Context> context) const {
2863  if (!HasCaught()) return {};
2864  return StackTrace(context, Exception());
2865 }

2867 v8::Local<v8::Message> v8::TryCatch::Message() const {
2868  i::Tagged<i::Object> message = ToObject(message_obj_);
2869  DCHECK(IsJSMessageObject(message) || IsTheHole(message, i_isolate_));
2870  if (HasCaught() && !IsTheHole(message, i_isolate_)) {
2871  return v8::Utils::MessageToLocal(i::direct_handle(message, i_isolate_));
2872  } else {
2873  return {};
2874  }
2875 }
2876 
2877 void v8::TryCatch::Reset() {
2878  if (rethrow_) return;
2879  if (V8_UNLIKELY(i_isolate_->is_execution_terminating()) &&
2880  !i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->CallDepthIsZero()) {
2881  return;
2882  }
2883  i_isolate_->clear_internal_exception();
2884  i_isolate_->clear_pending_message();
2885  ResetInternal();
2886 }
2887 
2888 void v8::TryCatch::ResetInternal() {
2889  i::Tagged<i::Object> the_hole = i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate_).the_hole_value();
2890  exception_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(the_hole.ptr());
2891  message_obj_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(the_hole.ptr());
2892 }

2925 void ScriptOrigin::VerifyHostDefinedOptions() const {
2926  // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): Remove checks once we allow arbitrary
2927  // host-defined options.
2928  if (host_defined_options_.IsEmpty()) return;
2929  Utils::ApiCheck(host_defined_options_->IsFixedArray(), "ScriptOrigin()",
2930  "Host-defined options has to be a PrimitiveArray");
2931  auto options =
2932  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*host_defined_options_.As<FixedArray>());
2933  for (int i = 0; i < options->length(); i++) {
2934  Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsPrimitive(options->get(i)), "ScriptOrigin()",
2935  "PrimitiveArray can only contain primtive values");
2936  }
2937 }

2999 int Message::GetWasmFunctionIndex() const {

3002  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
3003  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);

3007  if (start_position == -1) return Message::kNoWasmFunctionIndexInfo;

3124 Location StackFrame::GetLocation() const {
3125  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3126  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
3127  i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script(self->script(), i_isolate);
3128  i::Script::PositionInfo info;
3129  CHECK(i::Script::GetPositionInfo(
3130  script, i::StackFrameInfo::GetSourcePosition(self), &info));
3131  if (script->HasSourceURLComment()) {
3132  info.line -= script->line_offset();
3133  if (info.line == 0) {
3134  info.column -= script->column_offset();
3135  }
3136  }
3137  return {info.line, info.column};
3138 }

3211 
3212 MaybeLocal<Value> JSON::Parse(Local<Context> context,
3213  Local<String> json_string) {
3214  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_JSON_Parse};
3215  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
3216  auto string = Utils::OpenHandle(*json_string);
3217  i::Handle<i::String> source = i::String::Flatten(i_isolate, string);
3218  i::Handle<i::Object> undefined = i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3219  auto maybe_result =
3220  source->IsOneByteRepresentation()
3221  ? i::JsonParser<uint8_t>::Parse(i_isolate, source, undefined)
3222  : i::JsonParser<uint16_t>::Parse(i_isolate, source, undefined);
3223  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(maybe_result);
3224 }
3225 
3226 MaybeLocal<String> JSON::Stringify(Local<Context> context,
3227  Local<Value> json_object,
3228  Local<String> gap) {
3229  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_JSON_Stringify};
3230  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
3231  i::Handle<i::JSAny> object;
3232  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
3233  i::TryCast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenHandle(*json_object), &object),
3234  "JSON::Stringify",
3235  "Invalid object, must be a JSON-serializable object.")) {
3236  return {};
3237  }
3238  i::Handle<i::Undefined> replacer = i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3239  i::Handle<i::String> gap_string = gap.IsEmpty()
3240  ? i_isolate->factory()->empty_string()
3241  : Utils::OpenHandle(*gap);
3242  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> maybe;
3243  if (!i::JsonStringify(i_isolate, object, replacer, gap_string)
3244  .ToHandle(&maybe)) {
3245  return {};
3246  }
3247  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, maybe));
3248 }

3438 Maybe<bool> ValueDeserializer::ReadHeader(Local<Context> context) {
3439  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
3440  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
3441  RCCId::kAPI_ValueDeserializer_ReadHeader};
3442 
3443  bool read_header = false;
3444  if (!private_->deserializer.ReadHeader().To(&read_header)) return {};
3445  DCHECK(read_header);
3446 
3447  static const uint32_t kMinimumNonLegacyVersion = 13;
3448  if (GetWireFormatVersion() < kMinimumNonLegacyVersion &&
3449  !private_->supports_legacy_wire_format) {
3450  i_isolate->Throw(*i_isolate->factory()->NewError(
3451  i::MessageTemplate::kDataCloneDeserializationVersionError));
3452  return {};
3453  }
3454 
3455  return Just(true);
3456 }

3664 bool Value::IsUint32() const {
3665  auto obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3666  if (i::IsSmi(obj)) return i::Smi::ToInt(obj) >= 0;
3667  if (i::IsNumber(obj)) {
3668  double value = i::Object::NumberValue(i::Cast<i::Number>(obj));
3669  return !i::IsMinusZero(value) && value >= 0 && value <= i::kMaxUInt32 &&
3670  value == i::FastUI2D(i::FastD2UI(value));
3671  }
3672  return false;
3673 }

3727 MaybeLocal<String> Value::ToDetailString(Local<Context> context) const {
3728  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3729  i::Isolate* i_isolate;
3730  if (!context.IsEmpty()) {
3731  i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
3732  } else if (IsSmi(*obj) || !i::GetIsolateFromHeapObject(
3733  i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(*obj), &i_isolate)) {
3734  i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
3735  }
3736  if (i::IsString(*obj)) return ToApiHandle<String>(obj);
3737  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
3738  return Utils::ToLocal(i::Object::NoSideEffectsToString(i_isolate, obj));
3739 }

3745  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
3746  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(i::Object::ToObject(i_isolate, obj));
3747 }

3831 i::Address ConvertToJSGlobalProxyIfNecessary(i::Address holder_ptr) {
3832  i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> holder =
3833  i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(i::Tagged<i::Object>(holder_ptr));
3834 
3835  if (i::IsJSGlobalObject(holder)) {

3838  return holder_ptr;

4171 Maybe<double> Value::NumberValue(Local<Context> context) const {
4172  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4173  if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) {
4174  return Just(i::Object::NumberValue(i::Cast<i::Number>(*obj)));
4175  }
4176  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4177  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Value_NumberValue};
4178  i::DirectHandle<i::Number> num;
4179  if (!i::Object::ToNumber(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num)) return {};
4180  return Just(i::Object::NumberValue(*num));
4181 }
4182 
4183 Maybe<int64_t> Value::IntegerValue(Local<Context> context) const {
4184  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4185  if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) {
4186  return Just(NumberToInt64(*obj));
4187  }
4188  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4189  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Value_IntegerValue};
4190  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> num;
4191  if (!i::Object::ToInteger(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num)) return {};
4192  return Just(NumberToInt64(*num));
4193 }
4194 
4195 Maybe<int32_t> Value::Int32Value(Local<Context> context) const {
4196  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4197  if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) return Just(NumberToInt32(*obj));
4198  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4199  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Value_Int32Value};
4200  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> num;
4201  if (!i::Object::ToInt32(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num)) return {};
4202  return Just(IsSmi(*num) ? i::Smi::ToInt(*num)
4203  : static_cast<int32_t>(
4204  i::Cast<i::HeapNumber>(*num)->value()));
4205 }
4206 
4207 Maybe<uint32_t> Value::Uint32Value(Local<Context> context) const {
4208  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4209  if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) return Just(NumberToUint32(*obj));
4210  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4211  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Value_Uint32Value};
4212  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> num;
4213  if (!i::Object::ToUint32(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num)) return {};
4214  return Just(IsSmi(*num) ? static_cast<uint32_t>(i::Smi::ToInt(*num))
4215  : static_cast<uint32_t>(
4216  i::Cast<i::HeapNumber>(*num)->value()));
4217 }
4218 
4219 MaybeLocal<Uint32> Value::ToArrayIndex(Local<Context> context) const {
4220  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4221  if (i::IsSmi(*self)) {
4222  if (i::Smi::ToInt(*self) >= 0) return Utils::Uint32ToLocal(self);
4223  return {};
4224  }
4225  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_Object_ToArrayIndex};
4226  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
4227  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> string_obj;
4228  if (!i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, self).ToHandle(&string_obj)) return {};
4229  auto str = i::Cast<i::String>(string_obj);
4230  uint32_t index;
4231  if (!str->AsArrayIndex(&index)) return {};
4232  i::DirectHandle<i::Number> value =
4233  index <= static_cast<uint32_t>(i::Smi::kMaxValue)
4234  ? direct_handle<i::Number>(i::Smi::FromInt(index), i_isolate)
4235  : i_isolate->factory()->NewNumber(index);
4236  return api_scope.Escape(Utils::Uint32ToLocal(value));
4237 }
