4267 Maybe<bool> Value::InstanceOf(v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
4268  v8::Local<v8::Object> object) {
4269  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4270  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Value_InstanceOf};
4271  i::DirectHandle<i::JSAny> left;
4272  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
4273  i::TryCast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this), &left),
4274  "Value::InstanceOf",
4275  "Invalid type, must be a JS primitive or object.")) {
4276  return {};
4277  }
4278  auto right = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*object);
4279  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
4280  if (!i::Object::InstanceOf(i_isolate, left, right).ToHandle(&result)) {
4281  return {};
4282  }
4283  return Just(i::IsTrue(*result, i_isolate));
4284 }

4286 uint32_t Value::GetHash() {
4287  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4288 
4289  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4290  i::Tagged<i::Object> hash = i::Object::GetHash(*self);
4291  if (IsSmi(hash)) return i::Cast<i::Smi>(hash).value();
4292 
4293  i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> obj = i::Cast<i::JSReceiver>(self);
4294  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4295  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution(i_isolate);
4296  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions(i_isolate);
4297  return obj->GetOrCreateIdentityHash(i_isolate).value();
4298 }

4491 Maybe<bool> v8::Object::DefineOwnProperty(v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
4492  v8::Local<Name> key,
4493  v8::Local<Value> value,
4494  v8::PropertyAttribute attributes) {
4495  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4496  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4497  auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4498  auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4499 
4500  i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4501  desc.set_writable(!(attributes & v8::ReadOnly));
4502  desc.set_enumerable(!(attributes & v8::DontEnum));
4503  desc.set_configurable(!(attributes & v8::DontDelete));
4504  desc.set_value(i::Cast<i::JSAny>(value_obj));
4505 
4506  if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {
4507  // If it's not a JSProxy, i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty should never run
4508  // a script.
4509  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4510  RCCId::kAPI_Object_DefineOwnProperty};
4511  return i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(i_isolate, self, key_obj, &desc,
4512  Just(i::kDontThrow));
4513  }
4514  // JSProxy or WasmObject or other non-JSObject.
4515  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4516  RCCId::kAPI_Object_DefineOwnProperty};
4517  // Even though we said kDontThrow, there might be accessors that do throw.
4518  return i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(i_isolate, self, key_obj, &desc,
4519  Just(i::kDontThrow));
4520 }

4536 Maybe<bool> v8::Object::SetPrivate(Local<Context> context, Local<Private> key,
4537  Local<Value> value) {
4538  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4539  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4540  RCCId::kAPI_Object_SetPrivate};
4541  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4542  auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(reinterpret_cast<Name*>(*key));
4543  auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4544  if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {
4545  auto js_object = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(self);
4546  i::LookupIterator it(i_isolate, js_object, key_obj, js_object);
4547  if (i::JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(&it, value_obj,
4548  i::DONT_ENUM)
4549  .is_null()) {
4550  return {};
4551  }
4552  return Just(true);
4553  }
4554  if (i::IsJSProxy(*self)) {
4555  i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4556  desc.set_writable(true);
4557  desc.set_enumerable(false);
4558  desc.set_configurable(true);
4559  desc.set_value(i::Cast<i::JSAny>(value_obj));
4560  return i::JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSProxy>(self),
4561  i::Cast<i::Symbol>(key_obj), &desc,
4562  Just(i::kDontThrow));
4563  }
4564  // Wasm object, or other kind of special object not supported here.
4565  return Just(false);
4566 }

4605 Maybe<PropertyAttribute> v8::Object::GetPropertyAttributes(
4606  Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key) {
4607  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4608  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4609  RCCId::kAPI_Object_GetPropertyAttributes};
4610  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4611  auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4612  if (!i::IsName(*key_obj)) {
4613  if (!i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, key_obj).ToHandle(&key_obj)) return {};
4614  }
4615  auto key_name = i::Cast<i::Name>(key_obj);
4616  auto result = i::JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(i_isolate, self, key_name);
4617  if (result.IsNothing()) return {};
4618  if (result.FromJust() == i::ABSENT) {
4619  return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttribute>(i::NONE));
4620  }
4621  return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttribute>(result.FromJust()));
4622 }

4624 MaybeLocal<Value> v8::Object::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(Local<Context> context,
4625  Local<Name> key) {
4626  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{
4627  context, RCCId::kAPI_Object_GetOwnPropertyDescriptor};
4628  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
4629  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4630  auto key_name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4631 
4632  i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4633  Maybe<bool> found =
4634  i::JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(i_isolate, obj, key_name, &desc);
4635  if (found.IsNothing()) return {};
4636  if (!found.FromJust()) {
4637  return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
4638  }
4639  return api_scope.Escape(Utils::ToLocal(desc.ToObject(i_isolate)));
4640 }

4649 Local<Value> v8::Object::GetPrototypeV2() {

4654  // Skip hidden prototype (i.e. JSGlobalObject).

4658  return Utils::ToLocal(i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter));

4663 Maybe<bool> SetPrototypeImpl(v8::Object* this_, Local<Context> context,
4664  Local<Value> value, bool from_javascript) {
4665  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4666  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this_);
4667  auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4668  // TODO(333672197): turn this to DCHECK once it's no longer possible
4669  // to get JSGlobalObject via API.
4670  CHECK_IMPLIES(from_javascript, !i::IsJSGlobalObject(*value_obj));
4671  if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {
4672  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
4673  // TODO(333672197): turn this to DCHECK once it's no longer possible
4674  // to get JSGlobalObject via API.
4675  CHECK_IMPLIES(from_javascript, !i::IsJSGlobalObject(*self));
4676  auto result =
4677  i::JSObject::SetPrototype(i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSObject>(self),
4678  value_obj, from_javascript, i::kDontThrow);
4679  // Convert Just(false) to Nothing.
4680  if (!result.FromJust()) return {};
4681  return result;
4682  }
4683  if (i::IsJSProxy(*self)) {
4684  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4685  RCCId::kAPI_Object_SetPrototype};
4686  // We do not allow exceptions thrown while setting the prototype
4687  // to propagate outside.
4688  TryCatch try_catch(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
4689  auto result =
4690  i::JSProxy::SetPrototype(i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSProxy>(self),
4691  value_obj, from_javascript, i::kThrowOnError);
4692  if (result.IsNothing()) return {};
4693  // Convert Just(false) to Just(true).
4694  return Just(true);
4695  }
4696  // Wasm object or other kind of special object not supported here.
4697  return {};
4698 }
4699 
4700 } // namespace
4701 
4702 Maybe<bool> v8::Object::SetPrototype(Local<Context> context,
4703  Local<Value> value) {
4704  static constexpr bool from_javascript = false;
4705  return SetPrototypeImpl(this, context, value, from_javascript);
4706 }
4707 
4708 Maybe<bool> v8::Object::SetPrototypeV2(Local<Context> context,
4709  Local<Value> value) {
4710  static constexpr bool from_javascript = true;
4711  return SetPrototypeImpl(this, context, value, from_javascript);
4712 }
4713 
4714 Local<Object> v8::Object::FindInstanceInPrototypeChain(
4715  v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> tmpl) {
4716  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4717  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4718  i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, *self, i::kStartAtReceiver);
4719  i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> tmpl_info =
4720  *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*tmpl);
4721  if (!IsJSObject(iter.GetCurrent())) return {};
4722  while (!tmpl_info->IsTemplateFor(iter.GetCurrent<i::JSObject>())) {
4723  iter.Advance();
4724  if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return {};
4725  if (!IsJSObject(iter.GetCurrent())) return {};
4726  }
4727  // IsTemplateFor() ensures that iter.GetCurrent() can't be a Proxy here.
4728  return Utils::ToLocal(
4729  i::direct_handle(iter.GetCurrent<i::JSObject>(), i_isolate));
4730 }

4734  context, v8::KeyCollectionMode::kIncludePrototypes,

4736  v8::IndexFilter::kIncludeIndices);
4737 }
4738 
4739 MaybeLocal<Array> v8::Object::GetPropertyNames(
4740  Local<Context> context, KeyCollectionMode mode,
4741  PropertyFilter property_filter, IndexFilter index_filter,
4742  KeyConversionMode key_conversion) {
4743  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context,
4744  RCCId::kAPI_Object_GetPropertyNames};
4745  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
4746  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4747  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> value;
4748  i::KeyAccumulator accumulator(
4749  i_isolate, static_cast<i::KeyCollectionMode>(mode),
4750  static_cast<i::PropertyFilter>(property_filter));
4751  accumulator.set_skip_indices(index_filter == IndexFilter::kSkipIndices);
4752  if (accumulator.CollectKeys(self, self).IsNothing()) return {};
4753  value =
4754  accumulator.GetKeys(static_cast<i::GetKeysConversion>(key_conversion));
4755  DCHECK(self->map()->EnumLength() == i::kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel ||
4756  self->map()->EnumLength() == 0 ||
4757  self->map()->instance_descriptors(i_isolate)->enum_cache()->keys() !=
4758  *value);
4759  auto result = i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayWithElements(value);
4760  return api_scope.Escape(Utils::ToLocal(result));
4761 }

4810 Maybe<bool> v8::Object::Delete(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key) {
4811  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();

4813  auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4814  if (i::IsJSProxy(*self)) {
4815  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Object_Delete};

4817  i::LanguageMode::kSloppy);

4820  // a script.
4821  DCHECK(i::IsJSObject(*self) || i::IsWasmObject(*self));
4822  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4823  RCCId::kAPI_Object_Delete};
4824  return i::Runtime::DeleteObjectProperty(i_isolate, self, key_obj,
4825  i::LanguageMode::kSloppy);
4826  }
4827 }

4842 Maybe<bool> v8::Object::Has(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key) {
4843  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4844  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Object_Has};
4845  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4846  auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4847  // Check if the given key is an array index.
4848  uint32_t index = 0;
4849  if (i::Object::ToArrayIndex(*key_obj, &index)) {
4850  return i::JSReceiver::HasElement(i_isolate, self, index);
4851  }
4852  // Convert the key to a name - possibly by calling back into JavaScript.
4853  i::DirectHandle<i::Name> name;
4854  if (i::Object::ToName(i_isolate, key_obj).ToHandle(&name)) {
4855  return i::JSReceiver::HasProperty(i_isolate, self, name);
4856  }
4857  return {};
4858 }

4878 template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Data>
4879 static Maybe<bool> ObjectSetAccessor(Local<Context> context, Object* self,
4880  Local<Name> name, Getter getter,
4881  Setter setter, Data data,
4882  PropertyAttribute attributes,
4883  bool replace_on_access,
4884  SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
4885  SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
4886  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4887  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
4888  RCCId::kAPI_Object_SetAccessor};
4889  if (!IsJSObject(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(self))) return Just(false);
4890  auto obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(Utils::OpenHandle(self));
4891  i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> info = MakeAccessorInfo(
4892  i_isolate, name, getter, setter, data, replace_on_access);
4893  info->set_getter_side_effect_type(getter_side_effect_type);
4894  info->set_setter_side_effect_type(setter_side_effect_type);
4895  if (info.is_null()) return {};
4896  bool fast = obj->HasFastProperties();
4897  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
4898 
4899  i::DirectHandle<i::Name> accessor_name(info->name(), i_isolate);
4900  i::PropertyAttributes attrs = static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attributes);
4901  if (!i::JSObject::SetAccessor(obj, accessor_name, info, attrs)
4902  .ToHandle(&result)) {
4903  return {};
4904  }
4905  if (i::IsUndefined(*result, i_isolate)) return Just(false);
4906  if (fast) {
4907  i::JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(obj, 0, "APISetAccessor");
4908  }
4909  return Just(true);
4910 }
4911 
4912 void Object::SetAccessorProperty(Local<Name> name, Local<Function> getter,
4913  Local<Function> setter,
4914  PropertyAttribute attributes) {
4915  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4916  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4917  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
4918  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
4919  if (!IsJSObject(*self)) return;
4920  i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> getter_i =
4921  v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*getter);
4922  i::DirectHandle<i::JSAny> setter_i =
4923  v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*setter, true);
4924  if (setter_i.is_null()) setter_i = i_isolate->factory()->null_value();
4925 
4926  i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4927  desc.set_enumerable(!(attributes & v8::DontEnum));
4928  desc.set_configurable(!(attributes & v8::DontDelete));
4929  desc.set_get(getter_i);
4930  desc.set_set(setter_i);
4931 
4932  auto name_i = v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name);
4933  // DefineOwnProperty might still throw if the receiver is a JSProxy and it
4934  // might fail if the receiver is non-extensible or already has this property
4935  // as non-configurable.
4936  Maybe<bool> success = i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(
4937  i_isolate, self, name_i, &desc, Just(i::kDontThrow));
4938  USE(success);
4939 }

4943  AccessorNameGetterCallback getter, AccessorNameSetterCallback setter,
4944  v8::Local<Value> data, PropertyAttribute attributes,
4945  SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
4946  SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
4947  return ObjectSetAccessor(context, this, name, getter, setter, data,
4948  attributes, false, getter_side_effect_type,
4949  setter_side_effect_type);

4952 Maybe<bool> Object::SetLazyDataProperty(

5028 MaybeLocal<Value> v8::Object::GetRealNamedPropertyInPrototypeChain(
5029  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key) {
5030  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{
5031  context, RCCId::kAPI_Object_GetRealNamedPropertyInPrototypeChain};
5032  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
5033  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5034  if (!IsJSObject(*self)) return {};
5035  auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
5036  i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, self);
5037  if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return {};
5038  i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> proto =
5039  i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<i::JSReceiver>(iter);
5040  i::PropertyKey lookup_key(i_isolate, key_obj);
5041  i::LookupIterator it(i_isolate, self, lookup_key, proto,
5042  i::LookupIterator::PROTOTYPE_CHAIN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
5043  MaybeLocal<Value> result = Utils::ToMaybeLocal(i::Object::GetProperty(&it));
5044  if (!it.IsFound()) return {};
5045  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(result);
5046 }

5061  i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<i::JSReceiver>(iter);

5171 namespace {
5172 V8_INLINE void* GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContextImpl(
5173  i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> object,
5174  i::IsolateForSandbox i_isolate_for_sandbox, int index) {
5175  const char* location =
5176  "v8::Object::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContext()";
5177  auto maybe_context = object->GetCreationContext();
5178  if (!maybe_context.has_value()) return nullptr;
5179 
5180  // The code below mostly mimics Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData()
5181  // but it doesn't try to expand the EmbedderDataArray instance.
5182  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5183  i::Tagged<i::NativeContext> native_context = maybe_context.value();
5184 
5185  // This macro requires a real Isolate while |i_isolate_for_sandbox| might be
5186  // nullptr if the V8 sandbox is not enabled.
5187  i::DisallowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly no_execution;
5188  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions;
5189 
5190  // TODO(ishell): remove cast once embedder_data slot has a proper type.
5191  i::Tagged<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
5192  i::Cast<i::EmbedderDataArray>(native_context->embedder_data());
5193  if (V8_LIKELY(static_cast<unsigned>(index) <
5194  static_cast<unsigned>(data->length()))) {
5195  void* result;
5196  Utils::ApiCheck(i::EmbedderDataSlot(data, index)
5197  .ToAlignedPointer(i_isolate_for_sandbox, &result),
5198  location, "Pointer is not aligned");
5199  return result;
5200  }
5201  // Bad index, report an API error.
5202  Utils::ApiCheck(index >= 0, location, "Negative index");
5203  Utils::ApiCheck(index < i::EmbedderDataArray::kMaxLength, location,
5204  "Index too large");
5205  return nullptr;
5206 }
5207 } // namespace
5208 
5209 void* v8::Object::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContext(
5210  v8::Isolate* isolate, int index) {
5211  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5212  auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
5213  return GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContextImpl(self, i_isolate,
5214  index);
5215 }

5217 void* v8::Object::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContext(
5218  int index) {
5219  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5220  i::IsolateForSandbox isolate = i::GetCurrentIsolateForSandbox();
5221  return GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContextImpl(self, isolate,
5222  index);

5242 bool v8::Object::IsApiWrapper() const {
5243  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5244  // This checks whether an object of a given instance type can serve as API
5245  // object. It does not check whether the JS object is wrapped via embedder
5246  // fields or Wrap()/Unwrap() API.
5247  return IsJSApiWrapperObject(*self);
5248 }

5517 bool Function::Experimental_IsNopFunction() const {
5518  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5519  if (!IsJSFunction(*self)) return false;
5520  auto sfi = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(*self)->shared();
5521  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
5522  i::IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(sfi->is_compiled_scope(i_isolate));
5523  if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled() &&
5524  !i::Compiler::Compile(i_isolate, i::handle(sfi, i_isolate),
5525  i::Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION, &is_compiled_scope)) {
5526  return false;
5527  }
5528  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
5529  // Since |sfi| can be GC'ed, we get it again.
5530  sfi = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(*self)->shared();
5531  if (!sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) return false;
5532  i::Handle<i::BytecodeArray> bytecode_array(sfi->GetBytecodeArray(i_isolate),
5533  i_isolate);
5534  i::interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode_array, 0);
5535  if (it.current_bytecode() != i::interpreter::Bytecode::kLdaUndefined) {
5536  return false;
5537  }
5538  it.Advance();
5539  DCHECK(!it.done());
5540  if (it.current_bytecode() != i::interpreter::Bytecode::kReturn) return false;
5541  it.Advance();
5542  DCHECK(it.done());
5543  return true;
5544 }

5566 
5567 // Helpers for ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper
5568 template <size_t size>
5569 struct OneByteMask;
5570 template <>
5571 struct OneByteMask<4> {
5572  static const uint32_t value = 0xFF00FF00;
5573 };
5574 template <>
5575 struct OneByteMask<8> {
5576  static const uint64_t value = 0xFF00'FF00'FF00'FF00;
5577 };
5578 static const uintptr_t kOneByteMask = OneByteMask<sizeof(uintptr_t)>::value;
5579 static const uintptr_t kAlignmentMask = sizeof(uintptr_t) - 1;
5580 static inline bool Unaligned(const uint16_t* chars) {
5581  return reinterpret_cast<const uintptr_t>(chars) & kAlignmentMask;
5582 }
5583 
5584 static inline const uint16_t* Align(const uint16_t* chars) {
5585  return reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(chars) &
5586  ~kAlignmentMask);
5587 }
5588 
5589 class ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper {
5590  public:
5591  ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper() : is_one_byte_(true) {}
5592  ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper(const ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper&) = delete;
5593  ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper& operator=(const ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper&) =
5594  delete;
5595  bool Check(i::Tagged<i::String> string) {
5596  i::Tagged<i::ConsString> cons_string =
5597  i::String::VisitFlat(this, string, 0);
5598  if (cons_string.is_null()) return is_one_byte_;
5599  return CheckCons(cons_string);
5600  }
5601  void VisitOneByteString(const uint8_t* chars, int length) {
5602  // Nothing to do.
5603  }
5604  void VisitTwoByteString(const uint16_t* chars, int length) {
5605  // Accumulated bits.
5606  uintptr_t acc = 0;
5607  // Align to uintptr_t.
5608  const uint16_t* end = chars + length;
5609  while (Unaligned(chars) && chars != end) {
5610  acc |= *chars++;
5611  }
5612  // Read word aligned in blocks,
5613  // checking the return value at the end of each block.
5614  const uint16_t* aligned_end = Align(end);
5615  const int increment = sizeof(uintptr_t) / sizeof(uint16_t);
5616  const int inner_loops = 16;
5617  while (chars + inner_loops * increment < aligned_end) {
5618  for (int i = 0; i < inner_loops; i++) {
5619  acc |= *reinterpret_cast<const uintptr_t*>(chars);
5620  chars += increment;
5621  }
5622  // Check for early return.
5623  if ((acc & kOneByteMask) != 0) {
5624  is_one_byte_ = false;
5625  return;
5626  }
5627  }
5628  // Read the rest.
5629  while (chars != end) {
5630  acc |= *chars++;
5631  }
5632  // Check result.
5633  if ((acc & kOneByteMask) != 0) is_one_byte_ = false;
5634  }
5635 
5636  private:
5637  bool CheckCons(i::Tagged<i::ConsString> cons_string) {
5638  while (true) {
5639  // Check left side if flat.
5640  i::Tagged<i::String> left = cons_string->first();
5641  i::Tagged<i::ConsString> left_as_cons =
5642  i::String::VisitFlat(this, left, 0);
5643  if (!is_one_byte_) return false;
5644  // Check right side if flat.
5645  i::Tagged<i::String> right = cons_string->second();
5646  i::Tagged<i::ConsString> right_as_cons =
5647  i::String::VisitFlat(this, right, 0);
5648  if (!is_one_byte_) return false;
5649  // Standard recurse/iterate trick.
5650  if (!left_as_cons.is_null() && !right_as_cons.is_null()) {
5651  if (left->length() < right->length()) {
5652  CheckCons(left_as_cons);
5653  cons_string = right_as_cons;
5654  } else {
5655  CheckCons(right_as_cons);
5656  cons_string = left_as_cons;
5657  }
5658  // Check fast return.
5659  if (!is_one_byte_) return false;
5660  continue;
5661  }
5662  // Descend left in place.
5663  if (!left_as_cons.is_null()) {
5664  cons_string = left_as_cons;
5665  continue;
5666  }
5667  // Descend right in place.
5668  if (!right_as_cons.is_null()) {
5669  cons_string = right_as_cons;
5670  continue;
5671  }
5672  // Terminate.
5673  break;
5674  }
5675  return is_one_byte_;
5676  }
5677  bool is_one_byte_;
5678 };
5679 
5680 bool String::ContainsOnlyOneByte() const {
5681  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5682  if (str->IsOneByteRepresentation()) return true;
5683  ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper helper;
5684  return helper.Check(*str);
5685 }
5686 
5687 int String::Utf8Length(Isolate* v8_isolate) const {
5688  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5689  str = i::String::Flatten(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), str);
5690  int length = str->length();
5691  if (length == 0) return 0;
5692  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5693  i::String::FlatContent flat = str->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
5694  DCHECK(flat.IsFlat());
5695  int utf8_length = 0;
5696  if (flat.IsOneByte()) {
5697  for (uint8_t c : flat.ToOneByteVector()) {
5698  utf8_length += c >> 7;
5699  }
5700  utf8_length += length;
5701  } else {
5702  int last_character = unibrow::Utf16::kNoPreviousCharacter;
5703  for (uint16_t c : flat.ToUC16Vector()) {
5704  utf8_length += unibrow::Utf8::Length(c, last_character);
5705  last_character = c;
5706  }
5707  }
5708  return utf8_length;
5709 }
5710 
5711 size_t String::Utf8LengthV2(Isolate* v8_isolate) const {
5712  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5713  return i::String::Utf8Length(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), str);
5714 }
5715 
5716 namespace {
5717 // Writes the flat content of a string to a buffer. This is done in two phases.
5718 // The first phase calculates a pessimistic estimate (writable_length) on how
5719 // many code units can be safely written without exceeding the buffer capacity
5720 // and without leaving at a lone surrogate. The estimated number of code units
5721 // is then written out in one go, and the reported byte usage is used to
5722 // correct the estimate. This is repeated until the estimate becomes <= 0 or
5723 // all code units have been written out. The second phase writes out code
5724 // units until the buffer capacity is reached, would be exceeded by the next
5725 // unit, or all code units have been written out.
5726 template <typename Char>
5727 static int WriteUtf8Impl(base::Vector<const Char> string, char* write_start,
5728  int write_capacity, int options,
5729  int* utf16_chars_read_out) {
5730  bool write_null = !(options & v8::String::NO_NULL_TERMINATION);
5731  bool replace_invalid_utf8 = (options & v8::String::REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8);
5732  char* current_write = write_start;
5733  const Char* read_start = string.begin();
5734  int read_index = 0;
5735  int read_length = string.length();
5736  int prev_char = unibrow::Utf16::kNoPreviousCharacter;
5737  // Do a fast loop where there is no exit capacity check.
5738  // Need enough space to write everything but one character.
5739  static_assert(unibrow::Utf16::kMaxExtraUtf8BytesForOneUtf16CodeUnit == 3);
5740  static const int kMaxSizePerChar = sizeof(Char) == 1 ? 2 : 3;
5741  while (read_index < read_length) {
5742  int up_to = read_length;
5743  if (write_capacity != -1) {
5744  int remaining_capacity =
5745  write_capacity - static_cast<int>(current_write - write_start);
5746  int writable_length =
5747  (remaining_capacity - kMaxSizePerChar) / kMaxSizePerChar;
5748  // Need to drop into slow loop.
5749  if (writable_length <= 0) break;
5750  up_to = std::min(up_to, read_index + writable_length);
5751  }
5752  // Write the characters to the stream.
5753  if (sizeof(Char) == 1) {
5754  // Simply memcpy if we only have ASCII characters.
5755  uint8_t char_mask = 0;
5756  for (int i = read_index; i < up_to; i++) char_mask |= read_start[i];
5757  if ((char_mask & 0x80) == 0) {
5758  int copy_length = up_to - read_index;
5759  memcpy(current_write, read_start + read_index, copy_length);
5760  current_write += copy_length;
5761  read_index = up_to;
5762  } else {
5763  for (; read_index < up_to; read_index++) {
5764  current_write += unibrow::Utf8::EncodeOneByte(
5765  current_write, static_cast<uint8_t>(read_start[read_index]));
5766  DCHECK(write_capacity == -1 ||
5767  (current_write - write_start) <= write_capacity);
5768  }
5769  }
5770  } else {
5771  for (; read_index < up_to; read_index++) {
5772  uint16_t character = read_start[read_index];
5773  current_write += unibrow::Utf8::Encode(current_write, character,
5774  prev_char, replace_invalid_utf8);
5775  prev_char = character;
5776  DCHECK(write_capacity == -1 ||
5777  (current_write - write_start) <= write_capacity);
5778  }
5779  }
5780  }
5781  if (read_index < read_length) {
5782  DCHECK_NE(-1, write_capacity);
5783  // Aborted due to limited capacity. Check capacity on each iteration.
5784  int remaining_capacity =
5785  write_capacity - static_cast<int>(current_write - write_start);
5786  DCHECK_GE(remaining_capacity, 0);
5787  for (; read_index < read_length && remaining_capacity > 0; read_index++) {
5788  uint32_t character = read_start[read_index];
5789  int written = 0;
5790  // We can't use a local buffer here because Encode needs to modify
5791  // previous characters in the stream. We know, however, that
5792  // exactly one character will be advanced.
5793  if (unibrow::Utf16::IsSurrogatePair(prev_char, character)) {
5794  written = unibrow::Utf8::Encode(current_write, character, prev_char,
5795  replace_invalid_utf8);
5796  DCHECK_EQ(written, 1);
5797  } else {
5798  // Use a scratch buffer to check the required characters.
5799  char temp_buffer[unibrow::Utf8::kMaxEncodedSize];
5800  // Encoding a surrogate pair to Utf8 always takes 4 bytes.
5801  static const int kSurrogatePairEncodedSize =
5802  static_cast<int>(unibrow::Utf8::kMaxEncodedSize);
5803  // For REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8, catch the case where we cut off in the
5804  // middle of a surrogate pair. Abort before encoding the pair instead.
5805  if (replace_invalid_utf8 &&
5806  remaining_capacity < kSurrogatePairEncodedSize &&
5807  unibrow::Utf16::IsLeadSurrogate(character) &&
5808  read_index + 1 < read_length &&
5809  unibrow::Utf16::IsTrailSurrogate(read_start[read_index + 1])) {
5810  write_null = false;
5811  break;
5812  }
5813  // Can't encode using prev_char as gcc has array bounds issues.
5814  written = unibrow::Utf8::Encode(temp_buffer, character,
5815  unibrow::Utf16::kNoPreviousCharacter,
5816  replace_invalid_utf8);
5817  if (written > remaining_capacity) {
5818  // Won't fit. Abort and do not null-terminate the result.
5819  write_null = false;
5820  break;
5821  }
5822  // Copy over the character from temp_buffer.
5823  for (int i = 0; i < written; i++) current_write[i] = temp_buffer[i];
5824  }
5825 
5826  current_write += written;
5827  remaining_capacity -= written;
5828  prev_char = character;
5829  }
5830  }
5831 
5832  // Write out number of utf16 characters written to the stream.
5833  if (utf16_chars_read_out != nullptr) *utf16_chars_read_out = read_index;
5834 
5835  // Only null-terminate if there's space.
5836  if (write_null && (write_capacity == -1 ||
5837  (current_write - write_start) < write_capacity)) {
5838  *current_write++ = '\0';
5839  }
5840  return static_cast<int>(current_write - write_start);
5841 }
5842 } // anonymous namespace
5843 
5844 int String::WriteUtf8(Isolate* v8_isolate, char* buffer, int capacity,
5845  int* nchars_ref, int options) const {
5846  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5847  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
5848  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_String_WriteUtf8);
5849  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
5850  str = i::String::Flatten(i_isolate, str);
5851  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5852  i::String::FlatContent content = str->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
5853  if (content.IsOneByte()) {
5854  return WriteUtf8Impl<uint8_t>(content.ToOneByteVector(), buffer, capacity,
5855  options, nchars_ref);
5856  } else {
5857  return WriteUtf8Impl<uint16_t>(content.ToUC16Vector(), buffer, capacity,
5858  options, nchars_ref);
5859  }
5860 }
5861 
5862 template <typename CharType>
5863 static inline int WriteHelper(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const String* string,
5864  CharType* buffer, int start, int length,
5865  int options) {
5866  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_String_Write);
5867  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
5868  DCHECK(start >= 0 && length >= -1);
5869  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(string);
5870  int end = start + length;
5871  if ((length == -1) || (static_cast<uint32_t>(length) > str->length() - start))
5872  end = str->length();
5873  if (end < 0) return 0;
5874  int write_length = end - start;
5875  if (start < end) i::String::WriteToFlat(*str, buffer, start, write_length);
5876  if (!(options & String::NO_NULL_TERMINATION) &&
5877  (length == -1 || write_length < length)) {
5878  buffer[write_length] = '\0';
5879  }
5880  return write_length;
5881 }
5882 
5883 int String::WriteOneByte(Isolate* v8_isolate, uint8_t* buffer, int start,
5884  int length, int options) const {
5885  return WriteHelper(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), this, buffer,
5886  start, length, options);
5887 }
5888 
5889 int String::Write(Isolate* v8_isolate, uint16_t* buffer, int start, int length,
5890  int options) const {
5891  return WriteHelper(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), this, buffer,
5892  start, length, options);
5893 }

5895 template <typename CharType>
5896 static inline void WriteHelperV2(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const String* string,
5897  CharType* buffer, uint32_t offset,
5898  uint32_t length, int flags) {
5899  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_String_Write);
5900  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
5901 
5902  DCHECK_LE(length, string->Length());
5903  DCHECK_LE(offset, string->Length() - length);
5904 
5905  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(string);
5906  i::String::WriteToFlat(*str, buffer, offset, length);
5907  if (flags & String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate) {
5908  buffer[length] = '\0';
5909  }
5910 }

5950 v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(
5951  i::Tagged<i::String> string, uint32_t raw_hash, bool* is_one_byte) {
5952  DCHECK(i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash));
5953  const int index = i::String::ForwardingIndexValueBits::decode(raw_hash);
5954  // Note that with a shared heap the main and worker isolates all share the
5955  // same forwarding table.
5956  auto resource =
5957  i::Isolate::Current()->string_forwarding_table()->GetExternalResource(
5958  index, is_one_byte);
5959  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(resource);
5960  return resource;
5961 }

5969 bool v8::String::IsExternalTwoByte() const {
5970  auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5971  if (i::StringShape(*str).IsExternalTwoByte()) return true;
5972  uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
5973  if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
5974  bool is_one_byte;
5975  GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(*str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
5976  return !is_one_byte;
5977  }
5978  return false;
5979 }

5999 void v8::String::VerifyExternalStringResource(
6000  v8::String::ExternalStringResource* value) const {
6001  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6002  i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6003  const v8::String::ExternalStringResource* expected;
6004 
6005  if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6006  str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6007  }
6008 
6009  if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6010  const void* resource = i::Cast<i::ExternalTwoByteString>(str)->resource();
6011  expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResource*>(resource);
6012  } else {
6013  uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6014  if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6015  bool is_one_byte;
6016  auto resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(
6017  str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
6018  if (!is_one_byte) {
6019  expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResource*>(resource);
6020  }
6021  } else {
6022  expected = nullptr;
6023  }
6024  }
6025  CHECK_EQ(expected, value);
6026 }
6027 
6028 void v8::String::VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(
6029  v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* value, Encoding encoding) const {
6030  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6031  i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6032  const v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* expected;
6033  Encoding expectedEncoding;
6034 
6035  if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6036  str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6037  }
6038 
6039  if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalOneByte()) {
6040  const void* resource = i::Cast<i::ExternalOneByteString>(str)->resource();
6041  expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResourceBase*>(resource);
6042  expectedEncoding = ONE_BYTE_ENCODING;
6043  } else if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6044  const void* resource = i::Cast<i::ExternalTwoByteString>(str)->resource();
6045  expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResourceBase*>(resource);
6046  expectedEncoding = TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6047  } else {
6048  uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6049  if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6050  bool is_one_byte;
6051  expected = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(str, raw_hash_field,
6052  &is_one_byte);
6053  expectedEncoding = is_one_byte ? ONE_BYTE_ENCODING : TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6054  } else {
6055  expected = nullptr;
6056  expectedEncoding = str->IsOneByteRepresentation() ? ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
6057  : TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6058  }
6059  }
6060  CHECK_EQ(expected, value);
6061  CHECK_EQ(expectedEncoding, encoding);
6062 }

6064 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResourceSlow() const {
6065  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6066  i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6067 
6068  if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6069  str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6070  }
6071 
6072  if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6073  Isolate* isolate = i::Internals::GetCurrentIsolateForSandbox();
6074  i::Address value =
6075  i::Internals::ReadExternalPointerField<i::kExternalStringResourceTag>(
6076  isolate, str.ptr(), i::Internals::kStringResourceOffset);
6077  return reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
6078  } else {
6079  uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6080  if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6081  bool is_one_byte;
6082  auto resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(
6083  str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
6084  if (!is_one_byte) {
6085  return reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResource*>(resource);
6086  }
6087  }
6088  }
6089  return nullptr;
6090 }

6110 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(
6111  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
6112  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6113  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = nullptr;
6114  i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6115 
6116  if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6117  str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6118  }
6119 
6120  internal::Address string = str.ptr();
6121  int type = i::Internals::GetInstanceType(string) &
6122  i::Internals::kStringRepresentationAndEncodingMask;
6123  *encoding_out =
6124  static_cast<Encoding>(type & i::Internals::kStringEncodingMask);
6125  if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalOneByte() ||
6126  i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6127  Isolate* isolate = i::Internals::GetCurrentIsolateForSandbox();
6128  i::Address value =
6129  i::Internals::ReadExternalPointerField<i::kExternalStringResourceTag>(
6130  isolate, string, i::Internals::kStringResourceOffset);
6131  resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
6132  } else {
6133  uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field();
6134  if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6135  bool is_one_byte;
6136  resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(str, raw_hash_field,
6137  &is_one_byte);
6138  *encoding_out = is_one_byte ? Encoding::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
6139  : Encoding::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6140  }
6141  }
6142  return resource;
6143 }

6287 void v8::Object::SetAlignedPointerInInternalFields(int argc, int indices[],
6288  void* values[]) {
6289  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6290  if (!IsJSObject(*obj)) return;
6291  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6292  const char* location = "v8::Object::SetAlignedPointerInInternalFields()";
6293  auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj);
6294  int nof_embedder_fields = js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
6295  for (int i = 0; i < argc; i++) {
6296  int index = indices[i];
6297  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(index < nof_embedder_fields, location,
6298  "Internal field out of bounds")) {
6299  return;
6300  }
6301  void* value = values[i];
6302  Utils::ApiCheck(
6303  i::EmbedderDataSlot(js_obj, index)
6304  .store_aligned_pointer(i::Isolate::Current(), *obj, value),
6305  location, "Unaligned pointer");
6306  DCHECK_EQ(value, GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index));
6307  }
6308 }
6309 
6310 // static
6311 void* v8::Object::Unwrap(v8::Isolate* isolate, i::Address wrapper_obj,
6312  CppHeapPointerTagRange tag_range) {
6313  DCHECK_LE(tag_range.lower_bound, tag_range.upper_bound);
6314  return i::CppHeapObjectWrapper(
6315  i::Cast<i::JSObject>(i::Tagged<i::Object>(wrapper_obj)))
6316  .GetCppHeapWrappable(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate), tag_range);
6317 }

6323  i::Cast<i::JSObject>(i::Tagged<i::Object>(wrapper_obj)))
6324  .SetCppHeapWrappable(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate), wrappable,
6325  tag);
6326 }

6335 
6336 bool v8::V8::Initialize(const int build_config) {
6337  const bool kEmbedderPointerCompression =
6338  (build_config & kPointerCompression) != 0;
6339  if (kEmbedderPointerCompression != COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
6340  FATAL(
6341  "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6342  "pointer compression is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6343  kEmbedderPointerCompression ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED",
6344  COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED");
6345  }
6346 
6347  const int kEmbedderSmiValueSize = (build_config & k31BitSmis) ? 31 : 32;
6348  if (kEmbedderSmiValueSize != internal::kSmiValueSize) {
6349  FATAL(
6350  "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6351  "Smi value size is %d while on V8 side it's %d.",
6352  kEmbedderSmiValueSize, internal::kSmiValueSize);
6353  }
6354 
6355  const bool kEmbedderSandbox = (build_config & kSandbox) != 0;
6356  if (kEmbedderSandbox != V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL) {
6357  FATAL(
6358  "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6359  "sandbox is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6360  kEmbedderSandbox ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED",
6361  V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED");
6362  }
6363 
6364  const bool kEmbedderTargetOsIsAndroid =
6365  (build_config & kTargetOsIsAndroid) != 0;
6366 #ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_ANDROID
6367  const bool kV8TargetOsIsAndroid = true;
6368 #else
6369  const bool kV8TargetOsIsAndroid = false;
6370 #endif
6371  if (kEmbedderTargetOsIsAndroid != kV8TargetOsIsAndroid) {
6372  FATAL(
6373  "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6374  "target OS is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6375  kEmbedderTargetOsIsAndroid ? "Android" : "not Android",
6376  kV8TargetOsIsAndroid ? "Android" : "not Android");
6377  }
6378 
6379  const bool kEmbedderEnableChecks = (build_config & kEnableChecks) != 0;
6380 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6381  const bool kV8EnableChecks = true;
6382 #else
6383  const bool kV8EnableChecks = false;
6384 #endif
6385  if (kEmbedderEnableChecks != kV8EnableChecks) {
6386  FATAL(
6387  "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6388  "V8_ENABLE_CHECKS is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6389  kEmbedderEnableChecks ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED",
6390  kV8EnableChecks ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED");
6391  }
6392 
6393  i::V8::Initialize();
6394  if (!cppgc::IsInitialized()) {
6395  // cppgc::InitializeProcess() has to becalled after V8::Initialize().
6396  // V8::Initialize() triggers OS::Platform initialization code that is needed
6397  // by the default page allocator on Fuchsia to allocate memory correctly.
6398  cppgc::InitializeProcess(i::V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->GetPageAllocator());
6399  }
6400  return true;
6401 }

6405  void* context) {

6557 
6558 template <typename ObjectType>
6559 struct InvokeBootstrapper;
6560 
6561 template <>
6562 struct InvokeBootstrapper<i::NativeContext> {
6563  i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> Invoke(
6564  i::Isolate* i_isolate,
6565  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
6566  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
6567  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6568  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6569  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6570  return i_isolate->bootstrapper()->CreateEnvironment(
6571  maybe_global_proxy, global_proxy_template, extensions,
6572  context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer, microtask_queue);
6573  }
6574 };
6575 
6576 template <>
6577 struct InvokeBootstrapper<i::JSGlobalProxy> {
6578  i::DirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> Invoke(
6579  i::Isolate* i_isolate,
6580  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
6581  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
6582  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6583  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6584  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6585  USE(extensions);
6586  USE(context_snapshot_index);
6587  return i_isolate->bootstrapper()->NewRemoteContext(maybe_global_proxy,
6588  global_proxy_template);
6589  }
6590 };
6591 
6592 template <typename ObjectType>
6593 static i::DirectHandle<ObjectType> CreateEnvironment(
6594  i::Isolate* i_isolate, v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6595  v8::MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate> maybe_global_template,
6596  v8::MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_global_proxy, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6597  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6598  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6599  i::DirectHandle<ObjectType> result;
6600 
6601  {
6602  // Do some part of the EnterV8Scope, but without a context yet.
6603  DCHECK_IMPLIES(i::v8_flags.strict_termination_checks,
6604  !i_isolate->is_execution_terminating());
6605  i::VMState<v8::OTHER> vm_state(i_isolate);
6606  i::DisallowExceptionsDebugOnly no_exceptions(i_isolate);
6607 
6608  v8::Local<ObjectTemplate> proxy_template;
6609  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> proxy_constructor;
6610  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor;
6611  i::DirectHandle<i::UnionOf<i::Undefined, i::InterceptorInfo>>
6612  named_interceptor(i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
6613  i::DirectHandle<i::UnionOf<i::Undefined, i::InterceptorInfo>>
6614  indexed_interceptor(i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
6615 
6616  if (!maybe_global_template.IsEmpty()) {
6617  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_template =
6618  maybe_global_template.ToLocalChecked();
6619  // Make sure that the global_template has a constructor.
6620  global_constructor = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *global_template);
6621 
6622  // Create a fresh template for the global proxy object.
6623  proxy_template =
6624  ObjectTemplate::New(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
6625  proxy_constructor = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *proxy_template);
6626 
6627  // Set the global template to be the prototype template of
6628  // global proxy template.
6629  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetPrototypeTemplate(
6630  i_isolate, proxy_constructor,
6631  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_template));
6632 
6633  proxy_template->SetInternalFieldCount(
6634  global_template->InternalFieldCount());
6635 
6636  // Migrate security handlers from global_template to
6637  // proxy_template. Temporarily removing access check
6638  // information from the global template.
6639  if (!IsUndefined(global_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo(), i_isolate)) {
6640  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(
6641  i_isolate, proxy_constructor,
6642  direct_handle(global_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo(), i_isolate));
6643  proxy_constructor->set_needs_access_check(
6644  global_constructor->needs_access_check());
6645  global_constructor->set_needs_access_check(false);
6646  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(
6647  i_isolate, global_constructor,
6648  i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
6649  }
6650 
6651  // Same for other interceptors. If the global constructor has
6652  // interceptors, we need to replace them temporarily with noop
6653  // interceptors, so the map is correctly marked as having interceptors,
6654  // but we don't invoke any.
6655  if (!IsUndefined(global_constructor->GetNamedPropertyHandler(),
6656  i_isolate)) {
6657  named_interceptor = direct_handle(
6658  global_constructor->GetNamedPropertyHandler(), i_isolate);
6659  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetNamedPropertyHandler(
6660  i_isolate, global_constructor,
6661  i_isolate->factory()->noop_interceptor_info());
6662  }
6663  if (!IsUndefined(global_constructor->GetIndexedPropertyHandler(),
6664  i_isolate)) {
6665  indexed_interceptor = direct_handle(
6666  global_constructor->GetIndexedPropertyHandler(), i_isolate);
6667  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetIndexedPropertyHandler(
6668  i_isolate, global_constructor,
6669  i_isolate->factory()->noop_interceptor_info());
6670  }
6671  }
6672 
6673  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> maybe_proxy;
6674  if (!maybe_global_proxy.IsEmpty()) {
6675  maybe_proxy = i::Cast<i::JSGlobalProxy>(
6676  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*maybe_global_proxy.ToLocalChecked()));
6677  }
6678  // Create the environment.
6679  InvokeBootstrapper<ObjectType> invoke;
6680  result = invoke.Invoke(i_isolate, maybe_proxy, proxy_template, extensions,
6681  context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer,
6682  microtask_queue);
6683 
6684  // Restore the access check info and interceptors on the global template.
6685  if (!maybe_global_template.IsEmpty()) {
6686  DCHECK(!global_constructor.is_null());
6687  DCHECK(!proxy_constructor.is_null());
6688  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(
6689  i_isolate, global_constructor,
6690  i::direct_handle(proxy_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo(), i_isolate));
6691  global_constructor->set_needs_access_check(
6692  proxy_constructor->needs_access_check());
6693  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetNamedPropertyHandler(
6694  i_isolate, global_constructor, named_interceptor);
6695  i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetIndexedPropertyHandler(
6696  i_isolate, global_constructor, indexed_interceptor);
6697  }
6698  }
6699  // Leave V8.
6700 
6701  return result;
6702 }
6703 
6704 Local<Context> NewContext(
6705  v8::Isolate* external_isolate, v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6706  v8::MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate> global_template,
6707  v8::MaybeLocal<Value> global_object, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6708  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6709  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6710  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(external_isolate);
6711  // TODO(jkummerow): This is for crbug.com/713699. Remove it if it doesn't
6712  // fail.
6713  // Sanity-check that the isolate is initialized and usable.
6714  CHECK(IsCode(i_isolate->builtins()->code(i::Builtin::kIllegal)));
6715 
6716  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.NewContext");
6717  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_Context_New);
6718  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
6719  ExtensionConfiguration no_extensions;
6720  if (extensions == nullptr) extensions = &no_extensions;
6721  i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> env = CreateEnvironment<i::NativeContext>(
6722  i_isolate, extensions, global_template, global_object,
6723  context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer, microtask_queue);
6724  if (env.is_null()) return {};
6725  return Utils::ToLocal(scope.CloseAndEscape(env));
6726 }
6727 
6728 Local<Context> v8::Context::New(
6729  v8::Isolate* external_isolate, v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6730  v8::MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate> global_template,
6731  v8::MaybeLocal<Value> global_object,
6732  v8::DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback internal_fields_deserializer,
6733  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue,
6734  v8::DeserializeContextDataCallback context_callback_deserializer,
6735  v8::DeserializeAPIWrapperCallback api_wrapper_deserializer) {
6736  return NewContext(
6737  external_isolate, extensions, global_template, global_object, 0,
6738  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback(internal_fields_deserializer,
6739  context_callback_deserializer,
6740  api_wrapper_deserializer),
6741  microtask_queue);
6742 }
6743 
6744 MaybeLocal<Context> v8::Context::FromSnapshot(
6745  v8::Isolate* external_isolate, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6746  v8::DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback internal_fields_deserializer,
6747  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, MaybeLocal<Value> global_object,
6748  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue,
6749  v8::DeserializeContextDataCallback context_callback_deserializer,
6750  v8::DeserializeAPIWrapperCallback api_wrapper_deserializer) {
6751  size_t index_including_default_context = context_snapshot_index + 1;
6752  if (!i::Snapshot::HasContextSnapshot(
6753  reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(external_isolate),
6754  index_including_default_context)) {
6755  return {};
6756  }
6757  return NewContext(
6758  external_isolate, extensions, MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate>(), global_object,
6759  index_including_default_context,
6760  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback(internal_fields_deserializer,
6761  context_callback_deserializer,
6762  api_wrapper_deserializer),
6763  microtask_queue);
6764 }
6765 
6766 MaybeLocal<Object> v8::Context::NewRemoteContext(
6767  v8::Isolate* external_isolate, v8::Local<ObjectTemplate> global_template,
6768  v8::MaybeLocal<v8::Value> global_object) {
6769  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(external_isolate);
6770  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
6771  RCCId::kAPI_Context_NewRemoteContext);
6772  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
6773  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor =
6774  EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *global_template);
6775  Utils::ApiCheck(global_constructor->needs_access_check(),
6776  "v8::Context::NewRemoteContext",
6777  "Global template needs to have access checks enabled");
6778  i::DirectHandle<i::AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info(
6779  i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(global_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo()),
6780  i_isolate);
6781  Utils::ApiCheck(
6782  access_check_info->named_interceptor() != i::Tagged<i::Object>(),
6783  "v8::Context::NewRemoteContext",
6784  "Global template needs to have access check handlers");
6785  i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> global_proxy =
6786  CreateEnvironment<i::JSGlobalProxy>(
6787  i_isolate, nullptr, global_template, global_object, 0,
6788  i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback(), nullptr);
6789  if (global_proxy.is_null()) {
6790  if (i_isolate->has_exception()) i_isolate->clear_exception();
6791  return {};
6792  }
6793  return Utils::ToLocal(scope.CloseAndEscape(global_proxy));
6794 }

6814 namespace {
6815 
6816 bool MayContainObjectsToFreeze(i::InstanceType obj_type) {
6817  if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(obj_type)) return false;
6818  // SharedFunctionInfo is cross-context so it shouldn't be frozen.
6819  if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj_type)) return false;
6820  // All TemplateInfo objects are cross-context so they shouldn't be frozen.
6821  if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsTemplateInfo(obj_type)) return false;
6822  return true;
6823 }
6824 
6825 bool RequiresEmbedderSupportToFreeze(i::InstanceType obj_type) {
6826  DCHECK(i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type));
6827 
6828  return (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(obj_type) ||
6829  i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSExternalObject(obj_type) ||
6830  i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots(obj_type) ||
6831  i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsCppHeapExternalObject(obj_type));
6832 }
6833 
6834 bool IsJSReceiverSafeToFreeze(i::InstanceType obj_type) {
6835  DCHECK(i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type));
6836 
6837  switch (obj_type) {
6838  case i::JS_OBJECT_TYPE:
6839  case i::JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE:
6840  case i::JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE:
6841  case i::JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
6842  case i::JS_FUNCTION_TYPE:
6843  /* Function types */
6844  case i::BIGINT64_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6845  case i::BIGUINT64_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6846  case i::FLOAT16_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6847  case i::FLOAT32_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6848  case i::FLOAT64_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6849  case i::INT16_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6850  case i::INT32_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6851  case i::INT8_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6852  case i::UINT16_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6853  case i::UINT32_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6854  case i::UINT8_CLAMPED_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6855  case i::UINT8_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6856  case i::JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6857  case i::JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6858  case i::JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6859  case i::JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
6860  /* Prototype Types */
6861  case i::JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6862  case i::JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6863  case i::JS_MAP_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6864  case i::JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6865  case i::JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6866  case i::JS_REG_EXP_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6867  case i::JS_SET_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6868  case i::JS_SET_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6869  case i::JS_STRING_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6870  case i::JS_TYPED_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
6871  /* */
6872  case i::JS_ARRAY_TYPE:
6873  return true;
6874 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6875  case i::WASM_ARRAY_TYPE:
6876  case i::WASM_STRUCT_TYPE:
6877  case i::WASM_TAG_OBJECT_TYPE:
6878 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6879  case i::JS_PROXY_TYPE:
6880  return true;
6881  // These types are known not to freeze.
6882  case i::JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
6883  case i::JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
6884  case i::JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
6885  case i::JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
6886  case i::JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
6887  case i::JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE:
6888  case i::JS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_OBJECT_TYPE:
6889  case i::JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE:
6890  case i::JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_TYPE: {
6891  return false;
6892  }
6893  default:
6894  // TODO(behamilton): Handle any types that fall through here.
6895  return false;
6896  }
6897 }
6898 
6899 class ObjectVisitorDeepFreezer : i::ObjectVisitor {
6900  public:
6901  explicit ObjectVisitorDeepFreezer(i::Isolate* isolate,
6902  Context::DeepFreezeDelegate* delegate)
6903  : isolate_(isolate),
6904  delegate_(delegate),
6905  objects_to_freeze_(isolate),
6906  lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_(isolate) {}
6907 
6908  bool DeepFreeze(i::DirectHandle<i::Context> context) {
6909  bool success = VisitObject(i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(*context));
6910  if (success) {
6911  success = InstantiateAndVisitLazyAccessorPairs();
6912  }
6913  DCHECK_EQ(success, !error_.has_value());
6914  if (!success) {
6915  THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
6916  isolate_, NewTypeError(error_->msg_id, error_->name), false);
6917  }
6918  for (const auto& obj : objects_to_freeze_) {
6919  MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6920  isolate_,
6921  i::JSReceiver::SetIntegrityLevel(isolate_, obj, i::FROZEN,
6922  i::kThrowOnError),
6923  false);
6924  }
6925  return true;
6926  }
6927 
6928  void VisitPointers(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host, i::ObjectSlot start,
6929  i::ObjectSlot end) final {
6930  VisitPointersImpl(start, end);
6931  }
6932  void VisitPointers(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host, i::MaybeObjectSlot start,
6933  i::MaybeObjectSlot end) final {
6934  VisitPointersImpl(start, end);
6935  }
6936  void VisitMapPointer(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host) final {
6937  VisitPointer(host, host->map_slot());
6938  }
6939  void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(i::Tagged<i::Code> host,
6940  i::InstructionStreamSlot slot) final {}
6941  void VisitCustomWeakPointers(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host,
6942  i::ObjectSlot start, i::ObjectSlot end) final {}
6943 
6944  private:
6945  struct ErrorInfo {
6946  i::MessageTemplate msg_id;
6947  i::DirectHandle<i::String> name;
6948  };
6949 
6950  template <typename TSlot>
6951  void VisitPointersImpl(TSlot start, TSlot end) {
6952  for (TSlot current = start; current < end; ++current) {
6953  typename TSlot::TObject object = current.load(isolate_);
6954  i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> heap_object;
6955  if (object.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
6956  if (!VisitObject(heap_object)) {
6957  return;
6958  }
6959  }
6960  }
6961  }
6962 
6963  bool FreezeEmbedderObjectAndVisitChildren(i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> obj) {
6964  DCHECK(delegate_);
6965  LocalVector<Object> children(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate_));
6966  if (!delegate_->FreezeEmbedderObjectAndGetChildren(Utils::ToLocal(obj),
6967  children)) {
6968  return false;
6969  }
6970  for (auto child : children) {
6971  if (!VisitObject(
6972  *Utils::OpenDirectHandle<Object, i::JSReceiver>(child))) {
6973  return false;
6974  }
6975  }
6976  return true;
6977  }
6978 
6979  bool VisitObject(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> obj) {
6980  DCHECK(!obj.is_null());
6981  if (error_.has_value()) {
6982  return false;
6983  }
6984 
6985  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6986  i::InstanceType obj_type = obj->map()->instance_type();
6987 
6988  // Skip common types that can't contain items to freeze.
6989  if (!MayContainObjectsToFreeze(obj_type)) {
6990  return true;
6991  }
6992 
6993  if (!done_list_.insert(obj).second) {
6994  // If we couldn't insert (because it is already in the set) then we're
6995  // done.
6996  return true;
6997  }
6998 
6999  if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsAccessorPair(obj_type)) {
7000  // For AccessorPairs we need to ensure that the functions they point to
7001  // have been instantiated into actual JavaScript objects that can be
7002  // frozen. If they haven't then we need to save them to instantiate
7003  // (and recurse) before freezing.
7004  i::Tagged<i::AccessorPair> accessor_pair = i::Cast<i::AccessorPair>(obj);
7005  if (i::IsFunctionTemplateInfo(accessor_pair->getter()) ||
7006  IsFunctionTemplateInfo(accessor_pair->setter())) {
7007  i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorPair> lazy_accessor_pair(accessor_pair,
7008  isolate_);
7009  lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_.push_back(lazy_accessor_pair);
7010  }
7011  } else if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(obj_type)) {
7012  // For contexts we need to ensure that all accessible locals are const.
7013  // If not they could be replaced to bypass freezing.
7014  i::Tagged<i::ScopeInfo> scope_info =
7015  i::Cast<i::Context>(obj)->scope_info();
7016  for (auto it : i::ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
7017  if (!IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(
7018  scope_info->ContextLocalMode(it->index()))) {
7019  DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7020  error_ = ErrorInfo{i::MessageTemplate::kCannotDeepFreezeValue,
7021  i::direct_handle(it->name(), isolate_)};
7022  return false;
7023  }
7024  }
7025  } else if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type)) {
7026  i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> receiver(i::Cast<i::JSReceiver>(obj),
7027  isolate_);
7028  if (RequiresEmbedderSupportToFreeze(obj_type)) {
7029  auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(receiver);
7030 
7031  // External objects don't have slots but still need to be processed by
7032  // the embedder.
7033  if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSExternalObject(obj_type) ||
7034  js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount() > 0) {
7035  if (!delegate_) {
7036  DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7037  error_ =
7038  ErrorInfo{i::MessageTemplate::kCannotDeepFreezeObject,
7039  i::direct_handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate_)};
7040  return false;
7041  }
7042 
7043  // Handle embedder specific types and any v8 children it wants to
7044  // freeze.
7045  if (!FreezeEmbedderObjectAndVisitChildren(js_obj)) {
7046  return false;
7047  }
7048  } else {
7049  DCHECK_EQ(js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount(), 0);
7050  }
7051  } else {
7052  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
7053  i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(obj_type),
7054  i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*receiver)->GetEmbedderFieldCount() == 0);
7055  if (!IsJSReceiverSafeToFreeze(obj_type)) {
7056  DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7057  error_ =
7058  ErrorInfo{i::MessageTemplate::kCannotDeepFreezeObject,
7059  i::direct_handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate_)};
7060  return false;
7061  }
7062  }
7063 
7064  // Save this to freeze after we are done. Freezing triggers garbage
7065  // collection which doesn't work well with this visitor pattern, so we
7066  // delay it until after.
7067  objects_to_freeze_.push_back(receiver);
7068 
7069  } else {
7070  DCHECK(!i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsAccessorPair(obj_type));
7071  DCHECK(!i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(obj_type));
7072  DCHECK(!i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type));
7073  }
7074 
7075  DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7076  i::VisitObject(isolate_, obj, this);
7077  // Iterate sets error_ on failure. We should propagate errors.
7078  return !error_.has_value();
7079  }
7080 
7081  bool InstantiateAndVisitLazyAccessorPairs() {
7082  i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> native_context =
7083  isolate_->native_context();
7084 
7085  i::DirectHandleVector<i::AccessorPair> lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze(
7086  isolate_);
7087  std::swap(lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze, lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_);
7088 
7089  for (const auto& accessor_pair : lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze) {
7090  i::AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate_, native_context, accessor_pair,
7091  i::ACCESSOR_GETTER);
7092  i::AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate_, native_context, accessor_pair,
7093  i::ACCESSOR_SETTER);
7094  VisitObject(*accessor_pair);
7095  }
7096  // Ensure no new lazy accessor pairs were discovered.
7097  CHECK_EQ(lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_.size(), 0);
7098  return true;
7099  }
7100 
7101  i::Isolate* isolate_;
7102  Context::DeepFreezeDelegate* delegate_;
7103  std::unordered_set<i::Tagged<i::Object>, i::Object::Hasher> done_list_;
7104  i::DirectHandleVector<i::JSReceiver> objects_to_freeze_;
7105  i::DirectHandleVector<i::AccessorPair> lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_;
7106  std::optional<ErrorInfo> error_;
7107 };
7108 
7109 } // namespace
7110 
7111 Maybe<void> Context::DeepFreeze(DeepFreezeDelegate* delegate) {
7112  auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7113  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
7114 
7115  // TODO(behamilton): Incorporate compatibility improvements similar to NodeJS:
7116  // https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/main/lib/internal/freeze_intrinsics.js
7117  // These need to be done before freezing.
7118 
7119  Local<Context> context = Utils::ToLocal(env);
7120  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
7121  RCCId::kAPI_Context_DeepFreeze};
7122  ObjectVisitorDeepFreezer vfreezer(i_isolate, delegate);
7123  if (!vfreezer.DeepFreeze(env)) return {};
7124  return JustVoid();
7125 }

7136 void Context::SetMicrotaskQueue(v8::MicrotaskQueue* queue) {
7137  auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7138  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
7139  Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsNativeContext(*context),
7140  "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue",
7141  "Must be called on a native context");
7142  i::HandleScopeImplementer* impl = i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer();
7143  Utils::ApiCheck(!context->microtask_queue()->IsRunningMicrotasks(),
7144  "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue",
7145  "Must not be running microtasks");
7146  Utils::ApiCheck(context->microtask_queue()->GetMicrotasksScopeDepth() == 0,
7147  "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue",
7148  "Must not have microtask scope pushed");
7149  Utils::ApiCheck(impl->EnteredContextCount() == 0,
7150  "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue()",
7151  "Cannot set Microtask Queue with an entered context");
7152  context->set_microtask_queue(i_isolate,
7153  static_cast<const i::MicrotaskQueue*>(queue));

7222 void v8::Context::SetPromiseHooks(Local<Function> init_hook,
7223  Local<Function> before_hook,
7224  Local<Function> after_hook,
7225  Local<Function> resolve_hook) {
7226 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
7227  auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7228  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
7229 
7230  auto undefined = i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
7231  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> init = undefined;
7232  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> before = undefined;
7233  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> after = undefined;
7234  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> resolve = undefined;
7235 
7236  bool has_hook = false;
7237 
7238  if (!init_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7239  init = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*init_hook);
7240  has_hook = true;
7241  }
7242  if (!before_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7243  before = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*before_hook);
7244  has_hook = true;
7245  }
7246  if (!after_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7247  after = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*after_hook);
7248  has_hook = true;
7249  }
7250  if (!resolve_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7251  resolve = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*resolve_hook);
7252  has_hook = true;
7253  }
7254 
7255  i_isolate->SetHasContextPromiseHooks(has_hook);
7256 
7257  context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_init_function(*init);
7258  context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_before_function(*before);
7259  context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_after_function(*after);
7260  context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_resolve_function(*resolve);
7261 #else // V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
7262  Utils::ApiCheck(false, "v8::Context::SetPromiseHook",
7263  "V8 was compiled without JavaScript Promise hooks");
7264 #endif // V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
7265 }

7295 namespace {
7296 i::ValueHelper::InternalRepresentationType GetSerializedDataFromFixedArray(
7297  i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::Tagged<i::FixedArray> list, size_t index) {
7298  if (index < static_cast<size_t>(list->length())) {
7299  int int_index = static_cast<int>(index);
7300  i::Tagged<i::Object> object = list->get(int_index);
7301  if (!IsTheHole(object, i_isolate)) {
7302  list->set_the_hole(i_isolate, int_index);
7303  // Shrink the list so that the last element is not the hole (unless it's
7304  // the first element, because we don't want to end up with a non-canonical
7305  // empty FixedArray).
7306  int last = list->length() - 1;
7307  while (last >= 0 && list->is_the_hole(i_isolate, last)) last--;
7308  if (last != -1) list->RightTrim(i_isolate, last + 1);
7309  return i::Handle<i::Object>(object, i_isolate).repr();
7310  }
7311  }
7312  return i::ValueHelper::kEmpty;
7313 }
7314 } // anonymous namespace

7317  size_t index) {

7319  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
7320  auto list = i::Cast<i::FixedArray>(context->serialized_objects());
7321  return GetSerializedDataFromFixedArray(i_isolate, list, index);
7322 }

7367 MaybeLocal<v8::Object> FunctionTemplate::NewRemoteInstance() {
7368  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7369  i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolateChecked();
7370  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(
7371  i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_FunctionTemplate_NewRemoteInstance);
7372  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
7373  i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> constructor =
7374  EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *InstanceTemplate());
7375  Utils::ApiCheck(constructor->needs_access_check(),
7376  "v8::FunctionTemplate::NewRemoteInstance",
7377  "InstanceTemplate needs to have access checks enabled");
7378  i::DirectHandle<i::AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info(
7379  i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo()),
7380  i_isolate);
7381  Utils::ApiCheck(
7382  access_check_info->named_interceptor() != i::Tagged<i::Object>(),
7383  "v8::FunctionTemplate::NewRemoteInstance",
7384  "InstanceTemplate needs to have access check handlers");
7385  i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> object;
7386  if (!i::ApiNatives::InstantiateRemoteObject(
7387  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*InstanceTemplate()))
7388  .ToHandle(&object)) {
7389  return {};
7390  }
7391  return Utils::ToLocal(scope.CloseAndEscape(object));
7392 }
7393 
7394 bool FunctionTemplate::HasInstance(v8::Local<v8::Value> value) {
7395  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7396  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
7397  if (i::IsJSObject(*obj) && self->IsTemplateFor(i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj))) {
7398  return true;
7399  }
7400  if (i::IsJSGlobalProxy(*obj)) {
7401  // If it's a global proxy, then test with the global object. Note that the
7402  // inner global object may not necessarily be a JSGlobalObject.
7403  auto jsobj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj);
7404  i::PrototypeIterator iter(i::Isolate::Current(), jsobj->map());
7405  // The global proxy should always have a prototype, as it is a bug to call
7406  // this on a detached JSGlobalProxy.
7407  DCHECK(!iter.IsAtEnd());
7408  return self->IsTemplateFor(iter.GetCurrent<i::JSObject>());
7409  }
7410  return false;
7411 }
7412 
7413 bool FunctionTemplate::IsLeafTemplateForApiObject(
7414  v8::Local<v8::Value> value) const {
7415  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7416  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7417  i::Tagged<i::Object> object = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
7418  return self->IsLeafTemplateForApiObject(object);
7419 }

7434 Local<External> v8::External::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, void* value) {
7435  static_assert(sizeof(value) == sizeof(i::Address));
7436  // Nullptr is not allowed here because serialization/deserialization of
7437  // nullptr external api references is not possible as nullptr is used as an
7438  // external_references table terminator, see v8::SnapshotCreator()
7439  // constructors.

7442  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_External_New);
7443  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7444  i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> external =
7445  i_isolate->factory()->NewExternal(value);
7446  return Utils::ExternalToLocal(external);
7447 }

7479 inline int StringLength(const char* string) {
7480  size_t len = strlen(string);
7481  CHECK_GE(i::kMaxInt, len);
7482  return static_cast<int>(len);
7483 }

7486  return StringLength(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(string));
7487 }
7488 
7489 inline int StringLength(const uint16_t* string) {
7490  size_t length = 0;
7491  while (string[length] != '\0') length++;
7492  CHECK_GE(i::kMaxInt, length);
7493  return static_cast<int>(length);
7494 }

7530 // TODO(dcarney): throw a context free exception.
7531 #define NEW_STRING(v8_isolate, class_name, function_name, Char, data, type, \
7532  length) \
7533  MaybeLocal<String> result; \
7534  if (length == 0) { \
7535  result = String::Empty(v8_isolate); \
7536  } else if (length > 0 && \
7537  static_cast<uint32_t>(length) > i::String::kMaxLength) { \
7538  result = MaybeLocal<String>(); \
7539  } else { \
7540  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(v8_isolate); \
7541  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate); \
7542  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope( \
7543  i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_##class_name##_##function_name); \
7544  if (length < 0) length = StringLength(data); \
7545  i::DirectHandle<i::String> handle_result = \
7546  NewString(i_isolate->factory(), type, \
7547  base::Vector<const Char>(data, length)) \
7548  .ToHandleChecked(); \
7549  result = Utils::ToLocal(handle_result); \
7550  }
7551 
7552 Local<String> String::NewFromUtf8Literal(Isolate* v8_isolate,
7553  const char* literal,
7554  NewStringType type, int length) {
7555  DCHECK_LE(length, i::String::kMaxLength);
7556  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7557  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7558  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
7559  RCCId::kAPI_String_NewFromUtf8Literal);
7560  i::DirectHandle<i::String> handle_result =
7561  NewString(i_isolate->factory(), type,
7562  base::Vector<const char>(literal, length))
7563  .ToHandleChecked();
7564  return Utils::ToLocal(handle_result);
7565 }

7567 MaybeLocal<String> String::NewFromUtf8(Isolate* v8_isolate, const char* data,
7568  NewStringType type, int length) {
7569  NEW_STRING(v8_isolate, String, NewFromUtf8, char, data, type, length);
7570  return result;
7571 }

7573 MaybeLocal<String> String::NewFromOneByte(Isolate* v8_isolate,

7587 Local<String> v8::String::Concat(Isolate* v8_isolate, Local<String> left,
7588  Local<String> right) {
7589  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7590  auto left_string = Utils::OpenHandle(*left);
7591  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7592  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_String_Concat);
7593  auto right_string = Utils::OpenHandle(*right);
7594  // If we are steering towards a range error, do not wait for the error to be
7595  // thrown, and return the null handle instead.
7596  if (left_string->length() + right_string->length() > i::String::kMaxLength) {
7597  return {};
7598  }
7599  i::DirectHandle<i::String> result =
7600  i_isolate->factory()
7601  ->NewConsString(left_string, right_string)
7602  .ToHandleChecked();
7603  return Utils::ToLocal(result);
7604 }

7606 MaybeLocal<String> v8::String::NewExternalTwoByte(
7607  Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::String::ExternalStringResource* resource) {
7608  CHECK(resource && resource->data());
7609  // TODO(dcarney): throw a context free exception.
7610  if (resource->length() > static_cast<size_t>(i::String::kMaxLength)) {
7611  return {};
7612  }
7613  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7614  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7615  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
7616  RCCId::kAPI_String_NewExternalTwoByte);
7617  if (resource->length() > 0) {
7618  i::DirectHandle<i::String> string =
7619  i_isolate->factory()
7620  ->NewExternalStringFromTwoByte(resource)
7621  .ToHandleChecked();
7622  return Utils::ToLocal(string);
7623  } else {
7624  // The resource isn't going to be used, free it immediately.
7625  resource->Unaccount(v8_isolate);
7626  resource->Dispose();
7627  return Utils::ToLocal(i_isolate->factory()->empty_string());
7628  }
7629 }

7631 MaybeLocal<String> v8::String::NewExternalOneByte(
7632  Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* resource) {
7633  CHECK_NOT_NULL(resource);
7634  // TODO(dcarney): throw a context free exception.
7635  if (resource->length() > static_cast<size_t>(i::String::kMaxLength)) {
7636  return {};
7637  }
7638  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7639  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7640  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
7641  RCCId::kAPI_String_NewExternalOneByte);
7642  if (resource->length() == 0) {
7643  // The resource isn't going to be used, free it immediately.
7644  resource->Unaccount(v8_isolate);
7645  resource->Dispose();
7646  return Utils::ToLocal(i_isolate->factory()->empty_string());
7647  }
7648  CHECK_NOT_NULL(resource->data());
7649  i::DirectHandle<i::String> string =
7650  i_isolate->factory()
7651  ->NewExternalStringFromOneByte(resource)
7652  .ToHandleChecked();
7653  return Utils::ToLocal(string);
7654 }

7656 bool v8::String::MakeExternal(v8::String::ExternalStringResource* resource) {

7658  return MakeExternal(isolate, resource);

7660 
7661 bool v8::String::MakeExternal(Isolate* isolate,
7662  v8::String::ExternalStringResource* resource) {
7663  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7664 
7665  i::Tagged<i::String> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7666 
7667  if (i::IsThinString(obj)) {
7668  obj = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(obj)->actual();
7669  }
7670 
7671  if (!obj->SupportsExternalization(Encoding::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING)) {
7672  return false;
7673  }
7674 
7675  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
7676  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7677 
7678  CHECK(resource && resource->data());
7679 
7680  bool result = obj->MakeExternal(i_isolate, resource);
7681  DCHECK_IMPLIES(result, HasExternalStringResource(obj));
7682  return result;
7683 }
