7743 // TODO(v8:7569): This is a workaround for the Handle vs MaybeHandle difference
7744 // in the return types of the different Add functions:
7745 // OrderedNameDictionary::Add returns MaybeHandle, NameDictionary::Add returns
7746 // Handle.
7747 template <typename T>
7748 i::DirectHandle<T> ToHandle(i::Handle<T> h) {
7749  return h;
7750 }
7751 template <typename T>
7752 i::DirectHandle<T> ToHandle(i::MaybeHandle<T> h) {
7753  return h.ToHandleChecked();
7754 }
7755 
7756 template <typename T>
7757 i::DirectHandle<T> ToHandle(i::DirectHandle<T> h) {
7758  return h;
7759 }
7760 template <typename T>
7761 i::DirectHandle<T> ToHandle(i::MaybeDirectHandle<T> h) {
7762  return h.ToHandleChecked();
7763 }
7764 
7765 template <typename Dictionary>
7766 void AddPropertiesAndElementsToObject(
7767  i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::DirectHandle<Dictionary>& properties,
7768  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArrayBase>& elements, Local<Name>* names,
7769  Local<Value>* values, size_t length) {
7770  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
7771  auto name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*names[i]);
7772  auto value = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*values[i]);
7773 
7774  // See if the {name} is a valid array index, in which case we need to
7775  // add the {name}/{value} pair to the {elements}, otherwise they end
7776  // up in the {properties} backing store.
7777  uint32_t index;
7778  if (name->AsArrayIndex(&index)) {
7779  // If this is the first element, allocate a proper
7780  // dictionary elements backing store for {elements}.
7781  if (!IsNumberDictionary(*elements)) {
7782  elements =
7783  i::NumberDictionary::New(i_isolate, static_cast<int>(length));
7784  }
7785  elements = i::NumberDictionary::Set(
7786  i_isolate, i::Cast<i::NumberDictionary>(elements), index, value);
7787  } else {
7788  // Internalize the {name} first.
7789  name = i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name);
7790  i::InternalIndex const entry = properties->FindEntry(i_isolate, name);
7791  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
7792  // Add the {name}/{value} pair as a new entry.
7793  properties = ToHandle(Dictionary::Add(
7794  i_isolate, properties, name, value, i::PropertyDetails::Empty()));
7795  } else {
7796  // Overwrite the {entry} with the {value}.
7797  properties->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
7798  }
7799  }
7800  }
7801 }
7802 
7803 } // namespace
7804 
7805 Local<v8::Object> v8::Object::New(Isolate* v8_isolate,
7806  Local<Value> prototype_or_null,
7807  Local<Name>* names, Local<Value>* values,
7808  size_t length) {
7809  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7810  i::DirectHandle<i::JSPrototype> proto;
7811  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
7812  i::TryCast(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*prototype_or_null), &proto),
7813  "v8::Object::New", "prototype must be null or object")) {
7814  return {};
7815  }
7816  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_Object_New);
7817  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
7818 
7819  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArrayBase> elements =
7820  i_isolate->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
7821 
7822  // We assume that this API is mostly used to create objects with named
7823  // properties, and so we default to creating a properties backing store
7824  // large enough to hold all of them, while we start with no elements
7825  // (see http://bit.ly/v8-fast-object-create-cpp for the motivation).
7826  if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
7827  i::DirectHandle<i::SwissNameDictionary> properties =
7828  i_isolate->factory()->NewSwissNameDictionary(static_cast<int>(length));
7829  AddPropertiesAndElementsToObject(i_isolate, properties, elements, names,
7830  values, length);
7831  i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> obj =
7832  i_isolate->factory()->NewSlowJSObjectWithPropertiesAndElements(
7833  proto, properties, elements);
7834  return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
7835  } else {
7836  i::DirectHandle<i::NameDictionary> properties =
7837  i::NameDictionary::New(i_isolate, static_cast<int>(length));
7838  AddPropertiesAndElementsToObject(i_isolate, properties, elements, names,
7839  values, length);
7840  i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> obj =
7841  i_isolate->factory()->NewSlowJSObjectWithPropertiesAndElements(
7842  proto, properties, elements);
7843  return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
7844  }
7845 }

8066 MaybeLocal<v8::Object> v8::RegExp::Exec(Local<Context> context,
8067  Local<v8::String> subject) {
8068  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_RegExp_Exec};
8069 
8070  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
8071  auto regexp = Utils::OpenHandle(this);
8072  auto subject_string = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*subject);
8073 
8074  // TODO(jgruber): RegExpUtils::RegExpExec was not written with efficiency in
8075  // mind. It fetches the 'exec' property and then calls it through JSEntry.
8076  // Unfortunately, this is currently the only full implementation of
8077  // RegExp.prototype.exec available in C++.
8078  i::DirectHandle<i::JSAny> result;
8079  if (!i::RegExpUtils::RegExpExec(i_isolate, regexp, subject_string,
8080  i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value())
8081  .ToHandle(&result)) {
8082  return {};
8083  }
8084  // RegExp::Exec is documented to return Null on failure, but the return type
8085  // is `MaybeLocal<Object>` which cannot legally hold `Null`, thus the unsafe
8086  // `Utils::Convert<Object>`.
8087  // TODO(jgruber): Fix this.
8088  return api_scope.Escape(Utils::Convert<i::JSAny, Object>(result));
8089 }

8091 Local<v8::Array> v8::Array::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, int length) {
8092  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8093  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_Array_New);
8094  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
8095  int real_length = length > 0 ? length : 0;
8096  i::DirectHandle<i::JSArray> obj =
8097  i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArray(real_length);
8098  i::DirectHandle<i::Number> length_obj =
8099  i_isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromInt(real_length);
8100  obj->set_length(*length_obj);
8101  return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
8102 }
8103 
8104 Local<v8::Array> v8::Array::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, Local<Value>* elements,
8105  size_t length) {
8106  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8107  i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8108  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_Array_New);
8109  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
8110  int len = static_cast<int>(length);
8111 
8112  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> result = factory->NewFixedArray(len);
8113  for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
8114  auto element = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*elements[i]);
8115  result->set(i, *element);
8116  }
8117 
8118  return Utils::ToLocal(
8119  factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(result, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS, len));
8120 }
8121 
8122 // static
8123 MaybeLocal<v8::Array> v8::Array::New(
8124  Local<Context> context, size_t length,
8125  std::function<MaybeLocal<v8::Value>()> next_value_callback) {
8126  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_Array_New};
8127  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
8128  i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8129  const int len = static_cast<int>(length);
8130  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> backing = factory->NewFixedArray(len);
8131  v8::Local<v8::Value> value;
8132  for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
8133  MaybeLocal<v8::Value> maybe_value = next_value_callback();
8134  // The embedder may signal to abort creation on exception via an empty
8135  // local.
8136  if (!maybe_value.ToLocal(&value)) {
8137  CHECK(i_isolate->has_exception());
8138  return {};
8139  }
8140  backing->set(i, *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value));
8141  }
8142  return api_scope.Escape(Utils::ToLocal(
8143  factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(backing, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS, len)));
8144 }

8152 }

8160 namespace internal {
8161 
8162 bool CanUseFastIteration(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> array) {
8163  if (IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(array->map())) return false;
8164  if (array->GetElementsAccessor()->HasAccessors(*array)) return false;
8165  if (!JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *array)) return false;
8166  return true;
8167 }
8168 
8169 enum class FastIterateResult {
8170  kException = static_cast<int>(v8::Array::CallbackResult::kException),
8171  kBreak = static_cast<int>(v8::Array::CallbackResult::kBreak),
8172  kSlowPath,
8173  kFinished,
8174 };
8175 
8176 FastIterateResult FastIterateArray(DirectHandle<JSArray> array,
8177  Isolate* isolate,
8178  v8::Array::IterationCallback callback,
8179  void* callback_data) {
8180  // Instead of relying on callers to check condition, this function returns
8181  // {kSlowPath} for situations it can't handle.
8182  // Most code paths below don't allocate, and rely on {callback} not allocating
8183  // either, but this isn't enforced with {DisallowHeapAllocation} to allow
8184  // embedders to allocate error objects before terminating the iteration.
8185  // Since {callback} must not allocate anyway, we can get away with fake
8186  // handles, reducing per-element overhead.
8187  if (!CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array)) return FastIterateResult::kSlowPath;
8188  using Result = v8::Array::CallbackResult;
8189  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
8190  uint32_t length = GetLength(*array);
8191  if (length == 0) return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8192  switch (array->GetElementsKind()) {
8193  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
8194  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
8195  case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
8196  case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
8197  case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS: {
8198  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(array->elements());
8199  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8200  Tagged<Object> element = elements->get(static_cast<int>(i));
8201  // TODO(13270): When we switch to CSS, we can pass {element} to
8202  // the callback directly, without {fake_handle}.
8203  IndirectHandle<Object> fake_handle(
8204  reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&element));
8205  Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(fake_handle), callback_data);
8206  if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8207  return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8208  }
8209  DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8210  }
8211  return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8212  }
8213  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
8214  case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
8215  case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
8216  case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
8217  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS: {
8218  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(array->elements());
8219  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8220  Tagged<Object> element = elements->get(static_cast<int>(i));
8221  // TODO(13270): When we switch to CSS, we can pass {element} to
8222  // the callback directly, without {fake_handle}.
8223  auto fake_handle =
8224  IsTheHole(element)
8225  ? isolate->factory()->undefined_value()
8226  : IndirectHandle<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&element));
8227  Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(fake_handle), callback_data);
8228  if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8229  return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8230  }
8231  DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8232  }
8233  return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8234  }
8235  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
8236  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
8237  DCHECK_NE(length, 0); // Cast to FixedDoubleArray would be invalid.
8238  DirectHandle<FixedDoubleArray> elements(
8239  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(array->elements()), isolate);
8240  FOR_WITH_HANDLE_SCOPE(isolate, uint32_t, i = 0, i, i < length, i++, {
8241  DirectHandle<Object> value;
8242  if (elements->is_the_hole(i)) {
8243  value = Handle<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
8244 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
8245  } else if (elements->is_undefined(i)) {
8246  value = Handle<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
8247 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
8248  } else {
8249  value = isolate->factory()->NewNumber(elements->get_scalar(i));
8250  }
8251  Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(value), callback_data);
8252  if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8253  return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8254  }
8255  DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8256  });
8257  return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8258  }
8259  case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS: {
8260  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
8261  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dict = array->element_dictionary();
8262  struct Entry {
8263  uint32_t index;
8264  InternalIndex entry;
8265  };
8266  std::vector<Entry> sorted;
8267  sorted.reserve(dict->NumberOfElements());
8268  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
8269  for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
8270  Tagged<Object> key = dict->KeyAt(isolate, i);
8271  if (!dict->IsKey(roots, key)) continue;
8272  uint32_t index =
8273  static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(key)));
8274  sorted.push_back({index, i});
8275  }
8276  std::sort(
8277  sorted.begin(), sorted.end(),
8278  [](const Entry& a, const Entry& b) { return a.index < b.index; });
8279  for (const Entry& entry : sorted) {
8280  Tagged<Object> value = dict->ValueAt(entry.entry);
8281  // TODO(13270): When we switch to CSS, we can pass {element} to
8282  // the callback directly, without {fake_handle}.
8283  IndirectHandle<Object> fake_handle(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&value));
8284  Result result =
8285  callback(entry.index, Utils::ToLocal(fake_handle), callback_data);
8286  if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8287  return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8288  }
8289  SLOW_DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8290  }
8291  return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8292  }
8293  case NO_ELEMENTS:
8294  return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8295  case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
8296  case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
8297  // Probably not worth implementing. Take the slow path.
8298  return FastIterateResult::kSlowPath;
8299  case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
8300  case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
8301  case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
8302  case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
8303 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
8304  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
8305  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
8306 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
8307  // These are never used by v8::Array instances.
8308  UNREACHABLE();
8309  }
8310  // The input value of the switch is untrusted, so even if it's exhaustive, it
8311  // can skip all cases and end up here, triggering UB since there's no return.
8312  SBXCHECK(false);
8313 }
8314 
8315 } // namespace internal
8316 
8317 Maybe<void> v8::Array::Iterate(Local<Context> context,
8318  v8::Array::IterationCallback callback,
8319  void* callback_data) {
8320  auto array = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8321  i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
8322  i::FastIterateResult fast_result =
8323  i::FastIterateArray(array, isolate, callback, callback_data);
8324  if (fast_result == i::FastIterateResult::kException) return {};
8325  // Early breaks and completed iteration both return successfully.
8326  if (fast_result != i::FastIterateResult::kSlowPath) return JustVoid();
8327 
8328  // Slow path: retrieving elements could have side effects.
8329  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{isolate, context, RCCId::kAPI_Array_Iterate};
8330  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < i::GetLength(*array); ++i) {
8331  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> element;
8332  if (!i::JSReceiver::GetElement(isolate, array, i).ToHandle(&element)) {
8333  return {};
8334  }
8335  using Result = v8::Array::CallbackResult;
8336  Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(element), callback_data);
8337  if (result == Result::kException) return {};
8338  if (result == Result::kBreak) return JustVoid();
8339  }
8340  return JustVoid();
8341 }
8342 
8343 v8::TypecheckWitness::TypecheckWitness(Isolate* isolate)
8344 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
8345  // An empty local suffices.
8346  : cached_map_()
8347 #else
8348  // We need to reserve a handle that we can patch later.
8349  // We initialize it with something that cannot compare equal to any map.
8350  : cached_map_(v8::Number::New(isolate, 1))
8351 #endif
8352 {
8353 }
8354 
8355 void v8::TypecheckWitness::Update(Local<Value> baseline) {
8356  i::Tagged<i::Object> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*baseline);
8357 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
8358  if (IsSmi(obj)) {
8359  cached_map_ = Local<Data>();
8360  } else {
8361  i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> map = i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(obj)->map();
8362  cached_map_ = Local<Data>::FromAddress(map->ptr());
8363  }
8364 #else
8365  i::Tagged<i::Object> map = i::Smi::zero();
8366  if (!IsSmi(obj)) map = i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(obj)->map();
8367  // Design overview: in the {TypecheckWitness} constructor, we create
8368  // a single handle for the witness value. Whenever {Update} is called, we
8369  // make this handle point at the fresh baseline/witness; the intention is
8370  // to allow having short-lived HandleScopes (e.g. in {FastIterateArray}
8371  // above) while a {TypecheckWitness} is alive: it therefore cannot hold
8372  // on to one of the short-lived handles.
8373  // Calling {OpenIndirectHandle} on the {cached_map_} only serves to
8374  // "reinterpret_cast" it to an {i::IndirectHandle} on which we can call
8375  // {PatchValue}.
8376  auto cache = Utils::OpenIndirectHandle(*cached_map_);
8377  cache.PatchValue(map);
8378 #endif
8379 }
8380 
8381 Local<v8::Map> v8::Map::New(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
8382  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8383  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_Map_New);

8450 namespace {
8451 
8452 enum class MapAsArrayKind {
8453  kEntries = i::JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE,
8454  kKeys = i::JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE,
8455  kValues = i::JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE
8456 };
8457 
8458 enum class SetAsArrayKind {
8459  kEntries = i::JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE,
8460  kValues = i::JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE
8461 };
8462 
8463 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArray> MapAsArray(i::Isolate* i_isolate,
8464  i::Tagged<i::Object> table_obj,
8465  int offset, MapAsArrayKind kind) {
8466  i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8467  i::DirectHandle<i::OrderedHashMap> table(
8468  i::Cast<i::OrderedHashMap>(table_obj), i_isolate);
8469  const bool collect_keys =
8470  kind == MapAsArrayKind::kEntries || kind == MapAsArrayKind::kKeys;
8471  const bool collect_values =
8472  kind == MapAsArrayKind::kEntries || kind == MapAsArrayKind::kValues;
8473  int capacity = table->UsedCapacity();
8474  int max_length =
8475  (capacity - offset) * ((collect_keys && collect_values) ? 2 : 1);
8476  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> result = factory->NewFixedArray(max_length);
8477  int result_index = 0;
8478  {
8479  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
8480  i::Tagged<i::Hole> hash_table_hole =
8481  i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).hash_table_hole_value();
8482  for (int i = offset; i < capacity; ++i) {
8483  i::InternalIndex entry(i);
8484  i::Tagged<i::Object> key = table->KeyAt(entry);
8485  if (key == hash_table_hole) continue;
8486  if (collect_keys) result->set(result_index++, key);
8487  if (collect_values) result->set(result_index++, table->ValueAt(entry));
8488  }
8489  }
8490  DCHECK_GE(max_length, result_index);
8491  if (result_index == 0) return factory->NewJSArray(0);
8492  result->RightTrim(i_isolate, result_index);
8493  return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(result, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS,
8494  result_index);
8495 }
8496 
8497 } // namespace
8498

8503  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
8504  return Utils::ToLocal(
8505  MapAsArray(i_isolate, obj->table(), 0, MapAsArrayKind::kEntries));
8506 }

8566 namespace {
8567 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArray> SetAsArray(i::Isolate* i_isolate,
8568  i::Tagged<i::Object> table_obj,
8569  int offset, SetAsArrayKind kind) {
8570  i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8571  i::DirectHandle<i::OrderedHashSet> table(
8572  i::Cast<i::OrderedHashSet>(table_obj), i_isolate);
8573  // Elements skipped by |offset| may already be deleted.
8574  int capacity = table->UsedCapacity();
8575  const bool collect_key_values = kind == SetAsArrayKind::kEntries;
8576  int max_length = (capacity - offset) * (collect_key_values ? 2 : 1);
8577  if (max_length == 0) return factory->NewJSArray(0);
8578  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> result = factory->NewFixedArray(max_length);
8579  int result_index = 0;
8580  {
8581  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
8582  i::Tagged<i::Hole> hash_table_hole =
8583  i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).hash_table_hole_value();
8584  for (int i = offset; i < capacity; ++i) {
8585  i::InternalIndex entry(i);
8586  i::Tagged<i::Object> key = table->KeyAt(entry);
8587  if (key == hash_table_hole) continue;
8588  result->set(result_index++, key);
8589  if (collect_key_values) result->set(result_index++, key);
8590  }
8591  }
8592  DCHECK_GE(max_length, result_index);
8593  if (result_index == 0) return factory->NewJSArray(0);
8594  result->RightTrim(i_isolate, result_index);
8595  return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(result, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS,
8596  result_index);
8597 }
8598 } // namespace
8599

8609 MaybeLocal<Promise::Resolver> Promise::Resolver::New(Local<Context> context) {

8627 Maybe<bool> Promise::Resolver::Resolve(Local<Context> context,
8628  Local<Value> value) {
8629  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
8630  EnterV8Scope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
8631  RCCId::kAPI_Promise_Resolver_Resolve};

8634

8636  return Just(true);

8638

8640  .is_null()) {
8641  return {};
8642  }
8643  return Just(true);
8644 }

8665 MaybeLocal<Promise> Promise::Catch(Local<Context> context,
8666  Local<Function> handler) {
8667  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_Promise_Catch};
8668  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
8669  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8670  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> args[] = {i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
8671  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*handler)};
8672  // Do not call the built-in Promise.prototype.catch!
8673  // v8::Promise should not call out to a monkeypatched Promise.prototype.then
8674  // as the implementation of Promise.prototype.catch does.
8675  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(
8676  MaybeLocal<Promise>::Cast(Utils::ToMaybeLocal(i::Execution::CallBuiltin(
8677  i_isolate, i_isolate->promise_then(), self, base::VectorOf(args)))));
8678 }

8761 MaybeLocal<Proxy> Proxy::New(Local<Context> context, Local<Object> local_target,
8762  Local<Object> local_handler) {
8763  PrepareForExecutionScope api_scope{context, RCCId::kAPI_Proxy_New};
8764  i::Isolate* i_isolate = api_scope.i_isolate();
8765  auto target = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*local_target);
8766  auto handler = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*local_handler);
8767  // The API doesn't distinguish revocable proxies, so we must assume that all
8768  // objects created through it are revocable.
8769  bool api_proxies_assumed_revocable = true;
8770  return api_scope.EscapeMaybe(i::JSProxy::New(i_isolate, target, handler,
8771  api_proxies_assumed_revocable));

8782 OwnedBuffer CompiledWasmModule::Serialize() {
8783 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8784  TRACE_EVENT0("v8.wasm", "wasm.SerializeModule");
8785  i::wasm::WasmSerializer wasm_serializer(native_module_.get());
8786  size_t buffer_size = wasm_serializer.GetSerializedNativeModuleSize();
8787  std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> buffer(new uint8_t[buffer_size]);
8788  if (!wasm_serializer.SerializeNativeModule({buffer.get(), buffer_size})) {
8789  return {};
8790  }
8791  return {std::move(buffer), buffer_size};
8792 #else
8793  UNREACHABLE();
8794 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8795 }

8816 CompiledWasmModule WasmModuleObject::GetCompiledModule() {

8830 MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject> WasmModuleObject::FromCompiledModule(
8831  Isolate* v8_isolate, const CompiledWasmModule& compiled_module) {
8832 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8833  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8834  i::DirectHandle<i::WasmModuleObject> module_object =
8835  i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->ImportNativeModule(

8843 
8844 MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject> WasmModuleObject::Compile(
8845  Isolate* v8_isolate, MemorySpan<const uint8_t> wire_bytes) {
8846 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8847  base::OwnedVector<const uint8_t> bytes = base::OwnedCopyOf(wire_bytes);
8848  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8849  // We don't check for `IsWasmCodegenAllowed` here, because this function is
8850  // used for ESM integration, which in terms of security is equivalent to
8851  // <script> tags rather than to {eval}.
8852  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::WasmModuleObject> maybe_compiled;
8853  {
8854  i::wasm::ErrorThrower thrower(i_isolate, "WasmModuleObject::Compile()");
8855  auto enabled_features =
8856  i::wasm::WasmEnabledFeatures::FromIsolate(i_isolate);
8857  // TODO(14179): Provide an API method that supports compile options.
8858  maybe_compiled = i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->SyncCompile(
8859  i_isolate, enabled_features, i::wasm::CompileTimeImports{}, &thrower,
8860  std::move(bytes));
8861  }
8862  CHECK_EQ(maybe_compiled.is_null(), i_isolate->has_exception());
8863  if (maybe_compiled.is_null()) return {};
8864  return Utils::ToLocal(maybe_compiled.ToHandleChecked());
8865 #else
8866  Utils::ApiCheck(false, "WasmModuleObject::Compile",
8867  "WebAssembly support is not enabled");
8868  UNREACHABLE();
8869 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8870 }
8871 
8872 // static
8873 Local<WasmMemoryMapDescriptor> WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::New(
8874  v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::WasmFileDescriptor fd) {

8924 
8925 Maybe<bool> v8::ArrayBuffer::Detach(v8::Local<v8::Value> key) {
8926  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8927  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
8928  Utils::ApiCheck(obj->is_detachable(), "v8::ArrayBuffer::Detach",
8929  "Only detachable ArrayBuffers can be detached");
8930  Local<Context> context =
8931  reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate)->GetCurrentContext();
8932  // TODO(verwaest): Remove this case after forcing the embedder to enter the
8933  // context.
8934  if (context.IsEmpty()) {
8935  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
8936  if (key.IsEmpty()) {
8937  i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj).Check();
8938  } else {
8939  auto i_key = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
8940  constexpr bool kForceForWasmMemory = false;
8941  i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj, kForceForWasmMemory, i_key).Check();
8942  }
8943  return Just(true);
8944  }
8945  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
8946  RCCId::kAPI_ArrayBuffer_Detach};
8947  if (key.IsEmpty()) return i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj);
8948  auto i_key = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
8949  constexpr bool kForceForWasmMemory = false;
8950  return i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj, kForceForWasmMemory, i_key);
8951 }
8952 
8953 void v8::ArrayBuffer::Detach() { Detach(Local<Value>()).Check(); }

8957  auto i_key = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
8958  obj->set_detach_key(*i_key);

8969 namespace {
8970 i::InitializedFlag GetInitializedFlag(
8971  BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
8972  switch (initialization_mode) {
8973  case BackingStoreInitializationMode::kUninitialized:
8974  return i::InitializedFlag::kUninitialized;
8975  case BackingStoreInitializationMode::kZeroInitialized:
8976  return i::InitializedFlag::kZeroInitialized;
8977  }
8978  UNREACHABLE();
8979 }
8980 } // namespace
8981 
8982 MaybeLocal<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBuffer::MaybeNew(
8983  Isolate* isolate, size_t byte_length,
8984  BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
8985  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
8986  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
8987  RCCId::kAPI_ArrayBuffer_MaybeNew);
8988  size_t max = i_isolate->array_buffer_allocator()->MaxAllocationSize();
8989  DCHECK(max <= ArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
8990  if (byte_length > max) return {};
8991  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
8992  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> result =
8993  i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
8994  byte_length, GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
8995 
8996  i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer;
8997  if (!result.ToHandle(&array_buffer)) return {};
8998 
8999  return Utils::ToLocal(array_buffer);
9000 }
9001 
9002 Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBuffer::New(
9003  Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9004  BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9005  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9006  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_ArrayBuffer_New);
9007  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9008  i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> result =
9009  i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
9010  byte_length, GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9011 
9012  i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer;
9013  if (!result.ToHandle(&array_buffer)) {
9014  i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, "v8::ArrayBuffer::New");
9015  }
9016 
9017  return Utils::ToLocal(array_buffer);
9018 }
9019 
9020 Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBuffer::New(
9021  Isolate* v8_isolate, std::shared_ptr<BackingStore> backing_store) {
9022  CHECK_IMPLIES(backing_store->ByteLength() != 0,
9023  backing_store->Data() != nullptr);
9024  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9025  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_ArrayBuffer_New);
9026  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9027  std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStore> i_backing_store(
9028  ToInternal(std::move(backing_store)));
9029  Utils::ApiCheck(
9030  !i_backing_store->is_shared(), "v8_ArrayBuffer_New",
9031  "Cannot construct ArrayBuffer with a BackingStore of SharedArrayBuffer");
9032  i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> obj =
9033  i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayBuffer(std::move(i_backing_store));
9034  return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
9035 }
9036 
9037 std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9038  Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9039  BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode,
9040  BackingStoreOnFailureMode on_failure) {
9041  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9042  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
9043  RCCId::kAPI_ArrayBuffer_NewBackingStore);
9044  if (on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kOutOfMemory) {
9045  CHECK_LE(byte_length, i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9046  } else if (byte_length > i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength) {
9047  DCHECK(on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kReturnNull);
9048  return {};
9049  }
9050  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9051  std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9052  i::BackingStore::Allocate(i_isolate, byte_length,
9053  i::SharedFlag::kNotShared,
9054  GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9055  if (!backing_store) {
9056  if (on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kOutOfMemory) {
9057  i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate,
9058  "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore");
9059  } else {
9060  DCHECK(on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kReturnNull);
9061  return {};
9062  }
9063  }
9064  return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9065  static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9066 }

9073 VirtualAddressSpace* v8::IsolateGroup::GetSandboxAddressSpace() {
9074  i::Sandbox* sandbox = isolate_group_->sandbox();
9075  Utils::ApiCheck(sandbox->is_initialized(), "v8::V8::GetSandboxAddressSpace",
9076  "The sandbox must be initialized first");
9077  return sandbox->address_space();
9078 }
9079 #endif

9081 std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9082  void* data, size_t byte_length, v8::BackingStore::DeleterCallback deleter,
9083  void* deleter_data) {
9084  CHECK_LE(byte_length, i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9085 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
9086  Utils::ApiCheck(!data || i::Sandbox::current()->Contains(data),
9087  "v8_ArrayBuffer_NewBackingStore",
9088  "When the V8 Sandbox is enabled, ArrayBuffer backing stores "
9089  "must be allocated inside the sandbox address space. Please "
9090  "use an appropriate ArrayBuffer::Allocator to allocate these "
9091  "buffers, or disable the sandbox.");
9092 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
9093 
9094  std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9095  i::BackingStore::WrapAllocation(data, byte_length, deleter, deleter_data,
9096  i::SharedFlag::kNotShared);
9097  return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9098  static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9099 }
9100 
9101 // static
9102 std::unique_ptr<BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore(
9103  size_t byte_length, size_t max_byte_length) {
9104  Utils::ApiCheck(byte_length <= max_byte_length,
9105  "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore",
9106  "Cannot construct resizable ArrayBuffer, byte_length must be "
9107  "<= max_byte_length");
9108  Utils::ApiCheck(
9109  byte_length <= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength,
9110  "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore",
9111  "Cannot construct resizable ArrayBuffer, requested length is too big");
9112 
9113  size_t page_size, initial_pages, max_pages;
9114  if (i::JSArrayBuffer::GetResizableBackingStorePageConfiguration(
9115  nullptr, byte_length, max_byte_length, i::kDontThrow, &page_size,
9116  &initial_pages, &max_pages)
9117  .IsNothing()) {
9118  i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(nullptr,
9119  "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore");
9120  }
9121  std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9122  i::BackingStore::TryAllocateAndPartiallyCommitMemory(
9123  nullptr, byte_length, max_byte_length, page_size, initial_pages,
9124  max_pages, i::WasmMemoryFlag::kNotWasm, i::SharedFlag::kNotShared);
9125  if (!backing_store) {
9126  i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(nullptr,
9127  "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore");
9128  }
9129  return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9130  static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9131 }
9132 
9133 Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBufferView::Buffer() {
9134  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9135  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
9136  if (i::IsJSDataView(*obj)) {
9137  i::DirectHandle<i::JSDataView> data_view(i::Cast<i::JSDataView>(*obj),
9138  i_isolate);
9139  DCHECK(IsJSArrayBuffer(data_view->buffer()));
9140  return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
9141  i::Cast<i::JSArrayBuffer>(data_view->buffer()), i_isolate));
9142  } else if (i::IsJSRabGsabDataView(*obj)) {
9143  i::DirectHandle<i::JSRabGsabDataView> data_view(
9144  i::Cast<i::JSRabGsabDataView>(*obj), i_isolate);
9145  DCHECK(IsJSArrayBuffer(data_view->buffer()));
9146  return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
9147  i::Cast<i::JSArrayBuffer>(data_view->buffer()), i_isolate));
9148  } else {
9149  DCHECK(IsJSTypedArray(*obj));
9150  return Utils::ToLocal(i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(*obj)->GetBuffer(i_isolate));
9151  }
9152 }
9153 
9154 size_t v8::ArrayBufferView::CopyContents(void* dest, size_t byte_length) {
9155  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9156  size_t bytes_to_copy = std::min(byte_length, self->byte_length());
9157  if (bytes_to_copy) {
9158  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9159  const char* source;
9160  if (i::IsJSTypedArray(*self)) {
9161  i::Tagged<i::JSTypedArray> array = i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(*self);
9162  source = reinterpret_cast<char*>(array->DataPtr());
9163  } else {
9164  DCHECK(i::IsJSDataView(*self) || i::IsJSRabGsabDataView(*self));
9165  i::Tagged<i::JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView> data_view =
9166  i::Cast<i::JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView>(*self);
9167  source = reinterpret_cast<char*>(data_view->data_pointer());
9168  }
9169  memcpy(dest, source, bytes_to_copy);
9170  }
9171  return bytes_to_copy;
9172 }
9173 
9174 v8::MemorySpan<uint8_t> v8::ArrayBufferView::GetContents(
9175  v8::MemorySpan<uint8_t> storage) {
9176  internal::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9177  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9178  if (self->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds()) return {};
9179  if (internal::IsJSTypedArray(*self)) {
9180  i::Tagged<i::JSTypedArray> typed_array = i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(*self);
9181  if (typed_array->is_on_heap()) {
9182  // The provided storage does not have enough capacity for the content of
9183  // the TypedArray.
9184  size_t bytes_to_copy = self->byte_length();
9185  CHECK_LE(bytes_to_copy, storage.size());
9186  const uint8_t* source =
9187  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
9188  memcpy(reinterpret_cast<void*>(storage.data()), source, bytes_to_copy);
9189  return {storage.data(), bytes_to_copy};
9190  }
9191  // The TypedArray already has off-heap storage, just return a view on it.
9192  return {reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(typed_array->DataPtr()),
9193  typed_array->GetByteLength()};
9194  }
9195  if (i::IsJSDataView(*self)) {
9196  i::Tagged<i::JSDataView> data_view = i::Cast<i::JSDataView>(*self);
9197  return {reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data_view->data_pointer()),
9198  data_view->byte_length()};
9199  }
9200  // Other types of ArrayBufferView always have an off-heap storage.
9201  DCHECK(i::IsJSRabGsabDataView(*self));
9202  i::Tagged<i::JSRabGsabDataView> data_view =
9203  i::Cast<i::JSRabGsabDataView>(*self);
9204  return {reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data_view->data_pointer()),
9205  data_view->GetByteLength()};
9206 }
9207 
9208 bool v8::ArrayBufferView::HasBuffer() const {
9209  auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9210  if (!IsJSTypedArray(*self)) return true;
9211  auto typed_array = i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(self);
9212  return !typed_array->is_on_heap();
9213 }

9220 size_t v8::ArrayBufferView::ByteLength() {
9221  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9222  i::Tagged<i::JSArrayBufferView> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9223  if (obj->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds()) {
9224  return 0;
9225  }
9226  if (i::IsJSTypedArray(obj)) {
9227  return i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(obj)->GetByteLength();
9228  }
9229  if (i::IsJSDataView(obj)) {
9230  return i::Cast<i::JSDataView>(obj)->byte_length();
9231  }
9232  return i::Cast<i::JSRabGsabDataView>(obj)->GetByteLength();
9233 }

9359 Local<SharedArrayBuffer> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New(
9360  Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9361  BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9362  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9363  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
9364  RCCId::kAPI_SharedArrayBuffer_New);
9365  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9366 
9367  std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStore> backing_store =
9368  i::BackingStore::Allocate(i_isolate, byte_length, i::SharedFlag::kShared,
9369  GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9370 
9371  if (!backing_store) {
9372  i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New");
9373  }
9374 
9375  i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> obj =
9376  i_isolate->factory()->NewJSSharedArrayBuffer(std::move(backing_store));
9377  return Utils::ToLocalShared(obj);
9378 }

9398 
9399 Local<SharedArrayBuffer> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New(
9400  Isolate* v8_isolate, std::shared_ptr<BackingStore> backing_store) {
9401  CHECK_IMPLIES(backing_store->ByteLength() != 0,
9402  backing_store->Data() != nullptr);
9403  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9404  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate,
9405  RCCId::kAPI_SharedArrayBuffer_New);
9406  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9407  std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStore> i_backing_store(ToInternal(backing_store));
9408  Utils::ApiCheck(
9409  i_backing_store->is_shared(), "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New",
9410  "Cannot construct SharedArrayBuffer with BackingStore of ArrayBuffer");
9411  i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> obj =
9412  i_isolate->factory()->NewJSSharedArrayBuffer(std::move(i_backing_store));
9413  return Utils::ToLocalShared(obj);
9414 }
9415 
9416 std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9417  Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9418  BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode,
9419  BackingStoreOnFailureMode on_failure) {
9420  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9421  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(
9422  i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_SharedArrayBuffer_NewBackingStore);
9423  if (on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kOutOfMemory) {
9424  Utils::ApiCheck(
9425  byte_length <= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength,
9426  "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore",
9427  "Cannot construct SharedArrayBuffer, requested length is too big");
9428  } else {
9429  DCHECK(on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kReturnNull);
9430  if (byte_length > i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength) return {};
9431  }
9432  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9433  std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9434  i::BackingStore::Allocate(i_isolate, byte_length, i::SharedFlag::kShared,
9435  GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9436  if (!backing_store) {
9437  if (on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kOutOfMemory) {
9438  i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate,
9439  "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore");
9440  } else {
9441  DCHECK(on_failure == BackingStoreOnFailureMode::kReturnNull);
9442  return {};
9443  }
9444  }
9445  return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9446  static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9447 }
9448 
9449 std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9450  void* data, size_t byte_length, v8::BackingStore::DeleterCallback deleter,
9451  void* deleter_data) {
9452  CHECK_LE(byte_length, i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9453  std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9454  i::BackingStore::WrapAllocation(data, byte_length, deleter, deleter_data,
9455  i::SharedFlag::kShared);
9456  return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9457  static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9458 }

9531 Local<Number> v8::Number::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, double value) {

9611 
9612 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryImpl(
9613  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
9614  // Try to check for unreasonably large or small values from the embedder.
9615  static constexpr int64_t kMaxReasonableBytes = int64_t(1) << 60;
9616  static constexpr int64_t kMinReasonableBytes = -kMaxReasonableBytes;
9617  static_assert(kMaxReasonableBytes >= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9618  CHECK(kMinReasonableBytes <= change_in_bytes &&
9619  change_in_bytes < kMaxReasonableBytes);
9620 
9621  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9622  const uint64_t amount =
9623  i_isolate->heap()->UpdateExternalMemory(change_in_bytes);
9624 
9625  if (change_in_bytes <= 0) {
9626  return amount;
9627  }
9628 
9629  if (amount > i_isolate->heap()->external_memory_limit_for_interrupt()) {
9630  HandleExternalMemoryInterrupt();
9631  }
9632  return amount;
9633 }
9634 
9635 void Isolate::HandleExternalMemoryInterrupt() {
9636  i::Heap* heap = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap();
9637  if (heap->gc_state() != i::Heap::NOT_IN_GC) return;
9638  heap->HandleExternalMemoryInterrupt();
9639 }

9651 IsolateGroup& IsolateGroup::operator=(const IsolateGroup& other) {
9652  if (this != &other && isolate_group_ != other.isolate_group_) {
9653  if (isolate_group_) isolate_group_->Release();
9654  isolate_group_ = other.isolate_group_;
9655  if (isolate_group_) isolate_group_->Acquire();
9656  }
9657  return *this;
9658 }

9763 v8::Local<Value> Isolate::ThrowException(v8::Local<v8::Value> value) {
9764  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9765  EnterV8BasicScope api_scope(i_isolate);
9766  i_isolate->clear_internal_exception();
9767  // If we're passed an empty handle, we throw an undefined exception
9768  // to deal more gracefully with out of memory situations.
9769  if (value.IsEmpty()) {
9770  i_isolate->Throw(i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value());
9771  } else {
9772  i_isolate->Throw(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value));
9773  }
9774  return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
9775 }

9777 bool Isolate::HasPendingException() {
9778  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9779  if (i_isolate->has_exception()) {
9780  return true;
9781  }
9782  v8::TryCatch* try_catch_handler =
9783  i_isolate->thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_;
9784  return try_catch_handler && try_catch_handler->HasCaught();
9785 }

9888 void Isolate::RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting(GarbageCollectionType type) {
9889  Utils::ApiCheck(i::v8_flags.expose_gc,
9890  "v8::Isolate::RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting",
9891  "Must use --expose-gc");
9892  // The embedder must have entered the isolate (via `Isolate::Scope`) such that
9893  // the GC can get the "current" isolate from TLS.
9894  DCHECK_EQ(this, Isolate::TryGetCurrent());
9895 
9896  if (type == kMinorGarbageCollection) {
9897  reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap()->CollectGarbage(
9898  i::NEW_SPACE, i::GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting,
9899  kGCCallbackFlagForced);
9900  } else {
9901  DCHECK_EQ(kFullGarbageCollection, type);
9902  reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap()->PreciseCollectAllGarbage(
9903  i::GCFlag::kNoFlags, i::GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting,
9904  kGCCallbackFlagForced);
9905  }
9906 }
9907 
9908 void Isolate::RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting(GarbageCollectionType type,
9909  StackState stack_state) {
9910  std::optional<i::EmbedderStackStateScope> stack_scope;
9911  if (type == kFullGarbageCollection) {
9912  stack_scope.emplace(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap(),
9913  i::EmbedderStackStateOrigin::kExplicitInvocation,
9914  stack_state);
9915  }
9916  RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting(type);
9917 }

9949 Isolate::CreateParams::CreateParams() = default;
9950 
9951 Isolate::CreateParams::~CreateParams() = default;
9952 
9953 // static
9954 // This is separate so that tests can provide a different |isolate|.
9955 void Isolate::Initialize(Isolate* v8_isolate,
9956  const v8::Isolate::CreateParams& params) {
9957  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9958  TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.IsolateInitialize");
9959  if (auto allocator = params.array_buffer_allocator_shared) {
9960  CHECK(params.array_buffer_allocator == nullptr ||
9961  params.array_buffer_allocator == allocator.get());
9962  i_isolate->set_array_buffer_allocator(allocator.get());
9963  i_isolate->set_array_buffer_allocator_shared(std::move(allocator));
9964  } else {
9965  CHECK_NOT_NULL(params.array_buffer_allocator);
9966  i_isolate->set_array_buffer_allocator(params.array_buffer_allocator);
9967  }
9968  if (params.snapshot_blob != nullptr) {
9969  i_isolate->set_snapshot_blob(params.snapshot_blob);
9970  } else {
9971  i_isolate->set_snapshot_blob(i::Snapshot::DefaultSnapshotBlob());
9972  }
9973 
9974  if (params.fatal_error_callback) {
9975  v8_isolate->SetFatalErrorHandler(params.fatal_error_callback);
9976  }
9977 
9978 #if __clang__
9979 #pragma clang diagnostic push
9980 #pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
9981 #endif
9982  if (params.oom_error_callback) {
9983  v8_isolate->SetOOMErrorHandler(params.oom_error_callback);
9984  }
9985 #if __clang__
9986 #pragma clang diagnostic pop
9987 #endif
9988 
9989  if (params.counter_lookup_callback) {
9990  v8_isolate->SetCounterFunction(params.counter_lookup_callback);
9991  }
9992 
9993  if (params.create_histogram_callback) {
9994  v8_isolate->SetCreateHistogramFunction(params.create_histogram_callback);
9995  }
9996 
9997  if (params.add_histogram_sample_callback) {
9998  v8_isolate->SetAddHistogramSampleFunction(
9999  params.add_histogram_sample_callback);
10000  }
10001 
10002  i_isolate->set_api_external_references(params.external_references);
10003  i_isolate->set_allow_atomics_wait(params.allow_atomics_wait);
10004 
10005  CppHeap* cpp_heap = params.cpp_heap;
10006  if (!cpp_heap) {
10007  cpp_heap =
10008  CppHeap::Create(i::V8::GetCurrentPlatform(), CppHeapCreateParams{{}})
10009  .release();
10010  }
10011 
10012  i_isolate->heap()->ConfigureHeap(params.constraints, cpp_heap);
10013  if (params.constraints.stack_limit() != nullptr) {
10014  uintptr_t limit =
10015  reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(params.constraints.stack_limit());
10016  i_isolate->stack_guard()->SetStackLimit(limit);
10017  i_isolate->set_stack_size(base::Stack::GetStackStart() - limit);
10018  }
10019 
10020  // TODO(v8:2487): Once we got rid of Isolate::Current(), we can remove this.
10021  Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(v8_isolate);
10022  if (i_isolate->snapshot_blob() == nullptr) {
10023  FATAL(
10024  "V8 snapshot blob was not set during initialization. This can mean "
10025  "that the snapshot blob file is corrupted or missing.");
10026  }
10027  if (!i::Snapshot::Initialize(i_isolate)) {
10028  // If snapshot data was provided and we failed to deserialize it must
10029  // have been corrupted.
10030  FATAL(
10031  "Failed to deserialize the V8 snapshot blob. This can mean that the "
10032  "snapshot blob file is corrupted or missing.");
10033  }
10034 
10035  {
10036  // Set up code event handlers. Needs to be after i::Snapshot::Initialize
10037  // because that is where we add the isolate to WasmEngine.
10038  auto code_event_handler = params.code_event_handler;
10039  if (code_event_handler) {
10040  v8_isolate->SetJitCodeEventHandler(kJitCodeEventEnumExisting,
10041  code_event_handler);
10042  }
10043  }
10044 
10045  i_isolate->set_embedder_wrapper_type_index(
10046  params.embedder_wrapper_type_index);
10047  i_isolate->set_embedder_wrapper_object_index(
10048  params.embedder_wrapper_object_index);
10049 
10050  if (!i::V8::GetCurrentPlatform()
10051  ->GetForegroundTaskRunner(v8_isolate)
10052  ->NonNestableTasksEnabled()) {
10053  FATAL(
10054  "The current platform's foreground task runner does not have "
10055  "non-nestable tasks enabled. The embedder must provide one.");
10056  }
10057 }

10062 
10063 Isolate* Isolate::New(const IsolateGroup& group,

10068 }

10158 Isolate::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope(
10159  Isolate* v8_isolate,
10160  Isolate::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope::OnFailure on_failure)
10161  : v8_isolate_(v8_isolate), on_failure_(on_failure) {
10162  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
10163  switch (on_failure_) {
10164  case CRASH_ON_FAILURE:
10165  i::DisallowJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_);
10166  break;
10167  case THROW_ON_FAILURE:
10168  i::ThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_);
10169  break;
10170  case DUMP_ON_FAILURE:
10171  i::DumpOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_);
10172  break;
10173  }
10174 }
10175 
10176 Isolate::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope::~DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope() {
10177  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate_);
10178  switch (on_failure_) {
10179  case CRASH_ON_FAILURE:
10180  i::DisallowJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_);
10181  break;
10182  case THROW_ON_FAILURE:
10183  i::ThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_);
10184  break;
10185  case DUMP_ON_FAILURE:
10186  i::DumpOnJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_);
10187  break;
10188  }
10189 }

10196  i::NoThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate,

10274 void Isolate::GetHeapStatistics(HeapStatistics* heap_statistics) {
10275  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10276  i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10277 
10278  heap->FreeMainThreadLinearAllocationAreas();
10279 
10280  // The order of acquiring memory statistics is important here. We query in
10281  // this order because of concurrent allocation: 1) used memory 2) committed
10282  // physical memory 3) committed memory. Therefore the condition used <=
10283  // committed physical <= committed should hold.
10284  heap_statistics->used_global_handles_size_ = heap->UsedGlobalHandlesSize();
10285  heap_statistics->total_global_handles_size_ = heap->TotalGlobalHandlesSize();
10286  DCHECK_LE(heap_statistics->used_global_handles_size_,
10287  heap_statistics->total_global_handles_size_);
10288 
10289  heap_statistics->used_heap_size_ = heap->SizeOfObjects();
10290  heap_statistics->total_physical_size_ = heap->CommittedPhysicalMemory();
10291  heap_statistics->total_heap_size_ = heap->CommittedMemory();
10292 
10293  heap_statistics->total_available_size_ = heap->Available();
10294 
10295  // TODO(dinfuehr): Right now used <= committed physical does not hold. Fix
10296  // this and add DCHECK.
10297  DCHECK_LE(heap_statistics->used_heap_size_,
10298  heap_statistics->total_heap_size_);
10299 
10300  heap_statistics->total_heap_size_executable_ =
10301  heap->CommittedMemoryExecutable();
10302  heap_statistics->heap_size_limit_ = heap->MaxReserved();
10303  // TODO(7424): There is no public API for the {WasmEngine} yet. Once such an
10304  // API becomes available we should report the malloced memory separately. For
10305  // now we just add the values, thereby over-approximating the peak slightly.
10306  heap_statistics->malloced_memory_ =
10307  i_isolate->allocator()->GetCurrentMemoryUsage() +
10308  i_isolate->string_table()->GetCurrentMemoryUsage();
10309  // On 32-bit systems backing_store_bytes() might overflow size_t temporarily
10310  // due to concurrent array buffer sweeping.
10311  heap_statistics->external_memory_ =
10312  i_isolate->heap()->backing_store_bytes() < SIZE_MAX
10313  ? static_cast<size_t>(i_isolate->heap()->backing_store_bytes())
10314  : SIZE_MAX;
10315  heap_statistics->peak_malloced_memory_ =
10316  i_isolate->allocator()->GetMaxMemoryUsage();
10317  heap_statistics->number_of_native_contexts_ = heap->NumberOfNativeContexts();
10318  heap_statistics->number_of_detached_contexts_ =
10319  heap->NumberOfDetachedContexts();
10320  heap_statistics->does_zap_garbage_ = i::heap::ShouldZapGarbage();
10321 
10322 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10323  heap_statistics->malloced_memory_ +=
10324  i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->allocator()->GetCurrentMemoryUsage();
10325  heap_statistics->peak_malloced_memory_ +=
10326  i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->allocator()->GetMaxMemoryUsage();
10327 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10328 }
10329 
10330 size_t Isolate::NumberOfHeapSpaces() {
10331  return i::LAST_SPACE - i::FIRST_SPACE + 1;
10332 }
10333 
10334 bool Isolate::GetHeapSpaceStatistics(HeapSpaceStatistics* space_statistics,
10335  size_t index) {
10336  if (!space_statistics) return false;
10337  if (!i::Heap::IsValidAllocationSpace(static_cast<i::AllocationSpace>(index)))
10338  return false;
10339 
10340  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10341  i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10342 
10343  heap->FreeMainThreadLinearAllocationAreas();
10344 
10345  i::AllocationSpace allocation_space = static_cast<i::AllocationSpace>(index);
10346  space_statistics->space_name_ = i::ToString(allocation_space);
10347 
10348  if (allocation_space == i::RO_SPACE) {
10349  // RO_SPACE memory is shared across all isolates and accounted for
10350  // elsewhere.
10351  space_statistics->space_size_ = 0;
10352  space_statistics->space_used_size_ = 0;
10353  space_statistics->space_available_size_ = 0;
10354  space_statistics->physical_space_size_ = 0;
10355  } else {
10356  i::Space* space = heap->space(static_cast<int>(index));
10357  space_statistics->space_size_ = space ? space->CommittedMemory() : 0;
10358  space_statistics->space_used_size_ = space ? space->SizeOfObjects() : 0;
10359  space_statistics->space_available_size_ = space ? space->Available() : 0;
10360  space_statistics->physical_space_size_ =
10361  space ? space->CommittedPhysicalMemory() : 0;
10362  }
10363  return true;
10364 }

10369  return heap->NumberOfTrackedHeapObjectTypes();

10371 
10372 bool Isolate::GetHeapObjectStatisticsAtLastGC(
10373  HeapObjectStatistics* object_statistics, size_t type_index) {
10374  if (!object_statistics) return false;
10375  if (V8_LIKELY(!i::TracingFlags::is_gc_stats_enabled())) return false;
10376 
10377  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10378  i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10379  if (type_index >= heap->NumberOfTrackedHeapObjectTypes()) return false;
10380 
10381  const char* object_type;
10382  const char* object_sub_type;
10383  size_t object_count = heap->ObjectCountAtLastGC(type_index);
10384  size_t object_size = heap->ObjectSizeAtLastGC(type_index);
10385  if (!heap->GetObjectTypeName(type_index, &object_type, &object_sub_type)) {
10386  // There should be no objects counted when the type is unknown.
10387  DCHECK_EQ(object_count, 0U);
10388  DCHECK_EQ(object_size, 0U);
10389  return false;
10390  }
10391 
10392  object_statistics->object_type_ = object_type;
10393  object_statistics->object_sub_type_ = object_sub_type;
10394  object_statistics->object_count_ = object_count;
10395  object_statistics->object_size_ = object_size;
10396  return true;
10397 }
10398 
10399 bool Isolate::GetHeapCodeAndMetadataStatistics(
10400  HeapCodeStatistics* code_statistics) {
10401  if (!code_statistics) return false;
10402 
10403  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10404  i_isolate->heap()->CollectCodeStatistics();
10405 
10406  code_statistics->code_and_metadata_size_ =
10407  i_isolate->code_and_metadata_size();
10408  code_statistics->bytecode_and_metadata_size_ =
10409  i_isolate->bytecode_and_metadata_size();
10410  code_statistics->external_script_source_size_ =
10411  i_isolate->external_script_source_size();
10412  code_statistics->cpu_profiler_metadata_size_ =
10413  i::CpuProfiler::GetAllProfilersMemorySize(i_isolate);
10414 
10415  return true;
10416 }

10508  &handler_context))

10512 }

10589 int Isolate::ContextDisposedNotification(bool dependant_context) {
10590  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10591  if (V8_UNLIKELY(i::v8_flags.trace_context_disposal)) {
10592  i_isolate->PrintWithTimestamp("[context-disposal] Disposing %s context\n",
10593  dependant_context ? "nested" : "top-level");
10594  }
10595 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10596  if (!dependant_context) {
10597  if (!i_isolate->context().is_null()) {
10598  // We left the current context, we can abort all WebAssembly compilations
10599  // of that context.
10600  // A handle scope for the native context.
10601  i::HandleScope handle_scope(i_isolate);
10602  i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->DeleteCompileJobsOnContext(
10603  i_isolate->native_context());
10604  }
10605  }
10606 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10607  i_isolate->AbortConcurrentOptimization(i::BlockingBehavior::kDontBlock);
10608  return i_isolate->heap()->NotifyContextDisposed(dependant_context);
10609 }

10613  // ContextDisposedNotification() that still has a return parameter.
10614  START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
10615  ContextDisposedNotification(dependants == ContextDependants::kSomeDependants);
10616  END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
10617 }

10710 JSEntryStubs Isolate::GetJSEntryStubs() {
10711  JSEntryStubs entry_stubs;
10712 
10713  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10714  std::array<std::pair<i::Builtin, JSEntryStub*>, 3> stubs = {
10715  {{i::Builtin::kJSEntry, &entry_stubs.js_entry_stub},
10716  {i::Builtin::kJSConstructEntry, &entry_stubs.js_construct_entry_stub},
10717  {i::Builtin::kJSRunMicrotasksEntry,
10718  &entry_stubs.js_run_microtasks_entry_stub}}};
10719  for (auto& pair : stubs) {
10720  i::Tagged<i::Code> js_entry = i_isolate->builtins()->code(pair.first);
10721  pair.second->code.start =
10722  reinterpret_cast<const void*>(js_entry->instruction_start());
10723  pair.second->code.length_in_bytes = js_entry->instruction_size();
10724  }
10725 
10726  return entry_stubs;
10727 }
10728 
10729 size_t Isolate::CopyCodePages(size_t capacity, MemoryRange* code_pages_out) {
10730 #if !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT) && !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
10731  // Not implemented on other platforms.
10732  UNREACHABLE();
10733 #else
10734 
10735  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10736  std::vector<MemoryRange>* code_pages = i_isolate->GetCodePages();
10737 
10738  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(code_pages);
10739 
10740  // Copy as many elements into the output vector as we can. If the
10741  // caller-provided buffer is not big enough, we fill it, and the caller can
10742  // provide a bigger one next time. We do it this way because allocation is not
10743  // allowed in signal handlers.
10744  size_t limit = std::min(capacity, code_pages->size());
10745  for (size_t i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
10746  code_pages_out[i] = code_pages->at(i);
10747  }
10748  return code_pages->size();
10749 #endif
10750 }

10831 bool Isolate::AddMessageListener(MessageCallback callback, Local<Value> data) {
10832  return AddMessageListenerWithErrorLevel(callback, kMessageError, data);
10833 }
10834 
10835 bool Isolate::AddMessageListenerWithErrorLevel(MessageCallback callback,
10836  int message_levels,
10837  Local<Value> data) {
10838  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10839  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
10840  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
10841  i::DirectHandle<i::ArrayList> list =
10842  i_isolate->factory()->message_listeners();
10843  i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> listener =
10844  i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(3);
10845 
10846  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> callback_obj =
10847  FromCData<internal::kMessageListenerTag>(i_isolate, callback);
10848 
10849  listener->set(0, *callback_obj);
10850  listener->set(1, data.IsEmpty()
10851  ? i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value()
10852  : *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
10853  listener->set(2, i::Smi::FromInt(message_levels));
10854  list = i::ArrayList::Add(i_isolate, list, listener);
10855  i_isolate->heap()->SetMessageListeners(*list);
10856  return true;
10857 }
10858 
10859 void Isolate::RemoveMessageListeners(MessageCallback callback) {
10860  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10861  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
10862  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
10863  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
10864  i::Tagged<i::ArrayList> listeners = i_isolate->heap()->message_listeners();
10865  i::ReadOnlyRoots roots(i_isolate);
10866  for (int i = 0; i < listeners->length(); i++) {
10867  if (i::IsUndefined(listeners->get(i), roots)) {
10868  continue; // skip deleted ones
10869  }
10870  i::Tagged<i::FixedArray> listener =
10871  i::Cast<i::FixedArray>(listeners->get(i));
10872  v8::MessageCallback cur_callback =
10873  v8::ToCData<v8::MessageCallback, i::kMessageListenerTag>(
10874  i_isolate, listener->get(0));
10875  if (cur_callback == callback) {
10876  listeners->set(i, roots.undefined_value());
10877  }
10878  }
10879 }

10998 MicrotasksScope::MicrotasksScope(Local<Context> v8_context,
10999  MicrotasksScope::Type type)
11000  : MicrotasksScope(v8::Isolate::GetCurrent(),
11001  v8_context->GetMicrotaskQueue(), type) {}
11002 
11003 MicrotasksScope::MicrotasksScope(Isolate* v8_isolate,
11004  MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue,
11005  MicrotasksScope::Type type)
11006  : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)),
11007  microtask_queue_(microtask_queue
11008  ? static_cast<i::MicrotaskQueue*>(microtask_queue)
11009  : i_isolate_->default_microtask_queue()),
11010  run_(type == MicrotasksScope::kRunMicrotasks) {
11011  if (run_) microtask_queue_->IncrementMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11012 #ifdef DEBUG
11013  if (!run_) microtask_queue_->IncrementDebugMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11014 #endif
11015 }
11016 
11017 MicrotasksScope::~MicrotasksScope() {
11018  if (run_) {
11019  microtask_queue_->DecrementMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11020  if (MicrotasksPolicy::kScoped == microtask_queue_->microtasks_policy() &&
11021  !i_isolate_->has_exception()) {
11022  microtask_queue_->PerformCheckpoint(
11023  reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate_));
11024  DCHECK_IMPLIES(i_isolate_->has_exception(),
11025  i_isolate_->is_execution_terminating());
11026  }
11027  }
11028 #ifdef DEBUG
11029  if (!run_) microtask_queue_->DecrementDebugMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11030 #endif
11031 }
11032

11036  auto* microtask_queue = i_isolate->default_microtask_queue();
11037  microtask_queue->PerformCheckpoint(v8_isolate);
11038 }

11054 String::Utf8Value::Utf8Value(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::Local<v8::Value> obj)
11055  : str_(nullptr), length_(0) {
11056  if (obj.IsEmpty()) return;
11057  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11058  Local<Context> context = v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext();
11059  EnterV8BasicScope api_scope(i_isolate);
11060  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11061  TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
11062  Local<String> str;
11063  if (!obj->ToString(context).ToLocal(&str)) return;
11064  length_ = str->Utf8LengthV2(v8_isolate);
11065  str_ = i::NewArray<char>(length_ + 1);
11066  int flags = String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate |
11067  String::WriteFlags::kReplaceInvalidUtf8;
11068  str->WriteUtf8V2(v8_isolate, str_, length_ + 1, flags);
11069 }
11070 
11071 String::Utf8Value::~Utf8Value() { i::DeleteArray(str_); }
11072 
11073 String::Value::Value(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::Local<v8::Value> obj)
11074  : str_(nullptr), length_(0) {
11075  if (obj.IsEmpty()) return;
11076  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11077  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11078  Local<Context> context = v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext();
11079  EnterV8BasicScope api_scope(i_isolate);
11080  TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
11081  Local<String> str;
11082  if (!obj->ToString(context).ToLocal(&str)) return;
11083  length_ = str->Length();
11084  str_ = i::NewArray<uint16_t>(length_ + 1);
11085  str->WriteV2(v8_isolate, 0, length_, str_,
11086  String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate);
11087 }
11088 
11089 String::Value::~Value() { i::DeleteArray(str_); }
11090 
11091 String::ValueView::ValueView(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate,
11092  v8::Local<v8::String> str) {
11093  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11094  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11095  i::DirectHandle<i::String> i_str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*str);
11096  i::DirectHandle<i::String> i_flat_str = i::String::Flatten(i_isolate, i_str);
11097 
11098  flat_str_ = Utils::ToLocal(i_flat_str);
11099 
11100  i::DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease* no_gc =
11101  new (no_gc_debug_scope_) i::DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease();
11102  i::String::FlatContent flat_content = i_flat_str->GetFlatContent(*no_gc);
11103  DCHECK(flat_content.IsFlat());
11104  is_one_byte_ = flat_content.IsOneByte();
11105  length_ = flat_content.length();
11106  if (is_one_byte_) {
11107  data8_ = flat_content.ToOneByteVector().data();
11108  } else {
11109  data16_ = flat_content.ToUC16Vector().data();
11110  }
11111 }

11115  DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease* no_gc =
11116  reinterpret_cast<DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease*>(no_gc_debug_scope_);
11117  no_gc->~DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease();
11118 }

11120 void String::ValueView::CheckOneByte(bool is_one_byte) const {
11121  if (is_one_byte) {
11122  Utils::ApiCheck(is_one_byte_, "v8::String::ValueView::data8",
11123  "Called the one-byte accessor on a two-byte string view.");
11124  } else {
11125  Utils::ApiCheck(!is_one_byte_, "v8::String::ValueView::data16",
11126  "Called the two-byte accessor on a one-byte string view.");
11127  }
11128 }

11130 #define DEFINE_ERROR(NAME, name) \
11131  Local<Value> Exception::NAME(v8::Local<v8::String> raw_message, \
11132  v8::Local<v8::Value> raw_options) { \
11133  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current(); \
11134  ApiRuntimeCallStatsScope rcs_scope(i_isolate, RCCId::kAPI_##NAME##_New); \
11135  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate); \
11136  i::Tagged<i::Object> error; \
11137  { \
11138  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate); \
11139  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> options; \
11140  if (!raw_options.IsEmpty()) { \
11141  options = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*raw_options); \
11142  } \
11143  auto message = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*raw_message); \
11144  i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> constructor = \
11145  i_isolate->name##_function(); \
11146  error = *i_isolate->factory()->NewError(constructor, message, options); \
11147  } \
11148  return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(error, i_isolate)); \
11149  }
11150 
11151 DEFINE_ERROR(RangeError, range_error)
11152 DEFINE_ERROR(ReferenceError, reference_error)
11153 DEFINE_ERROR(SyntaxError, syntax_error)
11154 DEFINE_ERROR(TypeError, type_error)
11155 DEFINE_ERROR(WasmCompileError, wasm_compile_error)
11156 DEFINE_ERROR(WasmLinkError, wasm_link_error)
11157 DEFINE_ERROR(WasmRuntimeError, wasm_runtime_error)
11158 DEFINE_ERROR(WasmSuspendError, wasm_suspend_error)
11159 DEFINE_ERROR(Error, error)
11160 
11161 #undef DEFINE_ERROR

11163 Local<Message> Exception::CreateMessage(Isolate* v8_isolate,
11164  Local<Value> exception) {
11165  auto obj = Utils::OpenHandle(*exception);
11166  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11167  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
11168  i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11169  return Utils::MessageToLocal(
11170  scope.CloseAndEscape(i_isolate->CreateMessage(obj, nullptr)));
11171 }

11173 Local<StackTrace> Exception::GetStackTrace(Local<Value> exception) {
11174  auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*exception);
11175  if (!IsJSObject(*obj)) return {};
11176  auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(obj);
11177  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
11178  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
11179  auto stack_trace = i_isolate->GetDetailedStackTrace(js_obj);
11180  return Utils::StackTraceToLocal(stack_trace);
11181 }
11182 
11183 Maybe<bool> Exception::CaptureStackTrace(Local<Context> context,
11184  Local<Object> object) {
11185  auto i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
11186  EnterV8NoScriptScope<> api_scope{i_isolate, context,
11187  RCCId::kAPI_Exception_CaptureStackTrace};
11188  auto obj = Utils::OpenHandle(*object);
11189  if (!IsJSObject(*obj)) return Just(false);
11190 
11191  auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(obj);
11192 
11193  i::FrameSkipMode mode = i::FrameSkipMode::SKIP_FIRST;
11194 
11195  auto result = i::ErrorUtils::CaptureStackTrace(i_isolate, js_obj, mode, {});
11196 
11197  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> handle;
11198  if (!result.ToHandle(&handle)) return {};
11199  return Just(true);
11200 }
11201 
11202 v8::MaybeLocal<v8::Array> v8::Object::PreviewEntries(bool* is_key_value) {
11203  auto object = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
11204  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
11205  if (i_isolate->is_execution_terminating()) return {};
11206  if (IsMap()) {
11207  *is_key_value = true;
11208  return Map::Cast(this)->AsArray();
11209  }
11210  if (IsSet()) {
11211  *is_key_value = false;
11212  return Set::Cast(this)->AsArray();
11213  }
11214 
11215  Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate);
11216  EnterV8NoScriptNoExceptionScope api_scope(i_isolate);
11217  if (i::IsJSWeakCollection(*object)) {
11218  *is_key_value = IsJSWeakMap(*object);
11219  return Utils::ToLocal(i::JSWeakCollection::GetEntries(
11220  i::Cast<i::JSWeakCollection>(object), 0));
11221  }
11222  if (i::IsJSMapIterator(*object)) {
11223  auto it = i::Cast<i::JSMapIterator>(object);
11224  MapAsArrayKind const kind =
11225  static_cast<MapAsArrayKind>(it->map()->instance_type());
11226  *is_key_value = kind == MapAsArrayKind::kEntries;
11227  if (!it->HasMore()) return v8::Array::New(v8_isolate);
11228  return Utils::ToLocal(
11229  MapAsArray(i_isolate, it->table(), i::Smi::ToInt(it->index()), kind));
11230  }
11231  if (i::IsJSSetIterator(*object)) {
11232  auto it = i::Cast<i::JSSetIterator>(object);
11233  SetAsArrayKind const kind =
11234  static_cast<SetAsArrayKind>(it->map()->instance_type());
11235  *is_key_value = kind == SetAsArrayKind::kEntries;
11236  if (!it->HasMore()) return v8::Array::New(v8_isolate);
11237  return Utils::ToLocal(
11238  SetAsArray(i_isolate, it->table(), i::Smi::ToInt(it->index()), kind));
11239  }
11240  return {};
11241 }

11608 Local<Value> HeapGraphEdge::GetName() const {
11609  i::HeapGraphEdge* edge = ToInternal(this);
11610  i::Isolate* i_isolate = edge->isolate();
11611  switch (edge->type()) {
11612  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kContextVariable:
11613  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kInternal:
11614  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kProperty:
11615  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kShortcut:
11616  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kWeak:
11617  return ToApiHandle<String>(
11618  i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(edge->name()));
11619  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kElement:
11620  case i::HeapGraphEdge::kHidden:
11621  return ToApiHandle<Number>(
11622  i_isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromInt(edge->index()));
11623  default:
11624  UNREACHABLE();
11625  }
11626 }

11672 void HeapSnapshot::Delete() {
11673  i::Isolate* i_isolate = ToInternal(this)->profiler()->isolate();
11674  if (i_isolate->heap()->heap_profiler()->GetSnapshotsCount() > 1 ||
11675  i_isolate->heap()->heap_profiler()->IsTakingSnapshot()) {
11676  ToInternal(this)->Delete();
11677  } else {
11678  // If this is the last snapshot, clean up all accessory data as well.
11679  i_isolate->heap()->heap_profiler()->DeleteAllSnapshots();
11680  }
11681 }

11877 CFunctionInfo::CFunctionInfo(const CTypeInfo& return_info,
11878  unsigned int arg_count, const CTypeInfo* arg_info,
11879  Int64Representation repr)
11880  : return_info_(return_info),
11881  repr_(repr),
11882  arg_count_(arg_count),
11883  arg_info_(arg_info) {
11884  DCHECK(repr == Int64Representation::kNumber ||
11885  repr == Int64Representation::kBigInt);
11886  if (arg_count_ > 0) {
11887  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < arg_count_ - 1; ++i) {
11888  DCHECK(arg_info_[i].GetType() != CTypeInfo::kCallbackOptionsType);
11889  }
11890  }
11891 }

11898 namespace api_internal {
11899 V8_EXPORT v8::Local<v8::Value> GetFunctionTemplateData(
11900  v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Data> raw_target) {
11901  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
11902  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> target = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*raw_target);
11903  if (i::IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*target)) {
11904  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> data(
11905  i::Cast<i::FunctionTemplateInfo>(*target)->callback_data(kAcquireLoad),
11906  i_isolate);
11907  return Utils::ToLocal(data);
11908 
11909  } else if (i::IsJSFunction(*target)) {
11910  i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> target_func = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(target);
11911  auto shared = target_func->shared();
11912  if (shared->IsApiFunction()) {
11913  i::DirectHandle<i::Object> data(
11914  shared->api_func_data()->callback_data(kAcquireLoad), i_isolate);
11915  return Utils::ToLocal(data);
11916  }
11917  }
11918  Utils::ApiCheck(false, "api_internal::GetFunctionTemplateData",
11919  "Target function is not an Api function");
11920  UNREACHABLE();
11921 }
11922 } // namespace api_internal
11923 
11924 RegisterState::RegisterState()
11925  : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr), lr(nullptr) {}
11926 RegisterState::~RegisterState() = default;
11927 
11928 RegisterState::RegisterState(const RegisterState& other) { *this = other; }
11929 
11930 RegisterState& RegisterState::operator=(const RegisterState& other) {
11931  if (&other != this) {
11932  pc = other.pc;
11933  sp = other.sp;
11934  fp = other.fp;
11935  lr = other.lr;
11936  if (other.callee_saved) {
11937  // Make a deep copy if {other.callee_saved} is non-null.
11938  callee_saved =
11939  std::make_unique<CalleeSavedRegisters>(*(other.callee_saved));
11940  } else {
11941  // Otherwise, set {callee_saved} to null to match {other}.
11942  callee_saved.reset();
11943  }
11944  }
11945  return *this;
11946 }

11994 char* HandleScopeImplementer::ArchiveThread(char* storage) {
