11997  MemCopy(storage, this, sizeof(*this));
11998 
11999  ResetAfterArchive();
12000  current->Initialize();
12001 
12002  return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
12003 }
12004 
12005 int HandleScopeImplementer::ArchiveSpacePerThread() {
12006  return sizeof(HandleScopeImplementer);
12007 }
12008 
12009 char* HandleScopeImplementer::RestoreThread(char* storage) {
12010  MemCopy(this, storage, sizeof(*this));
12011  *isolate_->handle_scope_data() = handle_scope_data_;
12012  return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
12013 }
12014 
12015 void HandleScopeImplementer::IterateThis(RootVisitor* v) {
12016 #ifdef DEBUG
12017  bool found_block_before_persistent = false;
12018 #endif
12019  // Iterate over all handles in the blocks except for the last.
12020  for (int i = static_cast<int>(blocks()->size()) - 2; i >= 0; --i) {
12021  Address* block = blocks()->at(i);
12022  // Cast possibly-unrelated pointers to plain Address before comparing them
12023  // to avoid undefined behavior.
12024  if (HasPersistentScope() &&
12025  (reinterpret_cast<Address>(
12026  last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value()) <=
12027  reinterpret_cast<Address>(&block[kHandleBlockSize])) &&
12028  (reinterpret_cast<Address>(
12029  last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value()) >=
12030  reinterpret_cast<Address>(block))) {
12031  v->VisitRootPointers(
12032  Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, FullObjectSlot(block),
12033  FullObjectSlot(last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value()));
12034  DCHECK(!found_block_before_persistent);
12035 #ifdef DEBUG
12036  found_block_before_persistent = true;
12037 #endif
12038  } else {
12039  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, FullObjectSlot(block),
12040  FullObjectSlot(&block[kHandleBlockSize]));
12041  }
12042  }
12043 
12044  DCHECK_EQ(HasPersistentScope() &&
12045  last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value() != nullptr,
12046  found_block_before_persistent);
12047 
12048  // Iterate over live handles in the last block (if any).
12049  if (!blocks()->empty()) {
12050  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr,
12051  FullObjectSlot(blocks()->back()),
12052  FullObjectSlot(handle_scope_data_.next));
12053  }
12054 
12055  saved_contexts_.shrink_to_fit();
12056  if (!saved_contexts_.empty()) {
12057  FullObjectSlot start(&saved_contexts_.front());
12058  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, start,
12059  start + static_cast<int>(saved_contexts_.size()));
12060  }
12061  entered_contexts_.shrink_to_fit();
12062  if (!entered_contexts_.empty()) {
12063  FullObjectSlot start(&entered_contexts_.front());
12064  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, start,
12065  start + static_cast<int>(entered_contexts_.size()));
12066  }
12067 }
12068 
12069 void HandleScopeImplementer::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
12070  HandleScopeData* current = isolate_->handle_scope_data();
12071  handle_scope_data_ = *current;
12072  IterateThis(v);
12073 }
12074 
12075 char* HandleScopeImplementer::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, char* storage) {
12076  HandleScopeImplementer* scope_implementer =
12077  reinterpret_cast<HandleScopeImplementer*>(storage);
12078  scope_implementer->IterateThis(v);
12079  return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
12080 }
12081 
12082 std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> HandleScopeImplementer::DetachPersistent(
12083  Address* first_block) {
12084  std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> ph(new PersistentHandles(isolate()));
12085  DCHECK(HasPersistentScope());
12086  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(first_block);
12087 
12088  Address* block_start;
12089  do {
12090  block_start = blocks_.back();
12091  ph->blocks_.push_back(blocks_.back());
12092 #if DEBUG
12093  ph->ordered_blocks_.insert(blocks_.back());
12094 #endif
12095  blocks_.pop_back();
12096  } while (block_start != first_block);
12097 
12098  // ph->blocks_ now contains the blocks installed on the HandleScope stack
12099  // since BeginPersistentScope was called, but in reverse order.
12100 
12101  // Switch first and last blocks, such that the last block is the one
12102  // that is potentially half full.
12103  DCHECK(!ph->blocks_.empty());
12104  std::swap(ph->blocks_.front(), ph->blocks_.back());
12105 
12106  ph->block_next_ = isolate()->handle_scope_data()->next;
12107  block_start = ph->blocks_.back();
12108  ph->block_limit_ = block_start + kHandleBlockSize;
12109 
12110  DCHECK_EQ(blocks_.empty(),
12111  last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value() == nullptr);
12112  last_handle_before_persistent_block_.reset();
12113  return ph;
12114 }
12115 
12116 void InvokeAccessorGetterCallback(
12117  v8::Local<v8::Name> property,
12118  const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12119  // Leaving JavaScript.
12120  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12121  RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kAccessorGetterCallback);
12122 
12123  v8::AccessorNameGetterCallback getter;
12124  {
12125  Address arg = i_isolate->isolate_data()->api_callback_thunk_argument();
12126  // Currently we don't call InterceptorInfo callbacks via CallApiGetter.
12127  DCHECK(IsAccessorInfo(Tagged<Object>(arg)));
12128  Tagged<AccessorInfo> accessor_info =
12129  Cast<AccessorInfo>(Tagged<Object>(arg));
12130  getter = reinterpret_cast<v8::AccessorNameGetterCallback>(
12131  accessor_info->getter(i_isolate));
12132 
12133  if (V8_UNLIKELY(i_isolate->should_check_side_effects())) {
12134  i::DirectHandle<Object> receiver_check_unsupported;
12135 
12136  if (!i_isolate->debug()->PerformSideEffectCheckForAccessor(
12137  direct_handle(accessor_info, i_isolate),
12138  receiver_check_unsupported, ACCESSOR_GETTER)) {
12139  return;
12140  }
12141  }
12142  }
12143  ExternalCallbackScope call_scope(i_isolate, FUNCTION_ADDR(getter),
12144  v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet, &info);
12145  getter(property, info);
12146 }

12150 inline Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(
12151  const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12152  Tagged<Object> target = FunctionCallbackArguments::GetTarget(info);
12153  CHECK(IsFunctionTemplateInfo(target));
12154  return Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(target);
12155 }
12156 
12157 inline void InvokeFunctionCallback(
12158  const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info, CallApiCallbackMode mode) {
12159  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12160  RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kFunctionCallback);
12161 
12162  Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> fti = GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(info);
12163  v8::FunctionCallback callback =
12164  reinterpret_cast<v8::FunctionCallback>(fti->callback(i_isolate));
12165  switch (mode) {
12166  case CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric: {
12167  if (V8_UNLIKELY(i_isolate->should_check_side_effects())) {
12168  if (!i_isolate->debug()->PerformSideEffectCheckForCallback(
12169  handle(fti, i_isolate))) {
12170  // Failed side effect check.
12171  return;
12172  }
12173  if (DEBUG_BOOL) {
12174  // Clear raw pointer to ensure it's not accidentally used after
12175  // potential GC in PerformSideEffectCheckForCallback.
12176  fti = {};
12177  }
12178  }
12179  break;
12180  }
12181  case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimized:
12182  // CallFunction builtin should deoptimize an optimized function when
12183  // side effects checking is enabled, so we don't have to handle side
12184  // effects checking in the optimized version of the builtin.
12185  DCHECK(!i_isolate->should_check_side_effects());
12186  break;
12187  case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling:
12188  // This mode doesn't call InvokeFunctionCallback.
12189  UNREACHABLE();
12190  }
12191 
12192  ExternalCallbackScope call_scope(i_isolate, FUNCTION_ADDR(callback),
12193  info.IsConstructCall()
12194  ? v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor
12195  : v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation,
12196  &info);
12197  callback(info);
12198 }
12199 } // namespace
12200 
12201 void InvokeFunctionCallbackGeneric(
12202  const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12203  InvokeFunctionCallback(info, CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric);
12204 }
12205 
12206 void InvokeFunctionCallbackOptimized(
12207  const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12208  InvokeFunctionCallback(info, CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimized);
12209 }
12210 
12211 void InvokeFinalizationRegistryCleanupFromTask(
12212  DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
12213  DirectHandle<JSFinalizationRegistry> finalization_registry) {
12214  i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
12215  RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate,
12216  RuntimeCallCounterId::kFinalizationRegistryCleanupFromTask);
12217  // Do not use ENTER_V8 because this is always called from a running
12218  // FinalizationRegistryCleanupTask within V8 and we should not log it as an
12219  // API call. This method is implemented here to avoid duplication of the
12220  // exception handling and microtask running logic in CallDepthScope.
12221  if (i_isolate->is_execution_terminating()) return;
12222  Local<v8::Context> api_context = Utils::ToLocal(native_context);
12223  CallDepthScope<true> call_depth_scope(i_isolate, api_context);
12224  VMState<OTHER> state(i_isolate);
12225  JSFinalizationRegistry::Cleanup(i_isolate, finalization_registry);
12226 }

12276 template <typename T>
12277 bool ValidateFunctionCallbackInfo(const FunctionCallbackInfo<T>& info) {
12278  CHECK_GE(info.Length(), 0);
12279  // Theortically args-length is unlimited, practically we run out of stack
12280  // space. This should guard against accidentally used raw pointers.
12281  CHECK_LE(info.Length(), 0xFFFFF);
12282  if (info.Length() > 0) {
12283  CHECK(info[0]->IsValue());
12284  CHECK(info[info.Length() - 1]->IsValue());
12285  }
12286  auto* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12287  CHECK_EQ(i_isolate, Isolate::Current());
12288  CHECK(!i_isolate->GetIncumbentContext().is_null());
12289  CHECK(info.This()->IsObject());
12290  CHECK(!info.Data().IsEmpty());
12291  CHECK(info.GetReturnValue().Get()->IsValue());
12292  return true;
12293 }
12294 
12295 template <typename T>
12296 bool ValidatePropertyCallbackInfo(const PropertyCallbackInfo<T>& info) {
12297  auto* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12298  CHECK_EQ(i_isolate, Isolate::Current());
12299  CHECK(info.This()->IsValue());
12300  CHECK(info.HolderV2()->IsObject());
12301  CHECK(!i::IsJSGlobalObject(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info.HolderV2())));
12302  // Allow usages of v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() for now.
12303  // TODO(https://crbug.com/333672197): remove.
12304  START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
12305  CHECK(info.Holder()->IsObject());
12306  CHECK_IMPLIES(info.Holder() != info.HolderV2(),
12307  i::IsJSGlobalObject(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info.Holder())));
12308  END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
12309  i::Tagged<i::Object> key = i::PropertyCallbackArguments::GetPropertyKey(info);
12310  CHECK(i::IsSmi(key) || i::IsName(key));
12311  CHECK(info.Data()->IsValue());
12312  USE(info.ShouldThrowOnError());
12313  if (!std::is_same_v<T, void>) {
12314  CHECK(info.GetReturnValue().Get()->IsValue());
12315  }
12316  return true;
12317 }

12321  return ValidateFunctionCallbackInfo(info);
12322 }

12361 ExternalMemoryAccounter::~ExternalMemoryAccounter() {
12362 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12363  DCHECK_EQ(amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12364 #endif
12365 }
12366 
12367 ExternalMemoryAccounter::ExternalMemoryAccounter(
12368  ExternalMemoryAccounter&& other) {
12369 #if V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12370  amount_of_external_memory_ =
12371  std::exchange(other.amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12372  isolate_ = std::exchange(other.isolate_, nullptr);
12373 #endif
12374 }
12375 
12376 ExternalMemoryAccounter& ExternalMemoryAccounter::operator=(
12377  ExternalMemoryAccounter&& other) {
12378 #if V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12379  if (this == &other) {
12380  return *this;
12381  }
12382  DCHECK_EQ(amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12383  amount_of_external_memory_ =
12384  std::exchange(other.amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12385  isolate_ = std::exchange(other.isolate_, nullptr);
12386 #endif
12387  return *this;
12388 }
12389 
12390 void ExternalMemoryAccounter::Increase(Isolate* isolate, size_t size) {
12391 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12392  DCHECK(isolate == isolate_ || isolate_ == nullptr);
12393  isolate_ = isolate;
12394  amount_of_external_memory_ += size;
12395 #endif
12396  isolate->AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryImpl(
12397  static_cast<int64_t>(size));
12398 }
12399 
12400 void ExternalMemoryAccounter::Update(Isolate* isolate, int64_t delta) {
12401 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12402  DCHECK(isolate == isolate_ || isolate_ == nullptr);
12403  DCHECK_GE(static_cast<int64_t>(amount_of_external_memory_), -delta);
12404  isolate_ = isolate;
12405  amount_of_external_memory_ += delta;
12406 #endif
12407  isolate->AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryImpl(delta);
12408 }
12409 
12410 void ExternalMemoryAccounter::Decrease(Isolate* isolate, size_t size) {
12411  internal::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
12412  if (size == 0) {
12413  return;
12414  }
12415 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12416  DCHECK_EQ(isolate, isolate_);
12417  DCHECK_GE(amount_of_external_memory_, size);
12418  amount_of_external_memory_ -= size;
12419 #endif
12420  i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
12421  i_isolate->heap()->UpdateExternalMemory(-static_cast<int64_t>(size));
12422 }

12426  const Isolate* isolate) {
12427  const i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<const i::Isolate*>(isolate);
12428  return i_isolate->heap()->external_memory();
12429 }
